title: layered bean dip "trader joe's"(so easy, it's almost embarrassing!)
directions: Purchase the tortilla chips, spicy black bean dip, fresh salsa and cheeses from Trader Joe's.
Spread the beans in an ovenproof, shallow casserole dish.
Top with the salsa, then the cheese. Bake in a 350° oven until heated through and cheese is melted. Top with chopped ripe avocado; sprinkle with cilantro.
Add "dollops" of sour cream and garnish with chopped black olives. Serve with chips.

title: e-z brownies
directions: Flour and grease a 9 x 11-inch pan.
Melt butter.
Sift and mix together dry ingredients.
Add vanilla with beaten eggs and mix with the butter.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into pan. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Mix the flour and salt in a large bowl.
Cut in shortening with fork or pastry blender until pea size crumbs are formed. Combine cold water, vinegar and egg in a small bowl.
Add to flour mixture, stirring until mixture can be formed into a ball. Divide in half and roll out to 1/8-inch thickness on a lightly floured surface.
Line bottom of 9-inch pie plate with 1/2 of dough.
Use other half for the top crust.

title: ribbon salad
directions: An 8 x 8-inch pan works well.
Dissolve lime jello and let set (package directions).
Dissolve marshmallows and cream cheese in lemon jello, dissolved in 2 cups boiling water.
Let partially set and then add pineapple and whipped cream to mixture and let set. Top with cherry jello and let set.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Grease casserole.
Beat eggs slightly; add sugar, flour and pineapple and mix.
Put in casserole.
Cube or crumble bread over mixture.
Slice butter over all and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve with main dish or after meal.

title: poppin fresh barbecue cups
directions: Preheat oven at 400°.
In large skillet, brown beef and onions.
Drain.
Add barbecue sauce and brown sugar.
Separate dough into biscuits.
Place each biscuit in an ungreased muffin cup.
Press dough up sides.
Spoon meat mixture into cups.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Sprinkle with cheese. Serve.

title: pineapple cake dessert
directions: Mix the yellow Jiffy cake mix according to directions on the package.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 12 to 15 minutes (cake will be thin).
Cool.
Mix well the vanilla instant pudding and 2 cups milk.
In another bowl, mix cream cheese with 1/2 cup milk. Combine cream cheese mixture with pudding mixture and pour over cake.
Sprinkle pineapple over pudding mixture.
Top cake with Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain. Rinse with cold water; drain. Mix macaroni and remaining ingredients. Serve on salad greens. Yields 4 servings.

title: grandma jones' corn dish
directions: Fry bacon, onion and green pepper in skillet until tender. Add corn and tomatoes.
Let simmer for 15 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chuck wagon steaks
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add egg and 3/4 cup barbecue sauce. Shape into patties.
Place in oblong pan.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Pour other 3/4 cup barbecue sauce on patties during last 15 minutes of cooking.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Mix and bring to boil butter, cold water and cocoa;
pour into dry ingredients. Add eggs, vanilla, buttermilk and soda.
Beat again.
It will look thin.
Grease and flour 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
If glass, bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in top of double boiler over rapidly boiling water.
Beat with electric mixer for seven (7) minutes or until the mixture holds a peak.
Remove from heat and add vanilla. Beat well and spread on cake.

title: hot punch
directions: Put liquids in coffee pot.
Put spices in top.
Perk.
Makes 30 to 36 cups.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on high 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Turn to low to serve with tortilla chips.

title: lime cake
directions: Mix cake mix and Jell-O together. Add eggs, oil and juice and mix well. Pour into greased and floured cake pans. Cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: grape salad
directions: Mix sour cream and sugar.
Add softened cream cheese to sour cream mixture.
Add vanilla and stir.
Add mixture to grapes.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: In large mixer bowl place instant pudding, sour cream, milk and orange peel.
Beat at low speed, scraping bowl often until thick and well mixed.
By hand, fold whipping cream.
In a large bowl layer 1/2 of cake pieces, 1/3 strawberries and 1/2 of pudding mixture.
Repeat layers.
Arrange remaining strawberries on top. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except eggs and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Chill dough.
Roll dough in balls and then into confectioners sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Brown butter in a heavy skillet, this should be golden brown for good flavor.
Beat egg yolks in a bowl.
Add milk, brown sugar, salt and flour.
Mix well.
Add to browned butter in skillet.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool and add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell and cover with meringue.

title: peanut cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Roll in balls.
Dip in sugar.
Bake at 375°for 10 minutes.

title: egg pie crust
directions: Put egg in measuring cup and beat with a fork; add the vinegar and enough milk to make one cup.
Add to dry ingredient mix.
This makes 3 (2-crust) pies.
Can be frozen to use later.

title: sweet-n-sour chicken
directions: In large shallow microwave-safe dish, toss chicken with 2 teaspoons soy sauce and ginger.
Cut pepper into strips.
In large bowl, combine vinegar, water, cornstarch and 2 teaspoons soy sauce; mix well.
Stir in pineapple chunks and their syrup and the pepper strips.
Microwave on High (100%), stirring once, 3 minutes or until sauce is thickened.
Cover chicken with waxed paper; microwave on High for 6 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes with slotted spoon.
Add chicken to pineapple mixture.
Serve with cooked rice.

title: cranberry fluff salad
directions: The night before, puree cranberries and sugar in blender. Place in covered bowl, add marshmallows, stir and chill overnight. Before serving, add fruits, nuts, and salt.
Fold in whipped cream and chill. Serve in lettuce cups.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add pumpkin gradually, alternating with milk.
Mix sugar and spices together and add.
Add melted butter and vanilla. Pour into pie shells and bake in hot oven for few minutes, then bake in a slow oven, about 325°, until firm.
Makes 2 large pies.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs with a whisk or fork until blended.
Add sugar slowly and mix together.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well. Pour into ice cream container.
If necessary, add milk to finish filling container.
Freeze in ice cream freezer until ready to eat. If you have any left for the freezer, the ice cream will remain soft, if put in container with a cover.

title: taco dip
directions: Beat cream cheese; blend in rest of ingredients.
Spread evenly on cookie sheets with sides.
Top with your choice: shredded cheese, lettuce, tomato, olives, etc.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: reese's peanut butter squares
directions: Combine
1 1/2 sticks melted butter, graham crackers, peanut butter and sugar.
Pat tightly in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine 1/2 stick melted butter and melted chocolate and pour over top.
Chill and cut.

title: quick and easy ground beef crescent bake
directions: Mix the browned and drained ground beef, Ragu, sour cream and cheese.
Pour into a large casserole dish sprayed with a nonstick spray.
Top with a crust made from the rolls.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat oil and sugar with mixer.
Add eggs 1 at a time.
Add pumpkin.
Sift together dry ingredients and beat in.
Add nuts. Bake in loaf pans (greased and floured) until no longer sticky in the middle, about 50 minutes to 1 hour at 325°.
Cool 10 minutes in pans.

title: mrs. rock's strawberry delight
directions: Slice strawberries and put in sugar.
Add the pineapple. Chill before serving.

title: no bake orange juice cookies
directions: Mix together; roll into small balls.
Roll in coconut which can be tinted with food coloring.
Makes 48.
Refrigerate.

title: beth's irish soda bread
directions: Combine all dry ingredients, including caraway seed and raisins, in large bowl.
Mix all together.
In separate bowl, combine egg, milk and sour cream.
Add to dry mixture, 1/3 at a time and mix well until all moistened.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
May place in round or square pan.

title: pinwheels
directions: Mix cream cheese and dressing together. Add pimentos and chilies. Spread evenly over the 4 tortillas. Roll tightly. Refrigerate to set. Slice and serve.

title: tuna mousse appetizer
directions: Dissolve the Knox gelatine in the hot water.
Cool until it thickens to a syrupy consistency.
Whip together the cream cheese, soup, tuna and mayonnaise.
Fold in the gelatine mixture.
Add the diced vegetables.
Pour into a six cup mold and refrigerate until firm.
Unmold onto a plate lined with lettuce leaves.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix beef and next 3 ingredients.
Form into walnut size balls. Roll in a mixture of flour and paprika.
Brown in 1/4 cup margarine.
Pour off excess grease.
Simmer in soups and water for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: happy child
directions: Mix with generous parts of good humor and understanding. Blend in discipline as needed.
Surround with music, love of nature, pets and friends.
Bake in a warm, pleasant atmosphere. Baste frequently with love and affection.
Use a large amount of patience.
Do not be discouraged if at times, object does not seem to be turning out to your perfection.
Continue basting.
Before you realize it, your delight turns out even better than you had ever planned.
Release, when properly aged.

title: "secret salad number 2" delicious apricot
directions: Make jello and add rest of ingredients.
You can use fruit cocktail and mixed jello or strawberries and strawberry jello.
If you use sugar-free jello and lite Cool Whip, this can be a diet dessert.

title: helen reese's peanut butter pie
directions: Blend by hand the cream cheese.
Add peanut butter and milk until smooth.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Place in the cookie pie crust and freeze.
When firm, add a large jar of chocolate ice cream topping to cover the top of the pie.
Keep in the refrigerator until ready to cut.

title: my man's cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla, blend well.
Add dry mixture and mix well.
Stir in corn flakes, coconut, and pecans.
On baking sheet drop teaspoon size balls of cookie dough.
Bake at 350 degrees for 8 to 12 minutes.
Flatten slightly with a fork when you take them from the oven.
Cool.

title: chocolate peanut butter fudge(fast and easy)
directions: Melt margarine, vanilla, cocoa and peanut butter on stove (do not boil).
Remove from heat and mix in powdered sugar.
Place in 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Allow a few hours to set.

title: sticky buns
directions: Grease Bundt or tube pan; sprinkle a few nuts in the bottom of the pan.
Arrange frozen rolls in bottom; drizzle with melted margarine.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Sprinkle remaining nuts on top then top with dry pudding.
Cover with towel and let set overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecued peanuts
directions: Preheat the oven to 250°. In a saucepan, combine the liquid smoke, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco and water. Bring to a simmer. Turn off the heat and stir in the peanuts. Let the peanuts sit in the liquid for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Drain off the liquid and spread the peanuts in a shallow roasting pan. Bake for at least 1 hour or until good and dry. (Stir occasionally to help speed up the process.) When the peanuts are thoroughly dry, melt the butter and stir it into the
peanuts to coat. Sprinkle lightly with garlic salt. Yield: 3 servings.

title: minted cucumber salad
directions: Sprinkle cucumbers with salt; let stand 15 minutes on paper toweling.
Rinse and drain well; blot liquid.
Mix cucumbers with green pepper, onion, yogurt, lemon juice, oil, garlic and chopped mint.
Cover and chill 30 minutes to blend flavors.
Serve on fresh lettuce.
Garnish with mint leaves.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese dressing
directions: Cook together, thickening with a little flour if necessary. Serve as sauce over asparagus, onions, cauliflower or cabbage.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
Chop mushroom stems finely. In frypan, melt butter over low heat.
Add onion and cook until onions are transparent, about 2 minutes.
Add chopped mushroom stems to onions and continue cooking until soft, about 3 minutes. Add bread crumbs, 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese and salt to mushroom mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Using a teaspoon, mound mixture in hollows of mushroom caps.
Sprinkle mushrooms with remaining cheese.
With butter, grease bottom of 8-inch square pan.
Place mushrooms in pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken souffle (or tuna)
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread cubed bread in pan.
Mix tuna or chicken, green pepper, onion, mayonnaise, salt, pepper and celery and spread over cubed bread.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix together with mayonnaise or salad dressing.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: With fork, beat cream cheese until smooth and soft.
Stir in pineapple, 1/2 cup pecans, onion, green pepper, beef and seasoned salt.
Mix well.
Shape into ball.
Roll in remaining 1/2 cup pecans.
Chill overnight.
Set out 1/2 to 1 hour before serving.

title: miss christine's crazy coolers
directions: Put cranberry or grape juice into ice cube trays and freeze. For a twist, add juice cubes into glass of apple juice.
Kids really enjoy the crazy cubes and the juice add a variety to the plain apple juice.

title: amish friendship bread
directions: Pour into 2 well-greased and sugared loaf pans.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Pass along these instructions with 1 cup of starter to friend.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Dredge a 9-inch pie plate with margarine and flour.
Beat egg. Add the sugar; continue beating until thoroughly blended.
Add the flour, sifted, with the baking powder.
Add apples and nuts. Pour into pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: easy pate
directions: Soften braunschweiger to room temperature, then mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown in skillet the ground chuck and onion.
Remove from heat and stir in kidney beans and salt and pepper.
Combine in a large salad bowl the lettuce, tomatoes and tortilla chips.
Put meat and bean mixture in a bowl.
May use the Chili Tomato Sauce recipe or taco sauce of your choice.
Serve meat and bean mixture over salad mixture (individual servings).
Put chili sauce or taco sauce over the mixture.

title: persimmon pudding(this is a good thanksgiving and autumn dish)
directions: Strain persimmons and milks through a sieve.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in a 375° oven until it shrinks away from sides of the pan.

title: green chili enchiladas(large recipe; 375~.)
directions: Brown meat. Drain. Mix in taco seasoning according to directions on seasoning and cook.

title: wassail
directions: Bring apple cider and cinnamon stick to a boil.
Cover; simmer for 5 minutes.
Add nutmeg, honey, lemon juice, lemon rind and pineapple juice
to cider.
Slice orange.
Stick whole cloves into orange slices.
Float orange slices on top.
Serve hot.
Serves 18 to 20.

title: new potatoes gratiner
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Trim mushroom stems flush with cap.
Thinly slice lengthwise.
In large bowl, toss potatoes, mushrooms, onion, parsley, 2 ounces cheese, garlic, salt, pepper and 1 1/2 tablespoons melted butter.
Place in prepared dish.
Mix 1/4 cup warm water with 1 1/2 cups heavy cream and pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
As soon as cheese browns, cover with loose tent of foil and continue baking.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Beat egg and add with juices. Gradually blend egg/juice mixture with flour.
Cook over low heat until thick while stirring constantly.
Remove from stove and add butter.
Cool.
Mix with fruit and chill.

title: crunchy banana muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 12 muffin tin pans with Pam vegetable spray.
Mix and spoon into muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until tops are golden brown and toothpick tests clean.
Makes 12 servings.

title: beef provencale
directions: Trim excess fat off meat.
Remove tendon.
In a skillet, heat butter until lightly brown.
Add meat.
Brown well on all sides. Sprinkle with half the salt and pepper.
Reduce heat.
Cover.
Let meat cook for about 10 minutes, turning once during cooking time. Remove meat.
Cover with foil.
Place on a carving board.
Add water to pan.
Heat.
Scrape up brownings.
Strain juices.
Peel potatoes.
Slice thinly.
Layer potatoes on a lightly greased ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle remaining salt in between layers.
Pour pan juices over.
Bake potatoes at 425° for about 30 minutes. Remove from oven.
Cut beef into 8 even slices.
Place on top of potatoes.
Stir together softened butter, minced garlic and parsley.
Spread butter over meat.
Heat at 425° for about 8 minutes.
Serve.

title: beef steak and tortilla bake
directions: Brown round steak in oil in skillet; season with salt and pepper.
Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid.
Add enough water to reserved liquid to measure 1 1/4 cups.
Add to steak.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Add tomato sauce, enchilada sauce, mushrooms, 1/2 cup onion and garlic; mix well.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Dip tortillas, one at a time in sauce; place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spoon 2 teaspoons onion along one side of tortilla; roll up to enclose onion.
Arrange in baking dish. Stir 3/4 cup cheese into sauce; spoon sauce over tortillas.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: fettucine with cayenne, scallops, bacon and cream
directions: Fry bacon.
Reserve 1/2 of drippings in pan with bacon.
Add and saute the scallops with remaining ingredients except cream, for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add cream and heat briefly.
Serve over fettucine or other pasta.
Serves 8 as first course or 4 as main course.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger.
Slice and heat Polish sausage.
Combine all ingredients and bake for 1 hour at 400° or put in crock-pot and cook on high until bubbly.
Reduce heat to low and cook 1 more hour.

title: swedish nuts
directions: If using almonds, roast first for 15 minutes at 325° and cool. Melt the margarine in a large 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Beat egg whites until foamy. Add sugar and salt and then beat egg whites until stiff. Fold in the nut meats. Spread in pan over melted margarine. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, turning gently every 10 minutes. If desired, add cinnamon or nutmeg. Will keep for weeks if tightly sealed. Do not refrigerate.

title: tuna roll
directions: Mix everything except 1/2 of the parsley. Shape into a ball and roll in remaining 1/2 of parsley. Serve with a variety of crackers.

title: taco pie
directions: Press biscuits into 9-inch pie pan.
Brown turkey.
Add bouillon, onions, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Cook mixture, then add tomato paste, water and taco seasoning.
Put 1/2 meat mixture into unbaked crust.
Add 1/2 cheese, then remaining meat and cheese.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown meat and chives or onions.
Drain.
Mix soup, eggs and spices; add beef, mushrooms and cheese on top.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°, then 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon deluxe bars
directions: Mix and pour on top of the crust you just baked.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: potato soup
directions: Prepare potatoes for soup, cutting them into small squares. Place with chopped onion and seasoning in pan with water to simmer until tender.
Add milk slowly while stirring and warm.
Do not boil.
Float on butter and cheese if wanted.

title: vegetable pasta salad
directions: Cook and cool vegetables.
Toss vegetables, noodles and dressing.
Add tomato halves and tuna.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream the first 6 ingredients until well blended. Then add the remaining ingredients. Mix well. Spread in 9 x 13 greased and floured pan. Sprinkle 1/4 cup chocolate chips on top before baking. Bake at 325° for 40 or 45 minutes. This cake needs no icing.

title: orange loaf
directions: Spray loaf pan.
Preheat oven 350°.
Combine all ingredients and pour into pan.
Bake for 60-65 mins.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together with spoon until well blended.
Add the beaten eggs and hot water.
Mix all together very well.
Grease very well 5 nut loaf pans.
Pour batter evenly into the pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Let sit for a few minutes after coming from the oven.
Remove carefully from pans and brush with melted margarine and then sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Let cool, then store in plastic food bags. Easily frozen until ready for use.

title: funnel cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Fry in hot oil.

title: pate hush-hush
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Heat consomme; add gelatin and sherry.
Put aside to cool.
Mix cream cheese, pate, bourbon, Worcestershire sauce and seasonings thoroughly (an electric mixer is easiest).
Oil a flat mold with vegetable oil.
Pour cooled consomme into the mold to the depth of about 1/4 inch and put it into the freezer to set quickly.

title: turkey pasta salad
directions: Cut turkey into 1/2-inch cubes; set aside.
Combine pasta, spinach and dressing.
Place mixture in large, lettuce-lined salad bowl.
Sprinkle with cheese and pepper to taste.

title: cookie jar sugar cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar. Add egg.
Beat until mixture is light and fluffy. Add vanilla and grated orange peel. Mix thoroughly. Sift dry ingredients.
Stir into creamed mixture together with milk.
Divide dough in half.
Chill 1 hour, keeping the other chilled until you're ready to roll it.

title: crisp pickle slices(bread and butter)
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; cover with cracked ice or ice cubes.
Mix thoroughly.
Let stand 3 hours; drain thoroughly. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Heat just to boil.
Seal in hot, sterilized jars. Yield:
5 pints.

title: hot fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix other ingredients; pour over fruit.
Bake for 1 hour, uncovered, at 325°.
This will serve a large group.

title: hillbilly beans
directions: Cook bacon in a skillet until crisp.
Remove bacon and add chopped onion. Cook until tender.
Mix all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook for 2 hours.

title: dark chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pans.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Beat on medium for 2 minutes.
Stir in boiling water.
Bake 30 minutes (use toothpick test).
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Once cooled, cake can be frosted.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Blend cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add cherries, pineapple and marshmallows.
Whip the cream and add last.
Put in container and freeze.
(Can use ice trays.)

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in large kettle.
Bring to boil; lower heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Strain and serve hot.

title: ham rolls
directions: Combine onion, poppy seed, butter, mustard and worcestershire sauce in sauce pan.
Bring to a boil.
Cook till onions are clear. Slice rolls lengthwise.
Spoon on bottom layer of rolls.
Add ham and close.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: sandy's noodle pudding
directions: Cook noodles seven minutes and drain.
In a large bowl, blend softened cream cheese and cottage cheese.
Add milk, sugar, vanilla, melted butter and raisins.
Beat eggs and add to mixture with noodles.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix altogether.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: aunt mag's pound cake(no milk pound cake)
directions: Cream together, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, salt and vanilla.
mix together.
Start in a cold oven at 325°.
Bake about one hour.

title: quick and easy squares
directions: Place first two ingredients into double boiler and melt.
Let cool, then add marshmallows.
Pour into pan and refrigerate before cutting into serving pieces.

title: chinese delights
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels, add Chinese noodles and peanuts. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Makes 60 delights.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pat into microwavable bread loaf pan.
Microwave on Level 8 for 3 minutes.
Do 3 times.
Then microwave for about 30 seconds to 1 minute on High.

title: easy stew
directions: Put all ingredients into casserole or roasting pan and cover. Bake in 250° oven, for 4 hours.
Stir several times during baking. Do not brown meat.
During cooking, this will turn to a dark brown gravy.

title: sweet potato fries
directions: Heat oven to 525 degrees. Place melted butter into large bowl, add sweet potatoes, toss to coat. Add chili powder, parmesan cheese, salt and red pepper, toss to coat potatoes. Arrange sweet potatoes in single layer on greased baking pan. Bake for 20-25 minutes, turning once, until golden brown. Serve with chili flavored burgers for a great meal.

title: chocolate snowballs
directions: Mix all together, then add in 6 syrup cans of water.
Mix and put in containers to freeze or store in large plastic ice cream container.
Makes 5 gallons.

title: nana's israel stew
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add onions, corned beef and potatoes. When potatoes are almost done, add rest of ingredients.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: glorified chicken
directions: In 2-quart oblong baking dish, arrange chicken, skin side down.
Drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Spoon soup over chicken.
Bake for 20 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink and juices run clear.
Stir sauce before serving. Makes 4 servings.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Beat egg and sugar together until smooth.
Sift the flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add to egg mixture, then add apples, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into a well-greased pan and bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan while still hot and cut into squares.
Chill and serve with whipped cream.

title: cloud cookie puffs
directions: Soften cream cheese in a bowl.
Add Cool Whip, powdered sugar and drained pineapple; mix well.
(If mixture is stiff, add a very small amount of the saved juice until softer.)

title: egg in a cup
directions: Place egg in cup.
Fill with water.
Place cup in coals.
(Do not allow fire to touch top of cup where there is no liquid.
The cup may become dry and scorch or burn.)
Egg will boil in cup.

title: double boiler frosting(seven-minute frosting)
directions: Mix ingredients with beater for 1 minute in top of double boiler.
Place over boiling water.
Beat with egg beater about 7 minutes or until thick.
Remove from heat; add flavoring. Continue to beat until almost cold or until it holds its shape. Frost cake or cookies.

title: low-fat chocolate brownie supreme
directions: Beat margarine at medium speed of an electric mixer until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar and beat well.
Add egg whites, sour cream, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients; stir well.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Pour batter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Frost.

title: west indies salad
directions: Combine ingredients in a Tupperware bowl; stir well.
Cover with airtight lid and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Serve with favorite crackers.
(This appetizer gets better the longer it marinates.)

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook frozen broccoli, omitting salt.
Drain thoroughly.
Place broccoli in baking dish (10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch).
Stir together the soup and shredded cheese.
Gradually add milk, mayonnaise and egg to soup mixture.
Pour over broccoli.
Combine bread crumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle over soup mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until crumbs are lightly browned.

title: angel hair with prosciutto
directions: Rinse the mushrooms, dry and cut caps into thin strips.
Core the tomatoes and cut into cubes.
Cut Prosciutto into very thin strips.
Put snow peas in a saucepan and add water to cover. Bring to a boil and simmer one minute.
Drain.

title: green tomato pickle
directions: Slice the tomatoes and onions very thin.
Cut peppers in very thin strips.
Sprinkle the vegetables with the salt and let them set overnight.
Drain them well.
Mix all the other ingredients and bring to a boil, then pour over the vegetables and cook slowly for 1 hour.
Bottle when cold.

title: quick banana pudding
directions: Use a large bowl. Prepare instant pudding as package directs. Next, mix Eagle Brand milk, then Cool Whip. Stir in vanilla wafers and sliced or diced bananas.
Lay a few vanilla wafers over mixture to decorate. Serves better if chilled for about 2 hours.

title: endless coleslaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine cabbage, bell pepper and onion; set aside.

title: orange bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Add orange rind, orange juice, sugar, salt and shortening.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead about 10 minutes.
Place dough in a warm greased bowl.
Brush with melted shortening.
Cover and let rise double in bulk.
Punch dough down.
Divide in two equal portions and mold into balls.
Let rest closely covered for 10 minutes.
Shape into loaves.
Place in 2 greased loaf pans.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place quartered chicken in baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients in pan; bring to a boil.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Yields 4 servings.
Contains 125 calories per serving.

title: percolator punch
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in 25 cup percolator.
Add next 4 ingredients to percolator basket and run through coffeepot cycle.

title: lemon fruitcake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add lemon extract.
Sift flour and baking powder together, then add small amount of flour mixture to cake, beating well after each addition.
Then last, add the nuts, raisins, cherries and pineapple.
Mix thoroughly.

title: oven barbecued ribs
directions: Advance preparation:
In Dutch oven, add salted water to ribs to cover.
Cover pan; simmer until almost done, about 1 hour. Drain ribs.
Place in shallow baking pan.
In saucepan, combine 1 cup water, salt, ketchup and next 6 ingredients.
Bring to boil. Cook and stir 5 minutes.
Add onion and lemon.
Cool.
Spoon over ribs; cover.
Chill up to 24 hours.
Before serving, bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Baste often.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate - nut zucchini cake
directions: Grease and flour a tube pan.
Melt the 3 squares of chocolate in a double boiler.
Mix all the dry ingredients and set aside. Beat 4 eggs until thick and light.
Gradually add the 3 cups of sugar to the eggs, beating well.
Add vanilla and salad oil.
Mix with a beater the egg mixture, chocolate and dry ingredients.
Mix in the zucchini and nuts with a big spoon.
Bake in greased tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool on a rack before removing from pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
This cake freezes well.

title: sausage cheese bites
directions: In a skillet, cook and crumble sausage.
Drain.
In a large bowl, combine biscuit mix and cheese.
Add the sausage and stir until well blended.
Stir in water just until mixed.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.

title: white surprise
directions: Heat white almond bark in microwave about 4 minutes.
Place all other ingredients into a large bowl.
Pour melted almond bark over stuff in bowl and drop onto wax paper.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix apples, sugar and cinnamon in bowl.
In separate bowl, mix all other ingredients with a spoon until smooth.
Layer in Bundt pan (coated with Pam) 2 layers of apples and 2 layers of batter (alternate 1 apple layer, 1 batter layer).
The top layer should be apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour 10 minutes.

title: chicken squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In medium bowl, blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons margarine until smooth.
Add the next six ingredients and mix well.

title: peanut soup(goober slurry fuel)
directions: In saucepan, saute onions in butter.
Add brewers yeast, rice, flour and peanut butter and mix well.
Gradually add milk and cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Add tomato juice; continue cooking until soup is hot.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Rinse sauerkraut and drain well.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Mix well and let stand overnight.
Serve chilled.

title: gateau de pain(bread pudding)
directions: Cut crust off the bread.
Place in a bowl and add milk.
In another bowl, cream butter until light and fluffy.
Add sugar and beat until smooth.
Add yolks, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add orange rind, spices, raisins and bread.
Blend with a wooden spoon.
Beat the egg whites until soft peaks appear.
Add the 1/4 cup sugar and beat until stiff.
Fold into the bread mixture.
Put into buttered square baking pan and sprinkle generously with sugar and place into pan filled with warm water. Bake in preheated 325° oven for 40 to 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Serve hot or cold with sauce.

title: reindeer crunch
directions: Mix together first 5 items in a large bowl. In a saucepan, melt the baking chips and half and half. Add to the dry mixture; toss to coat. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper. Let set for 1 hour. Cover loosely to store.

title: quick milk shakes
directions: Cut frozen berries into small chunks.
Place in blender or food processor with other ingredients and process until smooth. Yields 2 to 3 servings.

title: fricidillies
directions: Mix meat, bread, salt and pepper.
Beat eggs, add milk, then mix thoroughly with meat.
Melt Crisco in skillet.
Drop meat by teaspoonful.
Brown and place in slightly buttered pan.
Blend 1 can mushroom soup and 3/4 cup water.
Pour over meat and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Cook the potatoes with the skins on, then peel potatoes. Crumble the bread.
Place all ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Cover with 1-inch of milk.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: seafood newburg
directions: Cut fish into bite size pieces.
Shell and devein shrimp, if using fresh.
In margarine, cook the mushrooms until tender; remove to bowl.
Melt 4 tablespoons margarine.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Blend and cook 1 minute.
Stir in half and half and milk. Stir until smooth.
Add fish, shrimp, peas, crab, sherry and mushrooms.
Cook until fish flakes easily.
Add cheese and pimentos.
Simmer gently 5 minutes.
Serve over biscuits.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serves 8.

title: hunter's stew
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven.
Dredge meat in flour and brown in oil.
Add onion and mushrooms.
Cook until onion browns.
Drain if necessary and return to pot.
Add 2 cups of beef stock, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally and add beef stock as necessary until meat is tender.
Peel potatoes and cut into small cubes.
Peel and shred carrots.
Add to meat. Continue to cook until vegetables are done.
Garnish with parsley.

title: delicious dessert
directions: Mix together flour, melted butter and 1/2 cup chopped pecans. Press in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Prepare pudding and milk according to directions.
Cool and put on second layer.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding mixture.
Top with toasted coconut or chopped pecans.

title: christmas kraut
directions: Heat sugar and Karo together until sugar dissolves.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
(Does not have kraut taste.)

title: white cake
directions: Add 2/3 cup milk to Crisco, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Blend for 1 minute.
Add rest of milk, eggs and vanilla. Beat 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: domino pound cake
directions: Blend sugar, salt, nutmeg and lemon rind in large bowl.
Cream sugar mixture and butter until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla. Blend flour into creamed mixture gradually; continue blending until mixed.
Beat eggs in mixture one at a time, beating well after each one.
When smooth, turn batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Let it stand in airtight container at least 24 hours before serving.

title: creole cake
directions: Mix well and pour into large 3-inch deep loaf pan.
Cook 20 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet and sour beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain on paper towel.
Add chopped onion to bacon fat and cook until soft.
Add brown sugar and vinegar; mix well.
Add drained beans and heat a few minutes. Crumble the bacon and sprinkle over beans before serving.
Serves 4.

title: surprise meat balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Roll in small balls; place in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 2 1/2 hours at 250°.
Remove from oven; drain and pour barbecue sauce over meat balls.
Return to oven for about 1/2 hour.

title: sandwich filling
directions: Mix cheese, salad olives, salt and pepper and eggs.
Then add mayonnaise to make mixture spreadable.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Cook on low for 8 hours, covered.
Add beans, if desired (pinto or red kidney beans).
Have sliced onions and oyster crackers with your chili.
Serves 10 or more.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Make cake mix as directed on box.
Meanwhile, simmer pineapple and sugar.
Remove cake from oven.
Punch holes in it and pour pineapple and sugar mixture over top.
Chill.
Mix instant pudding; spread over pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with pecans.

title: brownies
directions: Mix ingredients as listed.
Bake in oven for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken pie like dressing
directions: Cook onions and celery in chicken broth; add salt, pepper, poultry seasoning and chopped eggs. Pour over breadcrumbs. Layer dressing and layer chicken, etc. Pour cream of chicken soup over this. Bake at 350° to 375° until brown.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: In mixing bowl combine egg, melted oleo, broccoli, corn, onion, salt, pepper & 3/4 stuffing mix. Put in casserole dish and sprinkle remaining stuffing mix on top. Onion rings may also be added to top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn salad(with french dressing)
directions: Drain corn and pimiento.
Chop the pimiento into tiny bits and mix with corn, onion, green pepper and cucumber. Combine with French dressing and mix well. Chill and serve on large lettuce leaves.

title: apple dessert
directions: Beat egg, sugar and salt together.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add to sugar and egg.
Fold in diced apples, vanilla and nutmeats.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch pan at 375° for 35 minutes. Serve with heavy cream.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef, chopped onion and green pepper.
Add 1 package taco seasoning. Bring to a boil all the canned vegetables. Stir all together. Use Doritos instead of crackers.
Top with Cheddar cheese and sour cream.
You may use half and half, beef and turkey.

title: incredibles candy
directions: Combine butter and graham cracker crumbs.
Beat in peanut butter and sugar.
Spread over bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Frost with melted chocolate.
Chill to harden frosting.
Before frosting is set, cut into about a dozen pieces.

title: maine raspberry pie
directions: Combine
ingredients in a saucepan and cook over medium heat until
thickened.
Add
1 tablespoon butter.
Cool a bit and
pour over
3 cups of fresh, uncooked berries in a cooked pie shell. Chill and serve with whipped cream.

title: sausage balls
directions: Pour all ingredients into large bowl.
Mix with hands until well blended and no longer dry.
Shape into balls no larger than a walnut.
Place apart on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes, or until lightly brown.
Should be turned over or rolled once.
(May be frozen and cooked later.)

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in a large bowl.
Mix all other ingredients in bowl with butter.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam and pour mixture in dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle with cheese; bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spring salad
directions: Cook pasta until done.
Drain in cold water.
Chop pepperoni, green pepper, onion, cucumbers and add to pasta.
Slice black olives and pour cheese in.
Add italian dressing and chill in fridge for 1 hour.

title: uncle scott's barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil; stirring frequently.
Boil 1 minute.
Cool and enjoy on any meat.

title: white chocolate crispies
directions: Melt chocolate and oil in double boiler or in microwave oven 5 to 6 minutes at 350°.
Pour over 6 cups of crisp cereals and nuts. Mix.
Put on waxed paper, using a tablespoon.
Good for Christmas!

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Soften margarine.
Crush vanilla
wafers,
mix with milk and blend into a creamy
mixture.
Add
coconut,
walnuts
and salt. Blend together well.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325° in a tube pan.

title: lemon pie(for 9-inch pie)
directions: Mix 3/4 cup sugar, 3 tablespoons cornstarch and salt well. Grate rind of lemon into dry ingredients.
Add juice of lemon and egg yolks and mix well.
Add a few drops water, if necessary. Boil water and add lemon mixture.
Boil 2 or 3 minutes.
Add butter.

title: screaming stuffed jalapeno poppers(barbecue)
directions: Mix each package of cream cheese with chopped garlic, sun-dried tomatoes and a dash of chopped basil. Add a pinch of salt. Mix until mixture is soft and manageable. Slice each jalapeno lengthwise on one side, being careful not to cut the jalapeno in half. Remove the seeds if you can't handle the heat. Depending on the pepper, you may have to slice around the stem of the pepper to create a manageable opening to squeeze the filling in. Fill either a pastry bag or use something that will allow you squeeze and put your filling inside the jalapeno pepper. Be careful to not overfill the pepper; it may squirt while cooking. Wrap each pepper with 1 to 2 strips of bacon, securing the opening in the pepper to soak toothpicks first to prevent burning in the barbecue. Barbecue peppers until they are lightly roasted or until bacon is fully cooked. Cook time is approximately 10 minutes. Prep time: 30 minutes. Yields 10 to 25 poppers.

title: oatmeal-nut muffins
directions: Mix well oatmeal, flour, sugar, soda, salt and baking powder. Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Beat together egg and buttermilk; pour over flour mixture.
Add nuts. Stir just until dry ingredients are moist.
Spoon into 12 greased muffin tins.

title: heath bar chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake as directed and cool.
Using wooden spoon handle, poke holes in cake.
Pour condensed milk into holes and top with butterscotch caramel sauce.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle Heath bars on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: kevin's favorite creamed chipped beef
directions: In bowl, soak chipped beef in hot water until softened, then drain.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour and stir until blended. Whisk in milk and stir over medium heat until thickened, about 2 minutes.
Add chipped beef and season to taste.
Serve over toast or biscuits.

title: no oil cake
directions: In large bowl, combine all the ingredients in order.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Insert toothpick; it should come out clean if done.

title: my rolls(yield: 80 pocketbook rolls)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; pour boiling water over this. Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to first mixture.
Cool a little; combine, then add eggs.
Slowly add flour (about 4 cups), then beat thoroughly, slowly adding remaining flour (2 1/2 cups). Place in large greased bowl in refrigerator overnight to rise. Cover with plastic wrap.
(Could be used in a few hours.)

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute garlic in large skillet briefly.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to boil, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Leftovers may be frozen for future use.

title: sausage stew
directions: Place
all ingredients in pot.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Add 1/2 to 3/4 pound of spirals or bows.
Simmer until noodles are cooked. May put in crock-pot and simmer all day.
Put noodles in 2 hours before serving.

title: spinach dip
directions: Stir 1 package soup mix, sour cream and mayo until blended. Thaw spinach and squeeze dry.
Stir in spinach, water chestnuts and onions.
Cover; chill 2 hours before serving.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Follow package directions for pound cake mix except omit liquid and substitute sour cream.
Beat all ingredients well. Pour mixture into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° in oven for 60 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: puffy potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes, mash but don't add milk.
Add in cream cheese, sour cream and salts.
Beat up with electric beater.
Put in casserole.
Dot with butter and paprika.
Bake for one hour at 350 degrees.

title: spice apple cake
directions: Bring apples, raisins, sugar, Crisco, allspice, cloves, nutmeg, cinnamon, salt and boiling water to a boil and boil for 15 minutes. Cool.
Add flour and soda. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° until done (glossy on top or until a toothpick comes out clean).

title: creamed cabbage
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add cabbage.
Stir and let butter cover all the cabbage well.
Cook about 5 to 10 minutes.
Add salt, pepper, sugar and cream.
Mix well.
Cover and simmer about 5 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: rainbow pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to
package
directions; drain and cool by running cold water
over
pasta.
Add Italian dressing and toss pasta.
Add remaining
ingredients	and
toss
evenly through salad.
Chill in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: cranberry fruit salad
directions: Blend sugar and mayonnaise into softened cream cheese.
Add cranberry sauce and pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts. Chill.

title: microwave chili salsa dip
directions: Microwave sausage and onion for 6 to 7 minutes, or until sausage is cooked.
Drain off grease.
Add tomato sauce and salsa; mix well.
Place Gouda cheese in a 10-inch pie plate or a shallow 1 1/2-quart serving dish.
Pour salsa mixture over cheese. Microwave 5 to 6 minutes, or until hot and cheese melts.
Serve with your favorite corn chips.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Melt chocolate in the top of a double boiler.
In a large bowl, mix together oil and sugar.
Stir in melted chocolate.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Stir in flour, salt and baking powder.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Wrap dough in plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight or for at least 2 hours.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare greased cookie sheets.
Roll dough into walnut-sized balls and then roll balls in confectioners sugar.
Place balls 1-inch apart on cookie sheets and bake for 10 minutes or until cookies have white cracks on top showing chocolate beneath.
Cookies will crack on top.
Remove cookies to a wire rack to cool.
Yield:
7 dozen.

title: chocolate oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and cool.
Mix other ingredients in order given and beat well.
Bake in flat pan for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix all ingredients well.
Top with Rice Krispie crumbs mixed with 4 tablespoons melted butter. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate-peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk, cocoa and syrup until it forms a soft ball when dropped in glass of cold water.
Remove from heat; add butter, peanut butter and vanilla.
After cooled, beat until creamy.
Pour into greased dish.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Boil chicken breasts and save broth.
Remove the skin.
Cook spaghetti in the chicken broth and then drain.
Chop chicken in bite-size pieces.
Also chop onion and peppers.
Combine chopped chicken, onion, pepper with soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Place in casserole dish.

title: morning rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a medium bowl.
Microwave until apples are tender.
Serve.
Makes 2 servings; contains 340 calories and 1.2 gm fat.

title: spanish bean soup(guiso de garbanzos)
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil in large pot (cast-iron preferred).
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and cover pot.
Cook until potatoes are done.
Do not add salt.
There is enough in the ham and sausage to flavor the soup.
If lower fat is preferred, omit the ham hock or refrigerate and skim.

title: my great grandmother's plum pudding
directions: Soak together bread crumbs and milk.
Beat egg yolks until creamy.
Chop suet fine and salt.
Cut citron into small pieces. Put all together; steam in tight container or bag for 3 to 4 hours.

title: banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine condensed milk and water.
Add pudding mix; beat well and chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Using a 2 1/2-quart dish, layer wafers, bananas and pudding; repeat. Sprinkle wafer crumbs on top.

title: dennis kiker's slaw
directions: Mix well and put in refrigerator.
It is better if you let it sit for two days before you eat it.

title: pennsylvania dutch apple cake
directions: Mix the ingredients in order given.
The batter will be very thick.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
This may be served warm with vanilla ice cream, or:

title: fried spinach balls
directions: Mix ingredients and let stand 15 minutes so crumbs can soak up moisture.
Make in balls.
Dip in 1 egg, beaten with 4 tablespoons water.
Roll in cracker crumbs or meal and fry 3 minutes in oil.

title: holiday potatoes
directions: Cool potatoes; remove skin and shred.
Saute onion in 1/4 cup butter until tender; remove from heat.
Stir in soup and sour cream.
Pour over potatoes.
Add cheese.
Mix well.
Turn into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Combine cake mix, salad dressing, eggs, water and cinnamon. Mix at medium speed.
Stir in carrots and walnuts.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch greased baking pan and bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: rice salad milano
directions: Spoon rice into large mixing bowl.
Blend oil, juice, garlic and seasonings.
Stir into rice.
Let cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve at room temperature or chill.
Makes 6 servings.
Per serving:
127 calories, 3.1g protein, 10g fat, 21.5g carbohydrates, 22 mg sodium and 2 mg cholesterol.

title: fig muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter; add sugar gradually.
Add eggs and blend until light.
Sift together flour, baking powder and spices, alternating with milk to creamed mixture.
Stir in mashed figs and pecans.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in small greased muffin pan.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: batter fried shrimp
directions: Combine flour, eggs and beer until the right consistency and allow to set for 1 to 2 hours.
When ready to use, beat 2 egg whites and fold into batter.
Dry and season shrimp.
Dip shrimp in batter and deep fry in shortening or oil.

title: caramel corn
directions: In a saucepan, combine oleo, sugar and syrup; boil 5 minutes. Add cream of tartar.
Stir in soda.
Pour over popcorn.
Mix well. Pour coated popcorn into a buttered pan.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Great for a snack.

title: corn on the cob
directions: Remove the husks from fresh ears of corn; scrub with a stiff brush to remove silks.
Rinse.
Wrap each ear in waxed paper; place on paper towels in the microwave.
Cook on high power 3-5 minutes for 1 ear, 5-7 minutes for 2 ears, or 9-12 minutes for 4 ears.

title: company squash casserole
directions: Place squash and onion in pan, cover with water and cook 5 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Melt 3 tbsp. margarine in heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour and cook 1 minute. Gradually add milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick and bubbly.
Add cheese and stir to melt.
Stir in squash mixture and mushrooms.
Add salt and pepper.
Spoon into greased casserole.
Melt remaining margarine and stir in cracker crumbs. Sprinkle mixture over squash.
Bake.

title: christmas fruit cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 Christmas tree cake pans.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves in large bowl.
Stir in eggs, reserve 1 white for icing, melted butter, sugar and applesauce; blend well.
Stir in dried fruit, raisins and walnuts, mix well.
Spread in prepared pans.
Pans will be almost full.
Bake for 45 minutes or until center springs back when lightly touched with fingertip.
Cool in pans on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans, cool completely.
Layers may be wrapped and refrigerated a week before use.
May use Snow White Icing.

title: crab souffle
directions: Cream cream cheese and mayonnaise; add remaining ingredients, except Worcestershire, and mix.
Add a couple of drops of Worcestershire.
Bake in a greased souffle dish at 350° for 30 minutes, until light brown and bubbly.
Serve as a dip or spread with Triscuits or other crackers.

title: white baked beans
directions: Put beans in baking dish.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Pour bacon and grease over beans; add other ingredients; stir.
Bake at 350° for 3 to 4 hours.
Keep beans warm when serving!

title: mom's ginger cookies
directions: Combine first 7
ingredients
and
beat
until	smooth. Sift flour and soda together.
Add half of the flour to Crisco mixture and blend.	Blend in buttermilk.
Add remaining flour. Mix well. Measure out
level	tablespoons of dough on Crisco-coated baking sheet.
Flatten
cookies by stamping with a flat bottom glass covered with sugar.
Bake
in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes. Yields:
6 1/2 dozen.

title: arnold's cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake
at 350° for 25 minutes (three 8-inch pans or two 9-inch pans).

title: strawberry heaven
directions: Place bottom cake layer on serving platter. In a mixing bowl, stir crushed strawberries and mix into 1 cup whipped topping. Spread half of the strawberry mixture onto cake layer. Top with second cake layer. Repeat layers, ending with cake. Frost top and sides of cake with remaining whipped topping. Refrigerate 1 hour or until ready to serve.

title: chocolate salad dressing cake
directions: Mix sugar and salad dressing.
Add water, then flour, soda and cocoa into ingredients.
Lastly, add vanilla.
Bake in 350° oven.

title: linguini vegetable
directions: Cut vegetables into small pieces.
Add entire bottle of dressing and Salad Supreme.
Add linguini and stir together. Chill about 2 hours before use.

title: barbecue hamburgers("will feed 50 leaguers")
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add onion, celery, green pepper and other ingredients.
Mix well and let simmer until onions, celery and green peppers are tender.
You will need a good sized pot to cook this in after you finish browning all the hamburger. Serve on hamburger buns.

title: bourbon street shrimp
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter.
Add soup and sour cream.
Mix well.
Add the rest of ingredients and simmer.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: just married quick chicken
directions: Thaw chicken breast. Stab holes in chicken with fork, then place chicken in baking dish. Cover chicken with chicken broth. Season to taste with salt, pepper, black pepper, cloves, etc.

title: sugar-free oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix well the oil, applesauce, eggs and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop onto a greased sheet.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: joyce's brunch casserole
directions: Save 1/2 cup of each cheese for topping.
Mix and beat eggs, add cottage cheese, Jack and Cheddar cheese, crackers, chilies and ham.
Pour into buttered or Pam-sprayed 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, covered (with foil).
Then top with mixed remaining cheeses.
Bake, uncovered, for 10 minutes more.
Let set 5 minutes before cutting.
Can be frozen.
Serve with salsa for those who like it hotter.

title: strawberry rhubarb freezer jam
directions: Cut up and cook rhubarb with 1 cup and a small amount of water.
After cooking, mix jello (just the powder) and add strawberries.
Ladle into plastic containers 3/4 full.
Freeze until used.
Good for 4 weeks when removed from freezer.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Save broth where chicken is cooked to cook spaghetti in.
Cook celery, onions and green pepper in butter until color changes.
To this, add soups, salt and pepper; simmer for 15 minutes.
Then add chopped chicken.
Mix additional ingredients to drained, cooked spaghetti.
Pour into a long shallow pan.
Put grated cheese on top.
Cook in a 350° oven until cheese is melted well.
Serves 20 people.
Freezes well.

title: pepper chicken
directions: Put chicken
in a single layer in a pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.	Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: carol's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix well.
Put on meat the last 20 minutes of cooking.

title: cherry fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Place sausage in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with rice, celery, soup mix, water and almonds. Cover and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: clam casserole
directions: Drain clams.
Add milk to clam juice to make 1 1/2 cups.
Melt butter in medium saucepan; stir in flour.
Cook until bubbly, stirring constantly.
Stir in milk mixture.
Cook until thickens; boil 1 minute more.
Remove from heat and cool.
Beat in egg and clams.

title: old fashioned chocolate gravy
directions: Mix well and cook over low heat, stirring continuously.
Serve over hot biscuits.

title: hamburger stew(my grandchildren like this stew.)
directions: In a large kettle, boil the meat in a gallon of water (add more if needed) until tender.
Add all of the other ingredients, except the barley.
Boil 45 minutes, then add barley.
Stir often and cook 30 minutes more.
Remove bone before serving.
Serve with crackers.
You can freeze this soup in containers, if desired. Serves 12 to 20 people.

title: raspberry squares
directions: Add the sugar to 1 1/2 cups flour; add baking powder, salt, nuts and softened oleo.
Mix at medium speed until blended.
Add lemon peel and beaten egg, stirring with fork until moistened. Remove 1/2 cup dough.
Pat the rest in a 9 x 9-inch greased pan. Add to reserved dough 2 tablespoons flour and roll between 2 sheets of waxed paper to 9-inch square size.
Place in freezer for 5 minutes.
Spread jam over dough in pan, leaving 1/4-inch border.
Take dough from freezer and peel off waxed paper.
Cut in strips.
Place strips crosswise over jam.
In small bowl, combine egg
yolk and water.
Brush over dough.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: garlic roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a baking pan, place potatoes. Sprinkle with garlic and oil, turning potatoes to coat all sides. Sprinkle with salt and pepper and a liberal coating of paprika. If desired, stir in chopped onions.
Bake for 30 minutes.
With spatula, loosen potatoes and turn them over. Bake until tender, 15 to 20 minutes longer.
Makes 4 servings.

title: capered mushrooms
directions: Drain mushrooms.
Combine mushrooms, onion, garlic, Italian dressing and capers in small covered container.
Marinate for 1 to 2 days in refrigerator.

title: chocolate crunch brownies
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients; spread in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until tests done, remove.
Put marshmallows evenly over brownies, return to oven about 2 minutes. Let cool.
In saucepan or microwave, melt peanut butter and chocolate chips, stir in cereal, spread over marshmallow layer.

title: grandma's apple pie
directions: Mix egg, margarine,
flour,
salt,
sugar
and vanilla. Dice enough apples to
fill
unbaked
pie crust.
Pour mixture over apples in pie crust.
Bake	at
350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until apples are brown.

title: abby's pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well; pour into unbaked pie crust shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until set.
Cool.
May serve with Cool Whip topping.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients well, just until smooth. Pour into three 8-inch cake pans (greased and floured).
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes. Cool completely.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Fry the hamburger meat; drain.
Slop tortillas through grease. Chop onions; grate cheese.
Bring to a boil the soup and water. Add the chili peppers to soup.
Fill tortillas with meat, cheese and onions.
Roll and place in pan.
Top tortillas with remaining meat, cheese and onions.
Pour soup over tortillas.
Bake in moderate (approximately 350°) oven until soup bubbles, approximately 20 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Wash peppers; cut off tops and remove seeds. Mince and brown onion in oil. Pour into bowl and add meat. Wash rice, then add salt, pepper and beaten egg. Mix well. Fill each green pepper almost to top with mixture. Place peppers in deep pot. Pour on tomato sauce and enough water to cover. Simmer about 1 hour or until rice is cooked.

title: pound cake
directions: Warm butter to room temperature.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well between eggs.
Add flavorings. Slowly add flour a little at a time.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: mashed potatoes and turnips
directions: Cook turnips, covered, in small amount of boiling salted water, for 10 minutes.
Add potatoes and onion and cook until tender.
Drain well.
Mash vegetables with butter, salt and pepper.
Adjust seasonings to taste.
Serve hot.

title: peanut sticks
directions: Roll pie crust to 1/8 inch thickness.
Spread with layer of peanut butter about 1/16 inch thick.
Fold all four of outside edges into the center; roll to 1/8 inch thickness again.
Cut into strips 1/2 inch wide from 4 to 6 inches long.
Place in hot oven and bake until delicately brown.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Stir together sour cream and mayonnaise until blended. Stir in seasonings. Refrigerate. Serve with raw veggies or with chips.

title: pound cake
directions: Hold eggs and butter overnight at room temperature.
With a large bowl, beat eggs first, then add butter (one stick at a time).
Add other ingredients and beat well.
Pour batter into a floured pound cake pan and bake for 1 hour and 40 minutes on top rack at 300°.
Take care at end of time and let it cool for 20 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Combine beef, onion, 1 aig, 1 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon peppah, 1/4 cup braid crumbs.
Press in a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake fur 15 minutes in a 425° oven 'n then pore off fat.

title: p. j.'s rice pudding
directions: Put rice in large casserole dish; add sugar and 2 quarts milk and stir.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and add raisins.
Add several chunks of butter (about 1/3 cup).
Bake at 350° for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours or when rice is done.
Stir occasionally or use wire whisk to make it creamy.
You may have to add milk.
Do not let pudding go dry.
Last, add vanilla.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Saute ground beef, onion and garlic in skillet until beef loses redness; drain fat.
Add seasonings, Manwich and water; simmer 3 to 5 minutes.
In a 2-quart casserole, arrange alternate layers of tortillas, meat sauce and cheese until all used up. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: millie's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together the sugars, shortening, egg and water.
Add vanilla.
Mix together flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to sugar mixture, then add oats, raisins and/or nuts.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and cooking oil well together.
Add apples and nuts; mix well, then add flour and flavor.
Put into well greased tube pan.
Put in cold oven.
Turn on to 325°.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: amish cookies
directions: Mix oil, butter and sugar well.
Add eggs and beat until its white and fluffy.
Then add remaining ingredients and blend well. Spoon onto a greased cookie sheet and flatten.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in a jar with a tight fitting lid.
Add 1 to 2 teaspoons of mixture to 1 cup of hot water and serve.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Add next 5 items.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles in boiling water; drain and rinse.
(Start this when meat is simmering.)
Combine rest of items, except Mozzarella cheese, in bowl.

title: cranberry jello
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Stir in whole cranberry sauce and ginger ale.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan or mold.
Chill until firm.

title: peanut-popcorn balls
directions: Mix brown sugar, corn syrup, peanut butter and salt. Microwave on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until mixture begins to bubble. Stir. Stir in popcorn and peanuts until well coated.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Shape mixture firmly into four 3-inch balls with hands dipped in cold water.
Place onto waxed paper.
Let stand about 30 minutes or until completely cooled. Wrap in plastic wrap.
Yields 4 popcorn balls.
Contains 310 calories per ball.

title: brunch souffle
directions: Butter all the bread on both sides.
Place six slices in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle on half the cheese and half the ham.
Repeat bread, cheese and ham.

title: outrageous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat first 6 ingredients in bowl with wooden spoon until creamy and well blended.
Add dry ingredients; stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate until served.

title: turkey-rice casserole
directions: Combine rice, soup and chicken broth in a 2-quart casserole. Cover and cook on High in the microwave for 10 minutes.
Stir in turkey, mushrooms and salt and pepper.
Cover and cook on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until rice is cooked.
Let stand 5 minutes. Great use of leftover turkey!

title: chicken pan pie
directions: Boil eggs and chicken.
Debone chicken and cut up with eggs. Mix remainder of ingredients.
Bake at 325° after placing ingredients in pie crust.
Cook until crusts are golden brown.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in jello powder.
Let cool.
Combine with strawberries and pour into pie shell.
Add Cool Whip for topping.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie crust.
Mix 1 cup sugar and 4 tablespoons cornstarch. Mix into 1 cup water.
Boil until thickened and clear, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add 1 box strawberry Jell-O.
Let cool completely, add strawberries.
Mix well.
Put in shell when cool.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Makes 1 pie.
Double to make 2 pies.

title: golden puffs
directions: Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir with fork until mixed.
Drop by teaspoon into hot oil, 360°.
Fry until golden brown, about 3 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar or dip in glaze.
Cook 6 at a time.

title: tangy glazed ham
directions: Preheat oven to 450. Trim visible fat off ham and place ham in roasting pan. Reduce heat to 350. Bake 1 1/2 hours. Dissolve cornstarch in pineapple juice. Combine with butter buds, brown sugar, cloves, allspice in small saucepan; mix well and heat until thick. Add pineapple and pour over ham. Bake 1 1/2 hours, basting with glaze until done.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle graham crumbs over butter.
Sprinkle nuts over crumbs.
Scatter morsels over nuts.
Sprinkle coconut over morsels.
Pour milk over coconut. Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes. Cut in bars.

title: lemon filling
directions: Place all ingredients, except flour and eggs, in pan.
Cook over low heat until butter melts and sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat; stir vigorously.
Add flour and slightly beaten eggs. Return to low heat and cook until mixture coats back of spoon.

title: ting-a-lingslubbock, texas
directions: Melt chips in double boiler.
Mix dry ingredients in bowl, pour melted chips over and mix, drop on wax paper and chill.

title: puppy chow for people
directions: Melt the first 3 ingredients together in a saucepan and pour over cereal.
Pour powdered sugar in a large Tupperware container or Ziploc bag.
Add coated Crispix.
Close the container and toss until evenly coated with sugar.
Dry on foil and store in airtight container.

title: honey fruit glaze
directions: Combine all together; mix well.
Brush on chicken or ham during last 10 minutes or roasting.
Makes 1/2 cup.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients and 1/2 to 1/3 of chipped beef together.
Form into a ball and roll in remaining chipped beef. Serve on assorted crackers.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Put diced rhubarb in unbaked pie shell.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over rhubarb.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Heat olive oil in skillet, add chicken and remaining ingredients.

title: lemon lace cookies
directions: Mix together cake mix, Cool Whip and egg until well blended. Take 1 teaspoon and roll it in confectioners sugar and put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
(Chocolate cake mix could be used instead of lemon.)

title: oatmeal candy cookies
directions: In a large sauce pan, combine margarine, cocoa, milk, sugar and salt.
Boil for two minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, stir in vanilla.
Add oats and nuts.
Drop by the teaspoonful onto wax paper.
Let cool.
Store in an airtight container.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Refrigerate butter, juice, chives, tarragon and salt and pepper mixture for 1 hour.
Cut breasts in half.
Put scoop of mixture in center.
Fasten with toothpick, folding butter in center.
Roll in water, slightly beaten eggs and flour.
Roll in bread crumbs. Brown all sides in hot oil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken diable
directions: Wash chicken; pat dry.
Melt butter; stir in remaining ingredients.
Roll chicken in mixture to coat.
Arrange meaty side up in a single layer in same pan.
Bake at 375° oven for one hour. Serves 4.

title: potato soup
directions: Heat water in soup kettle.
Add potatoes, onion and celery. Cook 1/2 to 1 hour, then mash a few times.
Beat egg, salt and water together in small bowl.
Slowly add flour.
Mixture will be gooey.
Drop by teaspoon into boiling soup mixture.
The dough will drop to bottom of kettle, then rise to the top.

title: spanish rice with beef
directions: Brown meat, onion and green peppers.
Add tomatoes, rice, pepper and salt.
Cook over low heat for 25 minutes.

title: lemon butter icing
directions: Blend butter
and
sugar; stir in lemon juice and peel. Beat until smooth and of spreading consistency.

title: golden glow pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt onto cukes.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain.
Add vinegar, sugar and spices.
Cook vegetables until tender.
Jar and seal.

title: salmon cheese ball
directions: Mix together all ingredients except nuts and parsley.
Make into ball.
Roll in nuts mixed with parsley.
Wrap and chill.

title: corn cob jelly
directions: Break cobs in half.
Boil in water for 8 to 10 minutes. Strain and use 3 cups of liquid (add water if necessary to make 3 cups).
Add food coloring.
Add Sure-Jell.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Add sugar.
Boil hard or until when tested with a fork the tines fill up.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in margarine.
Mix corns, cornbread mix and eggs.
Add with sauteed mix.
Put in large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: In soup kettle, cook potatoes and onion in water with bouillon until tender.
Mash potatoes and blend in blender or mixer until fairly smooth.
Add seasoning.
Melt butter and add flour.
Whisk into hot soup.
Gradually add scalded milk; cook, stirring constantly, as soup thickens.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Just before serving, add cream.
Garnish each bowl with parsley flakes.

title: brownies
directions: Cook pudding mix and milk to almost the thickness if you were making a pie.
Quickly stir in dry cake mix.
Stir with spoon.
Do not beat!

title: trout
directions: Fill a 9-inch bowl 1/4 way full with 1/2 mixture of flour and corn meal.
Add salt and pepper.
Roll trout in flour mixture and fry in a thin layer of butter.
Brown on both sides and serve.

title: joan's peanut butter cups
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter together.
Stir in powdered sugar thoroughly.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chips together. Spread over peanut butter layer.
Cool.
Cut with warm knife.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine soup, milk, parsley and pepper.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole, arrange alternate layers of potatoes, onion and sauce. Dot top with butter; sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes more or until potatoes are done.

title: mexican swizzle sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix butter, sugar, egg and vanilla; blend in flour.
Mix in 2 envelopes premelted chocolate and cinnamon.
With star plate, form 4-inch figures on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Frost with chocolate glaze.

title: baked king or spanish mackerel(6 servings)
directions: Brush the fish lightly with olive oil.
Sprinkle well with salt.
Place portions close together in a well-buttered pan. Sprinkle cut portions with paprika.
Pour hot milk in the pan to the depth of 1/2-inch.
Place in oven heated to 350° and bake until the fish is browned on top.
Baste 3 to 4 times during the baking.

title: baked haddock
directions: Grease pan with Crisco.
Lady haddock in pan.
Mix together the Town House crackers (crushed), melted butter and Mozzarella cheese.
Pour over haddock.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: apricot-coconut balls(a no bake recipe!)
directions: In large bowl, combine apricots, coconut, walnuts and condensed milk; mix well.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Roll ball in powdered sugar.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields 8 to 10 dozen candies.

title: meatball vegetable
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and make balls or small patties.
Roll in flour and brown on both sides.
Add potatoes, peas, carrots, onions, water, salt and pepper.
Cook on low heat until everything is tender.
Also good to add corn or other vegetables.

title: harvest stew
directions: Mix all ingredients, except corn, potatoes and zucchini in greased baking dish with lid.
Bake for 2 hours and 30 minutes at 325°; stir occasionally.
Add corn and potatoes; bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir in zucchini.
Cover and let stand 10 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown chops in a skillet and drain. In a greased 2-quart oblong dish, arrange potatoes, mushrooms and chops.

title: summer salad
directions: In saucepan, heat lime jello and pineapple until starts to boil.
Remove from heat.
Let cool.
Add buttermilk, Cool Whip and nuts.
Put in jello mold until firm in refrigerator.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in square baking dish. Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Serve with Triscuits.

title: mexican food casserole
directions: Brown the first 4 ingredients in a large skillet with small amount of oil.
Add the Ro-Tel, green chilies and soup.
Layer mixture in 2 layers with corn tortillas; begin with corn tortillas, ending with meat mixture in greased pan.
Cover with grated cheese. Cover pan and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: canned slaw
directions: Mix together the mustard, vinegar and sugar.
Bring to a boil. Add cabbage and other ingredients.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake in a preheated oven at 400° for 1 hour or until done (pierce potatoes before baking).
As soon as the potatoes are cool enough to handle, halve each one lengthwise and carefully scoop the pulp out into a medium bowl and set the shells aside.
Mash the pulp with a hand mixer and then beat in the buttermilk, onion and butter.
Spoon the mix into the potato shells and sprinkle with paprika and Parmesan cheese or put Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes.

title: pennsylvania dutch potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in their jackets.
When soft, peel and dice.
Add celery, parsley, sliced eggs and onion.
Fry bacon until crisp and brown.
Combine beaten eggs, sugar, mustard, salt, pepper and vinegar diluted with water.
Mix well.
Pour egg mixture into the hot bacon and drippings.
Stir until mixture thickens, about 10 minutes.
Pour over the potato mixture and mix lightly.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 10 servings.

title: chicken breast supreme
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with a slice of bacon and secure with a toothpick.
Grease bottom of casserole and line with chipped dried beef.
Mix sour cream and mushroom soup.
Pour over chicken. Bake, uncovered, in a 275° oven for 3 hours.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together and put in a buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook chicken, debone and save 5 cups of broth.
Saute the celery, mushrooms and onion together in 2 tablespoons butter. Butter a Pyrex 9 x 13-inch dish.
Layer chicken and veggies.
Add 2 cans of chicken soup to the 5 cups of broth.
Pour over dish. Break 12 ounces raw spaghetti over dish.
Add the Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°, uncovered.
(Make ahead and then warm in microwave to serve.)

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients together one minute and add next 4 ingredients.
Mix together and drop by spoonful on wax paper. Flatten out like cookies if you wish and let them dry or chill.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat well until smooth.
Pour into uncooked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, or until knife comes out clean.
Makes 2 pies.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onions in 1 tablespoon of butter.
Cook broccoli as directed on package and drain.
Mix all ingredients together, except Durkee onions, and place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.
Add onions on top last 5 minutes.
Bake longer if not quite set.

title: trout almondine
directions: Season the trout with salt and pepper; dredge trout with flour.
In a large skillet, heat the oil to moderately high heat. Add the fillets.
Saute the fillets until golden brown on both sides.
Transfer trout to paper towels to drain; keep warm.
Melt butter.
Add almonds and saute until light golden brown; pour the almond mixture over the trout and garnish with lemon and parsley. Serves 4.

title: baby food cake
