directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Bake in a tube pan. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Baking time may vary, depending on individual ovens, so be sure to check early.

title: hot seafood pie "one-dish" dinner
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups potato chips and margarine.
Press into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes; cool.
Combine crab meat, shrimp, celery, green pepper, onion, lemon juice, salt, pimento and mayonnaise in large bowl; stir well.
Spoon mixture into potato chips crust.
Combine remaining chips and cheese; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, or until cheese melts.

title: aunt ceil's custard pie
directions: Bake for 50 to 60 minutes in an unbaked pie shell at 325°.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Combine water, cloves and cinnamon.
Heat to boil and remove from heat.
Add tea bags.
Cover and seep for 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
Combine sugar and juices.
Heat to boil, then combine with first mixture.
Serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: new south supper
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add cooked onion, then add cheese, soup, milk and Mexicorn.
Cook together until all blended.
Cook noodles of your choice.
Add cooked noodles to meat mixture and serve immediately.

title: vista balls
directions: Combine and shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Roll balls in 2/3 cup grated Cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Chill well.

title: angel food cake
directions: Allow egg whites to set at room temperature for 1 hour before mixing.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift 4 times onto a sheet of wax paper the cake flour and 3/4 cup sugar.
In large mixer bowl, combine egg whites, cream of tartar, salt, almond and coconut extract.
Beat on speed 12 or high until egg whites form soft peaks.
Do not overbeat.
Turn to speed 8 (medium) and rapidly sprinkle in remaining 1 cup of granulated sugar.
Scrape sides of bowl, as necessary.
Turn to speed 1 or low and gradually add sifted flour mixture.
When all sifted flour mixture has been added, stop mixer and using a rubber spatula, cut through batter several times, folding over and over.
Spoon batter into an ungreased 10 x 4-inch tube pan.
Push batter to edges of pan all around.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted into center of cake comes out clean.
Immediately invert on a funnel or bottle neck and allow to cool completely.
Then carefully run a clean spatula around edges of the pan.
Loosen around bottom and lift off.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook and slice chicken.
Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain and arrange broccoli in bottom of an 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking casserole.
Place chicken on broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, curry powder and cheese; pour over chicken.
Combine crumbs and margarine; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash. Drain and mash. Add all ingredients (except margarine and cracker crumbs).
Place in 2-quart casserole, greased.
Top with crumbs and dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. (Suitable for freezing.)
Serves 6 to 8.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease 9-inch x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle pecans and coconut in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix according to package directions. Pour over pecans and coconut.
Beat cream cheese and softened margarine.
Add sugar.
Drizzle over raw cake dough.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chewy blond brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In large pan beat together sugar and butter until well blended. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spread into prepared pan. Bake about 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add lemon juice.
Cool. Cream together the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add jello; mix well.
Fold whipped Milnot into gelatin mixture.
Crush graham crackers into fine crumbs; add melted butter.
Firmly pack 2/3 of crumb mixture in bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add filling; sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Chill several hours.

title: rutabaga-apple casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 1-quart baking dish.
Cook rutabaga until just tender.
Drain.
Place 1/2 of rutabaga and 1/2 of apple slices in baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of brown sugar. Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with salt.
Repeat layers.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In a large saucepan, combine soup, 1/2 cup milk, onion, cream cheese, celery, carrots, Parmesan cheese and salt.
Cook until hot and cheese is melted.
Stir in chicken and broccoli. Heat.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart dish.

title: low-fat chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine margarine, applesauce, sugars and cinnamon; blend. Add egg, salt, baking soda and vanilla; mix.
Blend in flour.
Add chocolate chips and stir.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken & rice combo
directions: Combine crushed crackers, almonds, 1 tsp. each salt and dill weed, paprika, and pepper. Dip chicken pieces in melted butter, then roll in seasoned crumbs to coat.

Combine rice, water, and remaining salt and dill weed in greased 9x13 baking dish. Place chicken, skin side up in same dish. Pour remaining butter and crumbs over top. Cover tightly with foil. Bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes. Remove foil, stir around edge of dish. Continue baking uncovered for 25-30 minutes.

title: zucchini cheese pie
directions: Beat eggs with a fork.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well. Place mixture in 8 x 8-inch greased baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken and dressing in one pan
directions: Put chicken in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put soup on top of chicken.
Mix together eggs, onion, milk and dressing mix.
Put mixture on top of soup.
Pour 1/2-inch chicken broth on top of this.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bunuelos
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and sugar.
Combine beaten eggs and milk.
Fold in dry ingredients.
Knead dough on floured board as you do for bread.
Make into small balls.
Roll out as thin as you can (stretch them a little more by hand just before you put them in frying pan).
Fry in hot shortening about 1 minute on each side or until light brown.
Prick with fork as you fry them.
Take out.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon while still hot.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook and drain carrots.
Cut onion and pepper into strips. Combine in heatproof bowl.
Combine soup (do not dilute), oil, sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Simmer over medium heat; pour over carrots.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serve cold.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Cook zucchini, onion and margarine 10 minutes.
Stir in rest of ingredients (spices).
Combine eggs and Mozzarella cheese; stir in zucchini mixture.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top. Can be refrigerated overnight. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool; refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Spread with cherry pie filling.
Makes 8 servings.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Spray 12 muffin cups with vegetable oil cooking spray or line with paper cooking cups. Combine dry ingredients. Add milk, egg and oil; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened. Fold in blueberries; fill muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: coconut falooda
directions: Combine agar-agar, salt, and sugar in water and boil over medium heat for 15 minutes.
Add coconut milk and mix well using wire whisk.
Simmer for 10 more minutes.
Pour mixture into 1-1/2 qt. glass dish.
Let it cool on countertop until completely set. Do not move dish around during this time.

title: luscious fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding mix, milk and orange juice with wire whisk until blended.
Add sour cream.
Fold in fruits.
Place all in large bowl; cover and refrigerate overnight.
Add bananas, apple and green grapes.
Mix lightly and serve.
Makes a large bowl.

title: chinese chews
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Stir in dates, walnuts and eggs.
Pour into greased and floured 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. Bake in moderate oven (350°) about 15 minutes.
While warm, cut into bars.
Cool, remove from pan and roll in sifted confectioners sugar.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Stir together flour, soda and salt.
In a mixing bowl beat butter and shortening at medium speed for 30 seconds.
Add sugar and beat until well combined.
Stir in chocolate pieces and nuts. Drop a teaspoon at a time 2 inches apart onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Place in buttered casserole dish. Combine milk and soup; pour over broccoli.
Mix butter, water and stuffing mix; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grandma's company pie
directions: Cook ingredients on top of stove in a heavy pan until thickened.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
You may top with whipped cream or meringue.

title: microwave easy chocolate fudge
directions: Microwave Method:
In large measuring cup, combine Toll House chips and sweetened condensed milk.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Stir until morsels melt and mixture is smooth.
Stir in walnuts and vanilla.
Spread evenly into foil-lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm, about 2 hours.
Makes about 1 1/4 pounds fudge.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Unwrap caramels and put in a microwavable bowl with 1/3 cup evaporated milk plus 1 tablespoon whole milk.
Melt butter and add to cake mix with 1/3 cup evaporated milk.

title: hershey bar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the candy bars, into cookie dough and put into a cookie press.
Press a strip of dough on a cookie sheet.
Place candy on the dough and press another layer of dough over the candy.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Remove from the oven and cut the cookies apart.

title: aunt emma's bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cut while warm and roll in sugar.

title: creme brulee
directions: In saucepan over medium heat, heat cream.
Do not boil.
In larger pan, beat egg yolks with wire whisk, adding sugar until well blended; slowly stir in cream.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture just coats the back of the spoon, approximately 15 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole/souffle dish or individual serving dishes and refrigerate until well chilled.
One hour prior to serving, carefully sift brown sugar over chilled mix.
Broil 3 to 4 minutes until sugar melts, making a shiny top.
Chill again until serving.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix together and marinate 24 hours.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place the beans in casserole dish.
Mix in water chestnuts. Add undiluted mushroom soup.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top. Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes or until heated thoroughly. Top with French fried onions and reheat in oven until onions are crisp. Watch onions so they won't burn.

title: peanut squares
directions: Combine syrup and sugar in a large saucepan. Cook until it bubbles around edges. Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter until well blended.
Add Krispies.
Press into a greased pan. Cool and cut in squares.
Serve.

title: bruschetta
directions: Chop and combine all ingredients, including cheese.
Let marinate overnight or for several hours.
Serve on toasted Italian bread slices.

title: mushroom and green bean salad(cold)
directions: Cut beans into 1 1/2-inch lengths.
Cover with water and cook on top of stove or add 3 tablespoons water and cook in microwave oven, just until beans are crisp-tender.
Do not overcook.
Drain beans.
Cover with ice water to stop cooking; set aside.
In small bowl, combine shallots, mayonnaise, lemon juice, oil and mustard; mix well.

title: chunky salsa
directions: Chop all ingredients except for lime and spices. Leave your seeds in the green chiles while chopping up. Mix everything together. Add salt, pepper, onion powder and garlic powder. Mix thoroughly. Squeeze lime juice on top and mix well. Ready to serve.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Dip chicken in milk, then flour.
Saute in oil.
Remove chicken and pour off fat.
In the same pan, saute the mushrooms in butter.
Add wine, mustard, milk and gravy and simmer for 1 minute.
Add chicken and simmer for 5 minutes, uncovered.
Very good.
I serve with rice or noodles.

title: manicotti
directions: Combine
flour,
water
and salt and beat until smooth. Beat in
eggs
one
at a time.
Heat a 5 or 6-inch skillet and grease with
a
few drops of oil.
Pour about 3 tablespoons of batter
in hot
skillet
and
roll
around
pan to distribute evenly.
Cook on low heat until firm.
Do not brown.
Turn and cook
lightly
on other side.
Do not grease skillet a second time.
Makes 12 to 14 manicotti shells.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: In saucepan, melt morsels with milk and margarine.
In large bowl, combine peanuts and marshmallows.
Pour chocolate mixture into nut mixture.
Spread into wax paper-lined 13 x 9-inch pan. Chill 2 hours.

title: three hour hot rolls
directions: Soak one cake of yeast in 1 1/2 cups of warm water.
Combine flour, salt, sugar and shortening and mix like pie dough.
Add yeast with water to dough and knead.
Let rise 1/2 hour.
Work down and let rise 1 hour. Make into rolls and let rise and bake. Before baking, grease tops of rolls with shortening.

title: quick chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soup, vegetables, poultry seasoning and garlic. Put into ungreased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Stir baking mix and milk until blended; pour over chicken mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake at 450° for 32 minutes or until crust is lightly golden brown.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: broccoli, ham pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions. Drain and rinse under cold water. Steam broccoli 3 to 4 minutes until tender; do not overcook. Cool. In a large bowl, gently combine pasta, broccoli, ham, tomato, celery, parsley and onion.

title: spoon bread
directions: Gradually stir cornmeal into 2 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add shortening or butter and salt.
Cool slightly.
Beat egg yolks; add to mixture.
Stir in buttermilk, mixed with baking soda.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Turn into buttered casserole or baking dish.
Bake 40 minutes at 425°.
Serves 8.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Mix pecans and coconut and spread on bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan. Mix cake mix according to directions on box and pour on top of nuts and coconut.
Melt butter and cream cheese (don't get too hot); add powdered sugar and blend with mixer.
Spoon on top of cake mix. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Make a mixture of first 5 ingredients.
In a greased casserole dish, put layer of chicken, a layer of cheese, onions, a layer of Doritos and layer of soup mixture.
Make 3 layers.
Top with cheese.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook 1 hour.

title: bohemian coffee cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and add other ingredients.
Mix well with mixer.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in Bundt pan.
(Check at 45 minutes.)

title: cafe viennese
directions: Mix ahead and store in airtight jar.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, and salt together.
Mix in 1 c. dark corn syrup.
Beat in two eggs- one at a time.
Mix in 1/2 c. Pet evaporated milk, 1 c. broken pecans, and 3/4 tsp. vanilla.
Pour into 9 inch uncooked pie shell.
Bake about 50 minutes or until firm at 375 degrees.

title: marbled brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Soften cream cheese and butter.
Beat together until smooth.
Add sugar, eggs, flour and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Set aside.

title: cajun burgers
directions: Mix together and form into patties.
Wrap each with a strip of bacon and secure with a toothpick.
Grill until done (approximately 20 minutes).
Top with Cheddar or Monterey Jack cheese.

title: fudge cake
directions: Place flour and sugar in a bowl.
Bring cocoa, butter, vanilla and water to a boil in a saucepan, then add it to flour mixture. Add buttermilk, soda and eggs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until done (use sheet pan or 3 layers).
Let cake cool.

title: hungarian holuska
directions: In a large frying pan, saute the onion in oil until golden. Add cabbage, water, onion, salt and pepper. Cover and let simmer until cabbage is tender, 15 minutes.
Add water until tender, if needed. Cook noodles. Drain and add to cabbage.
Mix well and fry 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Chop cabbage coarsely.
Cook in oil and salt over medium heat in covered pan until tender.
(You may want to add about 1/4 cup of water while cooking.)
Brown meat and onion.
Add sauce, water and rice.
Simmer until rice is done (about 20 minutes).
Starting with sauce in bottom of casserole dish, add a layer of cabbage, then sauce and cheese.
Repeat layering.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: confetti bites
directions: Press rolls into a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking sheet to form a crust.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, basil leaves and garlic powder.
Spread thinly over cooled crust.
Top with chopped vegetables.
Sprinkle generously with Salad Supreme seasoning.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix in order given.
Refrigerate and serve chilled.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in pastry-lined pie plate.
Beat eggs slightly; blend in remaining ingredients.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°, then reduce temperature to 300°.
Bake 30 minutes until knife inserted halfway between edge and center and edge comes out clean.
Let pie stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Serve hot.

title: jellied moose nose
directions: Cut upper jawbone just below the eyes.
Place in a large kettle of scalding water and parboil for 45 minutes.
Wash thoroughly and pick off hair, unless you like hair soup.
Place nose in fresh water with onion, a bit of garlic and pickling spice.
Boil gently until tender.
Let cool overnight in the same juice.
Remove bone and cartilage.
The nose is white meat and the jaw meat is dark.
Slice the meat thin and pack in jars and cover with the juice.
This will jell and can be sliced and served cold.

title: velvet creamed spinach soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook onion in butter until it is tender but not brown.
Stir in spinach.
Season the mixture with salt, pepper, sugar and nutmeg.
Stir in chicken broth; cover the pan and cook the mixture over low heat for 15 minutes.
Work the spinach mixture through a sieve or blend it in a blender.
Make a smooth paste of flour and 1/2 cup milk and stir it into the puree.
Add 2 cups milk and cook over low heat, stirring until it is thickened and boils about 3 minutes, then simmer 3 minutes.
Beat egg yolks with light cream.
Gradually pour into hot soup; stir until smooth. Do not boil after cream has been added.
Serve with cheese straws. Serves 6 to 8. This soup may be made with broccoli or asparagus. Freezes well.

title: easy macaroons
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool slightly, then remove to rack.

title: rice meatballs
directions: Combine rice from box, beef, egg, onion, salt, pepper, marjoram, and 1/2 c. tomato juice.
Mix lightly and shape into 18 balls, place in skillet and cook.
Add sugar to the remaining tomato juice and pour over meatballs.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer covered for 15 minutes while basting.
Serves 6.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter and saute onion till light brown.
Sprinkle with flour.
Cook for 1-2 minutes, stirring.
Add broth, bay leaf and peppercorns.
Boil and simmer 30 minutes covered.
Put into individual oven proof bowls.
Slice bread and toast on both sides. Place in bowls of soup and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in oven till cheese browns.

title: lemon jelly roll
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Break eggs in large mixing bowl.
Beat at high speed until lemon colored. Gradually add sugar, a tablespoon at a time, beating constantly. Add vanilla; reduce speed to slow.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture, beating only until blended.
Add hot water all at once and beat to a smooth batter.
Spread evenly in wax paper-lined 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes. Loosen cake carefully from sides of pan with spatula.
Sift powdered sugar over cake and cover with towel.
Turn out immediately.
Remove wax paper and beginning at narrow end, roll cake and towel together.
Cool.
Unroll and remove towel.
Fill as desired.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add beaten egg yolks, milk, flour, spices and then beaten egg whites. Flour berries well and stir into batter.
Last, add soda dissolved. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.
Recipe may be halved.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add nuts and fruits to flour and set aside.
Add vanilla and lemon to butter, sugar and egg mixture.
Fold in flour, nuts and fruits.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: coconut fruit bowl
directions: Combine fruits, marshmallows and coconut.
Stir in sour cream and salt.
Chill overnight.
Serves 8.

title: marinated slaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine cabbage, pimentos, green pepper and onion.
Toss lightly.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer uncovered for 20-25 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Cover and refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Slaw will keep in refrigerator for several days.
Yield: 8 - 10 servings.

title: wiener casserole
directions: In a casserole dish layer ingredients as follows: 1 cup wieners, 1	cup
green
beans,
can mushrooms and 1/4 cup grated
cheese.
Sprinkle with Accent.
Repeat the layers with remaining
ingredients, using most of cheese as topping.
Bake in 325°
oven	for
to
minutes.
Serve hot with baked potato or white rice.

title: bacon and cheddar muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line 12 muffin cups with paper baking cups.
Mix all ingredients except for cheese and bacon until moistened.
Fold in cheese and bacon.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake until golden brown, about 20 minutes.

title: toll house beans(for microwave)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a microwaveable dish.
Cook, covered, on High for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: white trash
directions: Melt chocolate over double boiler.
Add oil, blend.
Toss over mixture of cereals, peanuts, pretzels.
Layer on two large cookie sheets lined with wax paper.
Crumble after set.
Can be frozen.

title: holiday salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and bring to a boil for 2 minutes.
Mix in jello.
Let chill (thick but not jelled).
Add olives, pecan chips and cheese.
Beat whipping cream until it peaks and add.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: three cheese quiche
directions: Break eggs into 4 cup measuring cup and beat.
Add seasonings (nutmeg is very important).
Add cream to make custard.
Layer cheeses (and any precooked meat or vegetables you desire) in pie crust.
Pour custard over filling.
Dot with butter and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: italian bread with a touch
directions: Slice bread in half.
Spread butter.
Sprinkle basil and garlic.
Boil broccoli and cauliflower approximately 10 minutes. Strain and mix together.
Lay vegetables and cheese on top.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Other vegetables may be used.

title: hill country salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain, reserving 1/4 cup drippings. Crumble bacon and set aside.
Place lettuce in a large bowl; sprinkle with onion, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Drizzle reserved bacon drippings over greens, tossing gently.
Sprinkle with bacon and serve immediately.

title: banana pudding
directions: Dissolve pudding in 3 cups of cold, sweet milk, beating with electric mixer on low speed or until pudding gets thick.
Add Cool Whip and sour cream; mix well.
Sprinkle crushed wafers in bottom of a container that holds 3 quarts or more.
Layer with 3 sliced bananas and pudding.
Repeat same procedure using the next 3 bananas.
Sprinkle wafers on top.
Cover well and refrigerate until next day.

title: texas hash
directions: In
a
large
skillet,	cook
and stir meat, onions and celery until
meat is brown and vegetables are tender.
Drain off
fat. Stir
in
tomatoes,
rice, chili powder and pepper. Heat
through. Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Cover; bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: split pea soup
directions: Coarsely chop the vegetables and add to the boiling water, along with the ham bone and split peas. Cover and cook slowly for about 2 hours.
Remove ham bone.
Put soup through food mill and return to the pot.
Remove ham from bone in small pieces and add to the soup.
Season with salt and pepper as desired.
Serve.

title: 7-up valentine's punch
directions: For a decorative touch, freeze additional 7-Up in a heart-shaped mold, filling the mold 2/3 full.
(This allows for expansion of ice.)
A few drops of red food coloring may be added, if desired.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Press out crescent rolls in a pizza pan or cookie sheet until bottom is entirely covered.
Spread sausage over the uncooked crust and then the shredded cheese. Stir the eggs and milk together, then pour over the crust mixture. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: almost heaven
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Poke holes in cake with fork.
Pour pineapple all over cake.
Let cool completely.
Mix pudding according to directions.
Pour pudding over cake.
Add Cool Whip and nuts.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla. Add flour, oats, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add chocolate chips and the Hershey bar, grated.
Bake golf ball size dough balls for 6 minutes at 375° on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: world's best cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Add salad oil and continue to beat.
Add oatmeal, cornflakes and coconut, mixing well.
Add flour, salt, baking soda and vanilla and stir in the pecans.
Form mixture into balls the size of small walnuts and place on greased cookie sheet (12 to 15 on each cookie sheet).
Flatten with fork dipped in water.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes until lightly browned.
Allow to cool for a few minutes before removing from cookie sheet.
May sprinkle with sugar while warm, if desired.

title: torta cebuana
directions: Beat egg yolks, oil, sugar and vanilla together. Add flour, a small portion at a time, with milk.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: tuna and egg noodle dish
directions: Put water in pan and bring to a boil for noodles.
Add bell pepper (cut into small pieces) and cook for 5 to 10 minutes, then add noodles and cook until done.
Drain.
Add salt to taste.
Put in mushroom soup.
Stir and add tuna.
While still hot, stir in cheese pieces.
This is really good on cold days.

title: slim pickin chicken
directions: Remove all fat and skin from chicken parts.

Sprinkle with garlic powder, salt and pepper. Rest at least an hour in refrigerator. In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, pour orange soda. Lay chicken pieces side by side in this. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes on one side, turn the pieces and brown on the other.

title: real easy chicken
directions: You will need 1 large size oven cooking bag.

title: nancy's chili
directions: Mix together and simmer at least 1 to 2 hours.

title: rosanne's favorite cut-out cookies
directions: In large bowl, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in milk, egg and extracts.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt until well blended.
(If using one one food coloring, add several drops when beating in liquids.
Otherwise, divide dough and knead coloring into dough portions if using more than one color.)
Then wrap dough or portions of dough in plastic wrap and refrigerate approximately 1 hour.
Next, roll dough on a floured surface to about 1/4-inch and use cookie cutters for desired shapes.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° on ungreased cookie sheets for 10 minutes or until very lightly browned.
Cool on wire racks.

title: creamy pralines
directions: Cook together, brown sugar, sugar, milk, and cream of tartar stirring constantly until firm soft boil stage. Add margarine, vanilla, and pecans; beat. Drop by spoonfuls onto lightly greased wax paper or foil that has been buttered.

title: poor man's foie de gras
directions: Cook livers, celery, onion and parsley in water until soft (approximately 10 minutes).
Drain.
Use fork or food processor and mash livers, celery, onion and yolks of eggs together until smooth.
Blend in Thousand Island dressing, mayonnaise and salt and pepper to taste.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or before serving. Spread on crackers.
Stuff mixture into egg whites or celery stalks.
Sprinkle with paprika to decorate.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Stir butter, eggs and Parmesan cheese into spaghetti. Pour into a 9 x 13 baking dish. Brown beef with onion and green pepper, pouring off any fat. Stir in tomato sauce, sugar and spices. Heat thoroughly. Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti mixture and spread meat mixture over cottage cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Spread Mozzarella cheese over baked dish and return to oven for 5 to 10 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: ole' south crab cakes
directions: Remove crusts from bread slices.
Break into small pieces and moisten with milk.
Stir in all ingredients except cracker meal. Shape into cakes and roll in cracker meal.
Fry until golden brown. Serves 4.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Stir in syrup.
Add eggs, one at a time, stirring after each one until well blended.
Stir in oatmeal.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; melt butter.
Add to eggs.
Bake pie crust a little.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the margarine, sugar, eggs and sour cream. Stir in the baking powder and flour.
Add vanilla and lemon extract.
Chill dough several hours.
Roll out.
Sprinkle with a little sugar and roll again lightly.
Cut into small rounds.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: elsie's peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt margarine in pan, add milk, syrup and sugar.
Cook on medium heat stirring constantly until soft balls form in cold water (about 5 minutes after it starts to boil).
Remove from heat, stir in 7 oz. marshmallow creme, peanut butter and vanilla. Mix quickly and thoroughly.
Pour in a 9 x 12 inch buttered pan. Let cool.
For chocolate fudge add 1 cup cocoa.

title: touchdown chocolate fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt chips with milk, vanilla and salt. Remove from heat; stir in nuts.
Cool. On aluminum foil, shape into smooth balls, then in football shape.
Chill 2 hours. Garnish with powdered sugar.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan over medium heat.
Add the chopped tortillas, garlic and cilantro; saute until tortillas are soft. Add onion and tomatoes and bring to boil.
Add cumin, chili powder, tomato puree and stock.
Bring soup to boil again, then reduce heat to simmer.
Add red pepper and cook, stirring frequently, for 30 minutes.
Place tortilla strips in oven at 300° for 5 minutes.

title: german apple cake
directions: Blend all and beat as package directs.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes (until top springs back).
Cool.
Top with whipped cream sprinkled with cinnamon.
This is a quickie and is very moist.

title: punch(serves 75, approximately 3 gallons)
directions: Mix
juices
by directions on cans.
Chill well.
Add 2 quarts ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: oven-braised doves
directions: Season doves with salt and pepper.
Melt butter in heavy skillet and brown doves.
Remove to baking dish.
Add flour to butter in skillet, stirring well.
Slowly add chicken broth and sherry.
Season to taste.
Blend well and pour over doves.
Add mushrooms and parsley.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in covered baking dish.
Serve over wild rice.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time to dry ingredients.
Stir in creamed butter and sugar.
Add fruits.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 13 minutes.

title: blueberry orange bread
directions: Melt butter in boiling water in small bowl.
Add 1/2 cup orange juice and 3 teaspoons orange rind.
Beat egg with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with orange liquid, beating until smooth.
Fold in blueberries. Place in greased 1 1/2-quart 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Turn onto rack.

title: no-weep meringue
directions: Mix cornstarch with cold water in small saucepan.
Add boiling water; cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks.
Add cornstarch mixture, beating until stiff.
Add sugar slowly, one tablespoon at a time, beating well after each addition.
Continue beating until stiff. Beat in vanilla.
Spread meringue on pie.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Turn off oven heat.
Open door.
Let pie cool in the oven.
(The latter is the most important step to avoid weeping.)

title: chicken and asparagus casserole
directions: Cook chicken with onions and pepper.
Place frozen asparagus in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place pieces of boned chicken over asparagus.
Dilute soup with low sodium chicken broth.
Add mushrooms and pour mixture over chicken and
asparagus.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour after it starts to boil.
Yields 12 servings.

title: man's cake
directions: Mix.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
(If desired, one tablespoon butter flavoring may be added for taste.)

title: molded gazpacho salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Break up tomatoes with their juice, with back of spoon.
Add to gelatin along with hot pepper sauce, vinegar and chopped vegetables.
Using oiled 2-quart ring mold, chill until firm.
Turn out onto a platter.
Surround with sliced cucumber.
Serve with Horseradish Cream.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Drain all the fruit.
Mix the pudding into the fruit. Reserve the juice.
Freeze.
Put in jello instead of water.

title: weight watchers soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large stew pot and cook until tender.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Dredge potatoes in mixture. Layer potatoes in a Pam-sprayed 2-quart casserole dish.
Drizzle margarine (melted) over potatoes.
Bake in a 400° oven for 1 hour, uncovered.
Sprinkle more garlic salt over potatoes after you put them in pan (if desired).
(Can be cut larger than French fries.)

title: graham cracker squares
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; pack firmly
in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Add the Eagle Brand milk, coconut and vanilla.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° (not more). Cool; frost with a chocolate frosting.

title: italian ham pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and fill pie crusts (top and bottom crust). Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Makes 6 to 8 pies.

title: chicken pan pie
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Add broth to the soups and place over chicken in baking dish.
Mix Bisquick and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Roll stew meat in flour; brown in hot oil on all sides.
Place in crock-pot with 4 cups water or enough water to barely cover. Place the bay leaves in the pot.
Cut up the vegetables.
After beef has cooked 1 hour, place vegetables in crock-pot, along with the soup.
Cook on high for 3 more hours, or until beef and vegetables are tender.

title: hamburger rice pot
directions: Put all ingredients into 3-quart pot.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 14 minutes.
Turn off heat and let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 4 to 6 minutes.

title: linguine with clam sauce-red(linguine con le vongole)
directions: In medium saucepan
heat
oil
and
saute
garlic until golden.
Remove from
pan and discard.
Set oil aside.
Strain clam juice through
several
layers
of
cheese
cloth and set aside in separate bowl.
Wash
and
chop clams; place in separate bowl.
Add clam juice
and water to oil;
heat to a boil. Add rest of ingredients, except clams and cook on a medium low heat for 25 minutes.
Add clams and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Turn off heat and keep
pan
covered,
until
linguine
is cooked, according to package directions.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Combine flour, oats, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup butter. Mix until crumbly; use mixer on low speed.
Press into ungreased pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Combine pumpkin, milk, eggs, sugar, salt and spices in bowl.
Beat well; pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Combine pecans, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 2 tablespoons butter.
Mix; sprinkle over pumpkin filling.
Return to oven and bake 15 or 20 more minutes or until filling is set.
Cool in pan.
Cut in squares.
If desired, top with whipped topping.

title: chess cake
directions: Preheat at 350°.
Mix and bake for 35 minutes in oblong pan.

title: italian sausage roll
directions: Thaw bread dough.
When risen, punch down and roll out flat. Thaw spinach and cook partially.
Fry sausage and drain well.
On rolled out dough, spread sausage, spinach, onions and mushrooms. Sprinkle with cheeses.
Roll up.
Let rise about 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until crust is browned.
Remove from oven and brush top with beaten egg white.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Put back in oven for 5 minutes.

title: june's sweet and sour baked beans
directions: Drain beans (except baked).
Saute onions in bacon drippings. Add brown sugar, mustard, garlic powder, salt and vinegar. Combine beans, crumbled bacon and sauce.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheesy corn casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Reserve a few crumbs and cheese for topping.
Bake in a greased 8-inch pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: honey loep cookies
directions: Heat honey, sugar and butter until sugar melts.
Cool.
Add dry ingredients, pecans and mixed fruit.
Form rolls and chill. When ready to bake, slice 1/4-inch and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: artichoke-chili dip
directions: Combine the chopped artichoke hearts, chopped chili peppers, cheese and mayonnaise or salad dressing. Turn mixture into an 8-inch round baking dish. Bake in a 350° oven about 20 minutes or until heated through. Serve warm with tortilla chips and breadsticks. Makes about 2 2/3 cups.

title: chicken mozzarella
directions: Dip chicken breasts in beaten egg and coat with bread crumbs. Fry chicken in oil to brown.
Place chicken in baking pan.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour, salt and egg yolks with cold milk. Add scalded milk while stirring constantly. Cook slowly until thick. Remove from stove and add vanilla and 1/2 cup coconut. Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue; sprinkle with 1/2 cup coconut on top. Bake 15 minutes at 350° until browned.

title: lemonade pie(summertime pie)
directions: *Buy the crust already made.

title: one pound pork chops
directions: Brown chops in skillet with oil and remove.
Drain reserving 2 teaspoons.
Saute eggplant, onion, celery and garlic.
Stir in ketchup, water, olives, capers, vinegar, salt, oregano, basil and pepper.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Return chops to skillet and cook until chops are done, turning once.
Serve with rice pilaf and garlic bread.

title: peach torte
directions: Options:
Any flavor ice cream or whipped topping.

title: quick energy pick-ups
directions: Crush graham crackers with your fingers onto sheet of waxed paper.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly in bowl.
Shape teaspoonfuls of the mixture into 1-inch balls.
Roll the balls in the graham cracker crumbs until coated.
Arrange the coated balls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Refrigerate about 20 minutes or until firm.

title: lemon supreme pound cake
directions: Blend all ingredients and beat for 2 minutes. Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until center springs back when touched lightly.
Cool and ice with following frosting or make a glaze with:

title: chicken continental
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir until smooth.
Slowly add evaporated milk; continue stirring.
Cook until thick; remove from heat.
Beat egg yolks and slowly stir in a little of the hot sauce.
Stir in remaining hot sauce, butter and lemon juice.
Pour vegetables into buttered baking dish.
Top with slices of chicken.
Sprinkle with almonds; cover with sauce and top with grated cheese.
Place under broiler until sauce is bubbly and lightly browned on top.

title: crab meat pizza
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add other ingredients and stir until smooth.
Spread on serving dish.
Pour on 1/2 bottle chili sauce. Spread 1 small can crab meat on top of sauce.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix butter and oatmeal until melted on stove. Set aside to cool. Add milk, eggs and raisins. Combine dry ingredients. Add to oatmeal, butter, egg and milk; mix. Fold in nuts. Drop by spoonfuls onto a lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes until lightly browned.

title: spicy bean salsa
directions: In a medium bowl, combine black-eyed peas, black beans, corn, onion, green bell pepper, jalapeo pepper and tomatoes.
Season with Italian dressing and garlic salt; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight to blend flavors.

title: olive cheese bites
directions: Grate cheese; add softened oleo and beat until creamy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mold 1 teaspoon of dough around whole olive.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes in 400° oven.
Freezes great.

title: white chocolate mousse with kiwi and strawberry slices
directions: Combine sugar and water in small, heavy saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring just until dissolved.
Boil gently until it reaches 225° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Set aside while beating egg whites.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
With mixer at low speed, add sugar syrup in slow, steady stream.
Beat 30 seconds, or until fluffy.
Melt chocolate at 50% power in microwave.
Add to mixture and continue beating.
Set aside.
Whip the cream until stiff.
Fold into chocolate mixture.
Pour into serving dishes.
Chill.
Before serving, decorate top with sliced kiwi and strawberries.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Boil cabbage for 5 minutes. Drain.
Mix ground beef, sausage, onion and rice.
Make into balls and wrap with cabbage leaves. Hold together with toothpicks.
Make a broth of tomato juice, sugar and vinegar.
Put pork chops in broth, bring to boil.
Drop cabbage rolls into broth.
Simmer for 3 to 4 hours.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Mix ingredients in a pan.
Cook over medium heat and stir constantly until gelatine is dissolved and mixture is heated thoroughly.
Remove from heat.

title: orange juice cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients. Roll into small balls, then roll in coconut. Keep in fridge.

title: norma koerner's vanilla halloween taffy
directions: Mix and boil until hard-crack stage is reached.
Pour onto buttered dishes and begin to work from edges.
Careful, it's hot! When temperature has reached a tolerable point, start pulling. Keep hands well buttered to avoid sticking.
Taffy will appear snow white when done.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Cool until starts to thicken.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch dish. Refrigerate until completely set.
Serve plain or top with cottage cheese or sour cream.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender with 2 teaspoons salt in water; drain juice.
Chop pepper and add onions.
Reserve carrots.
Put sugar and other ingredients together; heat just enough to melt the sugar.
Pour heated ingredients over carrots while carrots are still warm.
Marinate for 24 to 48 hours in refrigerator.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: chicken yum yum
directions: Salt chicken.
Wrap each piece with a slice of dried beef and then a slice of bacon; secure with a toothpick.
Mix chicken soup with sour cream.
Place chicken breasts in casserole and cover with soup mixture.
Cover with foil and bake at 250° for about 3 hours.
Drain off gravy and pour over cooked rice.

title: lemon baked beefsteak
directions: Wipe steak with damp cloth or paper towel.
Place in large baking dish or Dutch oven.
Rub both sides with softened butter or margarine.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover with lemon and onion slices.

title: layered salad
directions: Place chopped lettuce in square bowl.
Layer peppers smooth, then onion, carrots, celery and English peas.
Mix mayonnaise with cream cheese; spread over peas.
Sprinkle bacon bits on top and chill.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except gingerale and apple, and freeze in milk cartons.
About 2 hours before serving, remove from freezer. Break up with fork.
Add gingerale and apple juice and mix together.

title: microwave creamy pralines
directions: In large bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
Cook 5 minutes in microwave on High.
Stir well.
Cook 8 minutes on High until soft boil stage, stirring occasionally.
Remove and add vanilla.
Beat about 4 minutes until color is dull.
Stir in pecans and drop on wax paper.

title: strawberry pound cake
directions: Beat the egg whites and add 6 tablespoons of the sugar; let set in refrigerator while mixing cake.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oleo, brown sugar and evaporated milk.
Let come to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and let cool. Add vanilla.

title: creamy pimento cheese spread
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl.
Add first 5 ingredients.
Process until smooth.
Add pimento; pulse 4 or 5 times.
Yields 3 1/3 cups.

title: grape pulp dessert
directions: Stir jello and water until jello is dissolved.
Add grape pulp and lemon juice.
Let cool until slightly thickened.
Add Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until set.
Garnish with mint leaves.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini (grated) and mix well.
In separate bowl, combine dry ingredients. Mix well.
Combine the two mixtures and add nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: skillet pasta
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add soup mix, tomatoes and water; bring to a boil.
Stir in macaroni; simmer for 20 minutes.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Serves 4.

title: corn-on-the-cob microwave recipe
directions: Will also need paper towels.

title: 25 hour layer salad
directions: Line a 13 x 9 x 2 glass dish with bite size pieces of lettuce. Sprinkle peppers, celery, onions and peas (frozen, not thawed). Add sugar to mayonnaise and spread over top.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pistachio pie
directions: Pour the cold milk and pudding mix in a bowl, then stir for two minutes with a wire whisk.
Pour into pie crust and leave in fridge for two hours.

title: bean delight
directions: Cut bacon into 1-inch pieces.
Fry and drain well.
To bacon drippings, add onion, vinegar, mustard and brown sugar.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour well drained beans and mushrooms in large casserole dish.
Add bacon and drippings mixture.
Stir well.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in pie pan.
Bake at 300° until brown. Cool.

title: strawberry-cheese salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Soften gelatin in the pineapple syrup.
Stir over low heat until gelatin is dissolved. Stir into strawberry-flavored yogurt with dash of salt.
Add thawed strawberries, including syrup and drained pineapple; mix well.
Pour into 1-quart mold.
Chill until set.
Unmold onto lettuce.
Garnish with more strawberries.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: enchilada style casserole
directions: Cook meat and onions until done; drain fat.
Add soup, sauce, milk and chilies; mix well.
Add diced cheese to mixture.
In large casserole (greased), put 1 layer of tortillas, quartered; add mixture alternately.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Do not salt.

title: apple cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease a 10-inch tube pan.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, soda, salt, cinnamon, allspice and nutmeg.
Stir in buttermilk, butter and egg just until combined. Fold in apples and almonds.

title: winter carrot casserole(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Cook carrots, covered in boiling water, 10 minutes or until barely tender.
Drain.
Place in 1-quart casserole.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Add the water and vanilla and beat until fluffy.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheddar potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into small chunks.
In a small bowl, combine soup, paprika and pepper.
Grease a 2-quart baking dish; line bottom of dish with potatoes.
Pour cheese over the potatoes, then pour the soup over the cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: little cheese cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix until creamy.
Put 1 vanilla wafer in bottom of foil muffin cup.
Fill 2/3 full of cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until firm.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Add broccoli, onion and carrots to broth.
Cook for 20 minutes. In a separate pan, melt butter; add flour.
Cook over low heat for 2 minutes.
Stir in milk.
Cook until it thickens.
Add the Velveeta cheese and continue to cook until cheese is melted.
Add to the broth and veggies.
Cook over low heat.

title: pie crust (3)
directions: Mix flour, shortening and salt.
Put egg in a cup; beat in vinegar and cold water.
Add to flour mixture.
After all is moistened, fold over three times, then divide and roll.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into a greased casserole dish or a greased 8 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick icing
directions: Beat 1 cup powdered sugar into foamy egg white.
Mix together Crisco, butter, flour and milk.
Beat into egg mixture.
Add 1 cup powdered sugar and vanilla and beat real good.

title: frozen snickers bar
directions: Let ice cream and Cool Whip soften.
Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Freeze in 8-inch square pan.

title: sauteed scallops montelimar(serves 8)
directions: Dry the scallops thoroughly with paper towels.
Season with salt and pepper.
Dredge lightly with flour, shaking off the excess.
Heat the butter and oil in a large heavy skillet.
Add the scallops; do not crowd the pan.
Saute over high heat until the scallops are golden brown on all sides.
Remove the skillet from the heat.
With a spatula, remove the scallops to a side dish and reserve.
Add the shallots, garlic and parsley to the pan. You may need an additional tablespoon butter.
Return the pan to the heat and cook the mixture for 2 minutes, scraping well the bottom of the pan.
Add the stock; bring to a boil and reduce to 2 tablespoons.
Add the cream; bring to a boil and reduce by one-third.
Combine the 4 tablespoons butter and flour together into a paste.
Whisk in bits of this mixture until the sauce heavily coats a spoon.
Mix up more if necessary.
Return the scallops to the pan and cook for 2 to 3 minutes, or until heated through.
Taste and correct the seasoning.
Transfer the scallops to a serving dish.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve hot.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Melt butter.
Blend in sugar and egg.
Add flour, nuts and vanilla.
Spread in well-greased and floured pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: stir and roll pie pastry
directions: Mix sifted, measured flour and salt.
Pour oil and milk into one
measuring
cup.
Do
not
stir.
Add oil and milk at once to flour.
Stir
until mixed.	Press into a smooth ball. Cut in two and flatten
each
half
slightly.	Place
one half between 2 sheets of waxed paper.
Roll
out gently to edges of paper.
Peel off top paper.
Ease
and
fit
pastry
into pan. Trim and add filling.
Roll top	crust
the same way and place over filling. Fold edges under bottom crust.
Seal with fork, pressing gently. Make slits	in center.
Bake as directed for pie.

title: funny pie
directions: Beat softened cream cheese.
Add in sugar and vanilla.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Spoon into graham cracker crust; top with cherries.

title: german apple cake
directions: Combine flour, powder and salt; set aside.
Beat eggs and 2 cups sugar.
Combine oil and orange juice and add alternately with dry ingredients to egg/sugar mixture.
Add vanilla and mix until smooth.
Pour 1/2 batter in greased tube pan.
Arrange 1/2 the apples on top.
Mix cinnamon and sugar and sprinkle 1/2 of it on apples.
Add remaining batter, then apples, then last of cinnamon/sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool. Can sprinkle confectioners sugar on top when completely cool.

title: chicken waldorf salad
directions: Mix all ingredients until blended and then serve.

title: scented ornament dough
directions: In large saucepan, mix cornstarch and baking soda.
Gradually add water.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally.
The mixture will start to thicken and get bubbly.
Stir it constantly until the mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat by placing on foil or plastic wrap.
When cool enough to handle, knead in cinnamon.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness and cut with cookie cutters.
Make hole for hanging with toothpick.
Air dry.

title: yummy punch
directions: Mix all juices together.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix powdered sugar and cream cheese together with electric mixer until creamy.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix until smooth.
Break angel food cake into bite-size pieces.
Mix into Cool Whip mixture.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix strawberries and glaze together.
Spread over cake.
Chill.

title: deer burger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown burger meat and drain.
Add first 4 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Place in Dutch oven or ovenproof serving dish.
Place small biscuits or 1/2 biscuits on top and around edge.
Cook until brown.
Turn heat off.
Sprinkle cheese over biscuits and remove from oven as soon as cheese melts.

title: polish sausage supper
directions: In a large skillet, combine first 5 ingredients on medium heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in peas and mushrooms.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until rice is cooked.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 15-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook onions and butter; add rest of ingredients and bake in casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple nutter treats
directions: Mix peanut butter and cornflakes.
Slice apples.
Spread peanut butter mixture on each of the apple slices.
Clean up. Enjoy Apple Nutters with three good friends.

title: tortilla beef bake
directions: Brown meat and onion together; drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes, enchilada sauce, cumin, 1/4 tsp. salt and pepper. Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Pour half of the meat sauce into 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Wrap the stack of tortillas in foil; warm in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Spread warm tortillas with cream cheese; top with chilies.
Fold tortillas in half.
Arrange folded tortillas over meat sauce in dish.
Pour remaining sauce down the center.
Cover and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Uncover.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Return to oven and bake 5 minutes more or until cheese melts.

title: custard cream
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine half and half or light cream, sugar, cornstarch, salt and egg yolk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture coats a spoon well, about 15 minutes (mixture should be about 170° to 175°, but do not boil or it will curdle).
Remove custard from heat.
Stir in vanilla. Pour into bowl.
To keep skin from forming as custard cools, press plastic wrap directly onto surface of Custard Cream.

title: ground beef oriental
directions: In skillet heat butter and brown celery and onions.
Add beef and rice and brown.
In buttered casserole, combine soup, water, soy sauce and pepper.
Add onions, beef and rice.
Lightly stir in mushrooms and bean sprouts.
Bake covered in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 30 more minutes.

title: impossible lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown meat in skillet, sprayed with cooking spray.
Spray an 8 x 8-inch baking dish with olive flavored cooking spray.
Layer cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese on bottom.
Mix browned meat, spices, tomato sauce and half the Mozzarella cheese.
Spoon over cheese layer.

title: cream of carrot soup
directions: Simmer carrots in chicken broth until tender, about 15 minutes.
In another pan, saute onion in butter until limp, but not browned.
Puree all in blender or food processor.
Add salt, pepper, cream and thyme.
Bring back to simmer, stirring constantly. Serve hot or chilled with a sprinkling of chopped parsley for garnish.
Makes 6 servings.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars.
Add applesauce, egg whites, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats, chocolate chips and nuts; mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes for a chewy cookie or 12 to 13 minutes for a crisp one.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: hot 'n spicy fried chicken
directions: Stir together hot sauce and garlic salt until blended.	Pour chicken in large bowl set aside.
Stir together bisquick mix, onion salt and pepper in medium bowl.
Remove chicken from sauce; drain. Coat chicken with bisquick mixture.
Heat oil in 12 inch skillet medium heat until hot.
Cook chicken in oil until golden brown on both sides.

title: plain cookies
directions: Blend dry ingredients (except sugar).
Cream butter and sugar until well blended.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat to blend.
Add dry ingredients (blend).
Place cookies on well-greased baking sheet with No. 40 scoop (1 3/4 tablespoons).
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes 100 cookies.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased casserole dish. Top with paprika and more grated cheese if desired. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: amish friendship bread
directions: Mix wet ingredients together well.
Mix dry ingredients together well.
Add dry ingredients to the wet.
Add one cup of apples, or raisins, or nuts or dates.
Or instead of putting nuts in the batter, put them in the bottom of baking pan(s).
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon, then add the batter.
Bake in a greased, well-floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or bake in 2 loaf pans at 325° for 1 hour.

title: grandma babe's tomato catsup
directions: Peel tomatoes and onions.
Remove seeds from peppers and slice. Cook vegetables 30 minutes.
Run through colander.
Boil pulp until thick.
Put allspice and other spices in rag and add all together with remaining ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Pour up into jars and seal.

title: easy pork chop dinner
directions: Brown pork chops and remove from skillet.
Slice onion, green pepper and cabbage in layers in skillet.
Arrange pork chops on top.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer for 3 hours.

title: spaghetti squash carbonara
directions: Scoop seed from squash.
Place halves, cut-side-down in 1/2 inch water in a 9 x 13 baking dish.
bake in preheated 350° oven 35 to 40 minutes, until squash is tender.
Meanwhile, in a medium skillet heat oil and butter over medium heat.
Saute ham, onion and garlic until onion is soft.
Add snow peas and red pepper. Saute 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat. In a large bowl beat eggs with cheese until blended.
Turn cooked squash halves cut-side-up. With fork pull out strands of squash. Work carefully so as not to tear the squash shell.
Add hot squash to egg mixture. Toss well.
Add warm ham-vegetable mixture.
Toss well. Spoon squash into shell. Serve with freshly ground black pepper, if desired.
Makes 2 servings.

title: millinocket fudge cake
directions: *Or 6 tablespoons cocoa and 2 tablespoons butter.

title: christmas lizzies
directions: Soak raisins in 1 cup whiskey overnight.
Drain and discard whiskey.
Stir the candied fruit, nuts and flour together. Combine all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 minutes.

title: harvard beets(mildred jernigan)
directions: Make sauce of sugar, water, vinegar and flour. Add onion and cook slowly for 5 minutes. Add beets and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: quick and easy salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Don't add water for the Jell-O. Store salad in refrigerator for at least 4 hours before serving.

title: yummy buffet potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and nuts.
Soften with mayonnaise or milk if needed.
Drain strawberries well.
Reserve juice.
Drop cream cheese mixture as ball size pieces into Pyrex dish.
Arrange strawberries around balls.
Dissolve jello in one cup of boiling water.
Use reserved juice and enough water to make 3/4 cup.
Pour in jello.
Pour jello mixture over cheese and strawberries.
Set overnight.

title: sweet and sour macaroni salad
directions: Scrape and dice carrots.
Dice celery.
Chop onion. Peel cucumber and chop.
Peel tomato and chop.
Cook macaroni and cool in water.
Combine all vegetables.
Combine oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Refrigerate for 8 hours.

title: biscuits
directions: Cut margarine into flour and baking soda.
Make a well in the mixture and pour in buttermilk.
Add enough flour to get dough out of the bowl and onto waxed paper.
Roll out 1/2 inch deep and cut biscuits (if you don't have a round cookie cutter use a mason jar lid).
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until barely golden brown.

title: eldon's mom's chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add alternately with the water.
Makes 2 layers or a 9 x 13-inch loaf cake.
Bake at 350° until cake tests done, 25 to 35 minutes.
Mom always frosted it with chocolate icing and it seemed there was always chocolate cake in the cake saver.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup and Ro-Tel together. Put cut up chicken in 3-quart casserole dish.
Add onion to top, then soup mixture.
Crush Doritos and add cheese to top.
Bake at 350° until hot and cheese is melted.

title: spicy corn
directions: In skillet over low heat, melt cream cheese and butter with milk until soft and creamy.
Remove from heat.
Add drained corn and jalapenos.
Mix thoroughly and put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: osgood pie
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and salt.
Add slightly beaten eggs, vanilla and vinegar.
Add raisins which have been soaked a few minutes in warm water.
Be sure to drain well.
Bake in 9-inch uncooked pie shell for 1 hour at 350°.

title: creamy mounds with sauce
directions: In mixing bowl, beat softened cream cheese with 3/4 cup powdered sugar until light and fluffy.
Add 1/4 cup powdered sugar into whipped cream.
Add vanilla extract and raspberry liqueur. Combine mixtures.
Using a rounded tablespoonful, place a mound in each 3-inch cup of a 12-cup muffin tin.
Freeze and when frozen, place muffin tin in plastic bag.
These will keep for several weeks.
Remove from freezer about 15 minutes before serving time. Unmold.
Serve with one of the warm sauces or chocolate sauce.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs to blend.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Continue beating with spoon.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Combine flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, walnuts and raisins.
Stir in gently into zucchini mixture just until blended. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Use 2 loaf pans, greased and floured.

title: russian rock cookies(ibm owego cafeteria)
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening, salt, cinnamon and baking soda. When well creamed, add eggs, molasses, chopped nuts and raisins. Scrape down bowl and add flour.
(This mixture should be moist enough to stay together, but dry enough to work by hand.)
Form dough into balls approximately 3/4 ounce each and flatten on cookie sheet.
Brush top of cookie with egg mixture (1 whole egg whipped, plus pinch of salt; if too thick, add a dash of water). Bake in a 380° oven for 13 to 14 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix the yeast, 2 cups of warm water and 3/4 cup sugar.
Let sit 5 to 10 minutes until bubbles appear.
Add eggs and margarine. Add enough flour to make a medium dough.
Cover with Saran Wrap. Let rise until doubles in bulk, then divide into 2 balls.
Roll each one out into a rectangle about 1/4 x 3-inches thick.
Spread with melted margarine.
Sprinkle on sugar-cinnamon and raisins. Roll up like jelly roll.
Cut into 2-inch pieces.
Place, cut side down, on buttered cookie sheet close together.
Brush on melted butter and let rise until doubles.
Bake at 400°. Remove from oven.
Glaze while warm with powdered sugar, vanilla and water.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring sugar, cornstarch, water and corn syrup to a boil. Cook 6 minutes until thick. Remove from heat. Add 3 tablespoons strawberry gelatin. Cool completely. Arrange strawberries in pie shell and pour glaze over. Serve with whipped cream.

title: sweet surprise chicken
directions: Mix cranberry sauce, soup mix and French dressing and pour over chicken breasts.
Bake, uncovered, at 250° for 1 1/2 hours. Serves 8.

title: rhubarb and raspberry preserves
directions: Put rhubarb and sugar in a sealable plastic bag and shake well until rhubarb is well coated with sugar.
Put in the refrigerator overnight.
In a large saucepan, bring the rhubarb/sugar mixture to a boil.
Reduce the heat to a low boil, and cook 20 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in the raspberry jell-o.
Pour into small, sterilized jars and seal.
Process in a water bath 10-15 minutes.
Fills 1 dozen mini jars or 6 1/2 pt. jars.

title: pizza roll
directions: Defrost pizza dough in refrigerator overnight.
Spread flat as if for a jelly roll.
Saute ground beef and/or sausage until brown.
Set aside to cool.
Mix grated cheese with eggs, egg yolk, Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Mix all together with meat.
Spread on pizza dough and roll up as a jelly roll.
Shape in half moon, seam side down.
Cover with remaining egg white.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Melt chocolate chips in top of double boiler.
Add melted chocolate to the crushed vanilla wafers, corn syrup, nuts and bourbon.
Mix well until thoroughly blended.
With hands, roll bits of dough into walnut sized balls.
(If dough is sticky, grease hands with butter.)
Roll balls in powdered sugar.
Store in tin or 2 pound coffee can at least 2 or 3 weeks before serving.

title: sherrill's shrimp
directions: Marinate large shrimp in:
butter, lime juice, mustard, olive oil, crushed garlic and Worcestershire sauce.
Marinate 2 to 3 hours.
Grill or broil at 450° for 5 minutes.
(Good with grilled veggies.)

title: western beef chili
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion and garlic.
Combine all remaining chili ingredients to undrained beans.
Stir into beef mixture. Simmer 30 minutes.
Salt and adjust amount of water.
Makes enough for 10 to 15 people.
Hot!

title: poppy seed bundt cake
directions: Mix
everything together in a bowl.
Beat with electric mixer for
about 3 minutes or until well blended.
Pour into a well-greased and
floured
Bundt
pan.
Bake
at
for 50 minutes to 1 hour until toothpick comes out clean.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
In large bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture and mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Cut pickles in chunks. Drain and discard liquid. Mix sugar, water, and vinegar and heat. When it begins to boil, add pickles and heat slightly. Pour back into jar and cool. Put into refrigerator at least 12 hours.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Put half of bread crumbs in casserole.
Add in order given, sauerkraut, corned beef, French dressing, Thousand Island dressing, mustard and Swiss cheese.
Put the other half of crumbs on top of cheese.
Pour melted butter over crumbs.
Add a little more sauerkraut juice, if necessary.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 40 minutes.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: seven-layer salad
directions: Place lettuce in shallow serving pan.
Cover with green onions, celery and water chestnuts.
Break peas apart over salad. Spread mayonnaise evenly over top.
Sprinkle with sugar, cheese, seasoned salt and garlic powder.
Cover and chill as long as 24 hours.
Just before serving, sprinkle salad with grated hard-boiled egg and sprinkle with bacon bits.
(Serves 15 or 20 people.)

title: pizza pie
directions: Mix thoroughly and add 1 cup lukewarm water containing 1 package yeast.
Knead to right consistency (rubbery).
Roll up in a ball and sprinkle with flour.
Let rise 20 minutes.

title: pork chop delight
directions: Brown pork chops with a little bacon grease.
Cook soup as directed except use 1/2 can water.
Cook rice as directed. Arrange chops in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour rice over chops, then pour soup over rice. Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with foil.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes at 350° until tender. Do not overcook chops.

title: pea and cheese salad
directions: Have peas cooled before mixing.
Dice cheese about the same as peas.
Lightly combine all ingredients (except lettuce) and serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes 5 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Bake 350° for 8 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together in casserole dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Put all ingredients in pot.
If desired, tie whole spices in cheesecloth or put in tea strainer.
Cover and set on high for 1 hour, then turn to low for 2 to 8 hours.
Serve from pot with ladle.

title: chicken broccoli divan
directions: Place broccoli in bottom of greased baking dish; add chicken. Combine soup and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese. Combine butter and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over all.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°.
Serves 4.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar.
Add Crisco, milk and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes, then add eggs.
Beat well.
Pour 1/3 of batter into layer pan.
Then, stir in nut meats and spices into rest of batter.
Make 2 layers out of this batter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. When layers are cool, spread filling between layers.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Place fruit in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine flour, sugar and egg; stir until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Spread over fruit.
Drizzle melted butter over topping.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm.
Yields about 6 servings.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In saucepan, combine water (or broth), onion and broccoli. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Place half of mixture in blender; cover and blend until smooth.
Pour in bowl; repeat with remaining mixture or if you want a chunky soup, just pour in bowl with first batch.
Set aside.
In saucepan, melt butter; stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Stir in vegetables; mix.
Cook and stir until soup is heated through. Season to taste with additional salt and pepper.
(Try this recipe using a different vegetable such as potatoes, asparagus, etc.)

title: carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray round pan, 8 x 1 1/2-inches, with nonstick cooking spray.
Reserve 1/4 cup crushed pineapple.
Blend 1/4 cup of the crushed pineapple, the reserved juice and remaining ingredients, except whipped topping, in medium bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, 1 minute.
Beat on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally, 2 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole(for microwave)
directions: Place in casserole in this order:
broccoli, chicken, soup and potatoes.
Top with cheese.
Bake in microwave for 15 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let stand at room temperature, mix and shape into ball.
Roll in minced nuts or parsley.

title: friendship
directions: Take some morning sunshine.
Add a smile.
Some kind words too---

title: best ever chocolate cake
directions: Bake chocolate cake mix according to directions.
When you take out of oven, poke holes all over the top.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over the top and spread.
Pour caramel topping over top and spread.
Pour chocolate topping over top and spread.
Crush Heath bars and sprinkle over the top.

title: icebox slaw
directions: Toss the first 6
ingredients together, then pour cool mixture over them which was made with vinegar, sugar and water. Mix ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Let cool. Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: pecan cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs and lemon juice; blend.
Sift dry ingredients together and combine with raisins and pecans.
Add to creamed mixture and blend thoroughly.
Pour in a well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry milkshakes
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.
Pour into glasses and drink with a straw.
Serves 8 to 12 people.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Open can of salmon and drain liquid.
In a mixing bowl, empty salmon and remove all bones.
Crumble up salmon.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix with your hands.
In frying pan, add 1/2 stick margarine.
Make patties with salmon and turn when each side is brown.
Squeeze lemon over patties (optional).
Makes 4 servings.

title: tater tots casserole
directions: Cook ground beef, drain. Put ground beef on bottom of 13 x 9 baking dish, spread drained green beans on top of beef. Mix soup and milk; pour over beans. Sprinkle cheese over soup; spread tater tots evenly over top of casserole and bake at 400° for 45 minutes. Top with onion rings and return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together sugar and oil.
Add eggs.
In a separate bowl, mix vanilla, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Fold these ingredients into the sugar/oil/egg mixture.
Mix pecans or walnuts, apples and coconut.
Fold these ingredients into the above mixture.
Bake in a greased/floured tube pan for about 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: nanny's green jello
directions: Mix jello and cream cheese in blender and then add drained crushed pineapple.
Let set.

title: chicken and zucchini
directions: Cook chicken and onion on low heat for about 20 minutes.
Add all other ingredients and continue to cook on low for 15 minutes or until zucchini is tender.

title: chicken noodle soup(beef or pork)
directions: Cut all vegetables into small pieces.
Cook vegetables until they are tender, not soft.
Add remaining ingredients.
Make noodles ahead of time and add.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: In a square baking dish, pour in sugar.
Add peaches and mix. Add Bisquick mix.
Use 1 stick of butter and put pats of butter on top.
Preheat oven to 375° and bake for 1 hour or until brown.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Boil chicken in salt water and debone.
Strain liquid and add enough water to make 2 to 3 quarts.
Add green pepper, onion and tomatoes.
Boil 20 minutes.
In a separate bowl, combine butter and flour.
Stir until darken.
Add to the boiled liquid.
After 5 minutes, add chopped chicken and okra.
Cook another 5 to 7 minutes. Add seasoning, salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over rice.

title: broccoli mushroom casserole
directions: Separate broccoli and cook in 1-inch boiling water for 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain.
Put in a 9-inch square pan.
Melt margarine and blend flour, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir until smooth.
Remove from heat and stir in milk; add cheese.
Saute mushrooms in remaining margarine until tender; add to sauce.
Add peppers and cook 1 minute.
Pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pasta with vegetables
directions: Brown garlic cloves in olive oil.
Add broccoli, red pepper and mushrooms.
Cook until tender.
Add wine, water, butter, black pepper and grated cheese.
Cook, uncovered, for approximately 5 minutes.
Cook your favorite pasta according to directions.
Serve vegetables over pasta.

title: jean's manicotti
directions: Fry meat and drain.
Mix all ingredients and fill cooked manicotti.
Arrange manicotti side by side in single layer. Cover with spaghetti sauce.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes covered.

title: strawberry pie(diabetic)
directions: Combine sweetener, water, cornstarch and jello in medium saucepan.
Cook until mixture is clear and becomes thick.
Let cool.
Add strawberries; pour into crust.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken broccoli shells
directions: In a large bowl, combine the alfredo sauce, broccoli, chicken and cheeses.
Spoon into pasta shells.
Place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2 in. baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 - 35 minutes or until heated through.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil the potatoes until tender.
Refrigerate them until cold; peel and grate.
In a large bowl, combine all of the ingredients. Place mixture in a lightly buttered casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 more minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: oven barbecue chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in a greased baking dish.
Sprinkle lightly with salt.
Bake 35 minutes at 400°.
Meanwhile, combine ketchup and remaining ingredients for sauce.
Brush chicken generously with sauce and bake additional 30 minutes and baste occasionally.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Break cake into pieces.
Dissolve the Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water.
Add strawberries.
Make pudding according to directions.
Layer cake, strawberries, pudding and Cook Whip.

title: praline cake
directions: Beat at low speed until mixed well, then beat on high for 2 minutes.
Pour over Praline Mix (recipe follows) and bake for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix and pour ingredients into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach stuffed fish rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, combine spinach, cheese, onion and hot sauce.
Mix well.
Divide filling into 4 portions.
Place one portion across fish; starting with short end, roll fish around filling.
Melt butter and stir in garlic.
