Brush each fish roll with this and place in shallow baking pan. Sprinkle liberally with paprika.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Serve over rice, if desired.

title: amish friendship cake
directions: Keep at room temperature in a covered container.

title: hot shrimp and crab dip
directions: Melt margarine; add cornstarch, then add enough milk to make desired consistency.
Beat eggs well and add a little of the hot mixture to the eggs.
Then pour all the eggs into the mixture. Cook until thickened; more cornstarch dissolved in water may be added if not thick enough.
Add cooking sherry, seasonings and seafoods.
Serve in patty shells from chafing dish.

title: broccoli bisque
directions: In a large saucepan, saute leeks and mushrooms until tender (do not brown).
Add flour and cook, stirring, until bubbling. Remove from heat and gradually blend in chicken broth.
Return to heat and simmer 20 minutes or until broccoli is tender.
Blend in cream and cheese and cook until cheese melts.

title: spinach and chicken quiche
directions: Prick and bake pie crusts for 10 minutes at 350°.
Mix all ingredients and pour into pie crusts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Mix together remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Bake in a 9 x 5 loaf pan. Pecans can be sprinkled on top.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken in salted water.
Remove chicken and debone.
Use chicken broth to make medium-thick gravy.

title: copper pennies salad
directions: Place carrots in large dish with pepper and onions in layers. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over carrots.
Cover lightly and place in refrigerator 12 hours.
Drain part of the dressing.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: First, brown chicken in pan.
Put in a baking pan.
Mix all ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Put in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: phyllis' apple pie mix
directions: Cook all ingredients, except apples, until thick; let cool. Pack apples in jars and pour sauce over.
Seal and process.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Place dill and garlic clove in bottom of a quart jar.
Fill jar with quartered cucumbers.
Place dill on top
of jar.
Boil together vinegar, sugar, water and salt. Fill jars with this hot vinegar solution.
Set completed jars in boiling water for 15 minutes. Simmer.

title: quick chicken parmesan
directions: Using palm of hand, flatten chicken to even thickness.
Dip chicken into egg then into crumbs to coat.
In skillet, over medium heat, in hot butter, brown chicken on both sides.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 10 minutes. Sprinkle with cheeses and parsley.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes or until cheese melts. Serves 4.

title: california chicken
directions: In large baking dish, cover bottom with uncooked rice.
Next use 1 packet of dry onion soup mix; sprinkle on rice.
Place chicken breasts on top of this, then pour one can of golden soup over top.
Add approximately 2 cans of water.
Keep rice watered until 15 minutes before ready to serve.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mom's stew
directions: Cook veggies in water. Add hamburger, spices and soup. Simmer 10 minutes. Serve with rolls.

title: sunrise chicken
directions: Line baking dish with dried beef.
Wrap chicken breasts with strip of bacon, and place on chipped dried beef.
Mix sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Bake in a 300° oven for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: tender meatballs in mushroom gravy
directions: Pull apart bread into small, dime size pieces.
Combine hamburger, bread, salt, pepper and minced onion in large mixing bowl.
Using a spoon, scoop out rounds of meat or shape into several round 2-inch balls by hand.
Brown meatballs in a hot skillet using a small amount of butter or oil.
Turn them occasionally so all sides are browned.
Place meat in crock-pot. Add soup and water.
Cook on low for 6 to 12 hours or high for up to 6 hours.

title: chips and chicken casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and place in casserole.
(May be topped with added crushed chips.)
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: toll house pie
directions: Cream together the first 6 ingredients.
Fill tart shells with the creamed ingredients and bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican pie
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add seasoning and tomatoes; cover 15 minutes.
Put mixture into baking dish and cover with cornbread mix, prepared as directed on package.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: oven fried catfish
directions: Combine egg white and vinegar; stir well.
Combine milk powder and cornmeal.
Add seasonings.
Dip fish into egg white mixture and dredge in cornmeal mixture.
Place fish on rack of broiler pan, coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 400° for 2 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.

title: chinese chews
directions: Place in large mixing bowl:

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: Place beef, water, salt, Worcestershire sauce and pepper in large pot.
Cover and simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour longer.

title: creme filled coffee cake
directions: Melt sugar, salt and oleo in scalded milk.
Add beaten eggs. Liquid should be very warm to touch.
Add 2 cups of the flour; sprinkle dry yeast over flour.
Stir with whisk.
Add rest of flour with big spoon.
Let rise 1 hour in bowl.
Divide dough into three (8-inch) round cake pans; cover with Crumb Topping.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 375° until golden.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add garlic salt, Italian seasoning, onions, pepper, tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Add more liquid, if needed.

title: english berry pudding
directions: Line a deep 1 1/2 to 2-quart bowl with plastic wrap.
Line bottom and sides of bowl with about half the bread triangles, completely covering the surface so there are no gaps between bread slices.
In medium saucepan over high heat, combine berries and raspberry preserves; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium and simmer fruit 5 minutes to release juices.

title: chicken stuffed shells
directions: (Hint:
This is much better if it sits in refrigerator for a day.)

title: old-fashioned peanut butter cookies
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients together; set aside.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat margarine and peanut butter until smooth.
Beat in sugars until blended.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture; beat until well blended.
Chill dough.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten slightly and decorate with candied cherries or flatten with fork and colored sugars.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: country ham dip
directions: In a food processor, grind ham.
Add onion and bell pepper. Chop well.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, milk and pepper.
Blend well.
Pour into a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Top with pecans. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat in microwave on medium until butter is melted and sugar is dissolved (about 8 minutes usually). Place in airtight jar and keep in refrigerator.
Use for grilling or broiling.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix with electric mixer until smooth.
Using a spring-form pan, make graham cracker crust (use your own favorite recipe). Add cheese mixture to pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: my favorite lentil soup
directions: Heat the oil in a large saucepan and saute the onions, carrots, marjoram and thyme, stirring the vegetables for about 5 minutes.
Add the tomatoes, broth and lentils.
Bring the soup to a boil.
Reduce the heat, cover the pan and simmer the soup for about 1 hour or until the lentils are tender.
Add the salt, pepper, wine and parsley and simmer the soup for a few minutes. Serve with cheese sprinkled on each portion.

title: pepperoni dip
directions: Add small amounts of cheese, pepperoni and milk; slowly blend. Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: persimmon butter
directions: Cook the persimmon pulp slowly with a little water, stirring often. Cook together until thick and brown.
Put in hot sterilized jars and seal.
Yields nine 1/2 pints.

title: potato chip dip
directions: Fry bacon and crumble.
Mix all ingredients together and add bacon.
Serve with ruffled potato chips.

title: dolly favorite dessert
directions: Cream egg yolks with sugar and whip until smooth.
Add flour and mix well.
Scald milk and when hot enough, add the cream mixture.
Stir constantly, 20 to 25 minutes until it thickens. Remove heat and add vanilla.
Boil some water.
Whip egg whites and add to boiling water until hardened.
Remove with spatula and put on top of cream mixture.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Chill.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Saute raw, shelled nuts in 2 tablespoons butter for 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
Spread popcorn in shallow pan. Put in 250° oven.
Fold in peanuts.
Combine margarine, brown sugar, corn syrup and salt in 2-quart pan over medium heat, stir until sugar dissolves.
Boil to firm ball (248°) about 5 minutes. Remove and stir in soda to foam.
Take corn from oven and pour caramel over popcorn in a fine stream.
Stir well.
Return to oven 45 to 50 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Cool.
Store in airtight containers.
Keep in cool place.

title: corn sticks(7 corn sticks or small skillet)
directions: Mix with buttermilk.
Spoon into cold, greased stick pan and bake at 450° until brown.
The mayonnaise takes the place of eggs and shortening.
Heaping Tbsp. in this recipe means all the meal, flour and mayonnaise you can scoop up with a tablespoon at one time.

title: sweet relish
directions: Grind tomatoes, celery, onions and peppers together and mix with
cup salt.
Let stand 2 hours and drain 2 hours. Take remaining ingredients; stir all together and pack in jars when cold.

title: sis' frozen fruit salad
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil in small saucepan.
Reduce heat and simmer until syrupy, 8 minutes.
Cool.
Combine remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir in cooled syrup.
Spoon into 18 foil-lined muffin cups and freeze until firm, 4 hours or overnight. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 18 servings.
Per serving has 90 calories, 0 grams of fat, 0 grams of saturated fat, 0 grams of cholesterol.

title: spring salmon dinner
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, preheat broiler if manufacturer directs.
Cut potatoes into 1/4-inch thick slices. Arrange potato slices in single layer at one end of rack in broiling pan.
In small saucepan over low heat, melt 2 tablespoons corn oil spread. Stir in pepper and 1/2 teaspoon salt. With pastry brush, lightly brush some light corn oil spread mixture over potato slices.
Place broiling pan in oven 5 to 7-inches from source of heat.
Broil potatoes 8 minutes.

title: austrian jam cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugar, vanilla and egg yolk in medium bowl until fluffy.
Stir in flour and gather dough into a ball.
Chill several hours.
Roll 1 teaspoon of dough into a ball.
Dip into slightly beaten egg white and roll in chopped nuts.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet 1 inch apart.
Press indentation in center of each cookie and fill with jam.
Bake in 300° oven for 20 minutes or until lightly golden.
Cool on wire rack.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake in oblong pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix Crisco, 1 cup sugar and eggs.
Add soda to buttermilk; stir until foaming.
Add the buttermilk with the dry ingredients to the Crisco mix.
Add dates, orange rind and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured pan in moderate oven (375°) for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: white cake
directions: Beat egg whites until they peak, but are not dry.
Set aside. Cream butter and sugar. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with milk to the creamed mixture.
Fold in vanilla and egg whites. Pour into 3 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: christmas salad
directions: Make red jello as directed on package; pour into a large glass pan.
Let set.
Mix together the Cool Whip, cream cheese, drained pineapple and the mayonnaise.
Melt the marshmallows, the juice from the pineapple and the lemon jello (no water).
Cool.
When starting to set, mix with the pineapple mixture.
Carefully spread over the red jello; let set.
Top with prepared lime jello. Decorate with maraschino cherries that have been dried with paper towel, when the lime jello starts to set.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Sift together the flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Cut in butter.
Stir in raisins.
Combine buttermilk, egg and baking soda.
Stir buttermilk mixture into flour mixture until just moistened, then divide into 2 round loaves and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup(diet)
directions: Pour in pan 2 to 3 tablespoons sunflower oil.
Heat and stir-fry the celery and onion (cut up).
When tender, stir in the broccoli (only flowerets), not the stalks.
Stir until covered with oil. Add the water. Cover and boil. When boils, add the bouillon cubes and bouquet garni or other soup spices to taste. Cover and simmer until broccoli is just tender.

title: apples in hand(kids)
directions: Peel (optional) and core a whole apple.
Mix peanut butter with one of the following:
raisins, wheat germ or granola.
Stuff into the hole of the cored apple.
This may be sliced in half for table serving.
Soft cheese may also be stuffed into the hole.

title: pickled jalapeno peppers
directions: Wash jalapenos and leave whole.
Peel carrots and cut in 3/8 inch pieces.
Wash onions, peel and quarter.
Wash and sterilize jars.
Pack peppers, carrots and onions in jars.
Heat vinegar and water to boiling and lower temperature to 175°.
Add 1 tablespoon olive oil to each jar along with 1 bay leaf, 1 garlic clove and a little oregano if desired.
Pour brine (175°) over peppers.
Let cool slightly and seal jars.
Eat in 4 to 6 weeks or when peppers turn olive green.
There is enough brine for 8 pints.

title: shrimp louis dip
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Cover and chill well. Yields about 3 cups.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix the sugar, cocoa, flour and dash of salt.
Mix the milk and egg yolks.
Mix the milk and egg mixture into the first mixture.
Cook until thick. Add 1/2 stick butter and vanilla. Cool and pour into baked 9-inch pie crust. Cover with meringue and brown at 300°.

title: philly crab spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and milk.
Add crab meat, onion and horseradish.
Blend well.
Spoon into ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve piping hot to spread on crackers.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Grease tube pan.
Mix together apples, sugar and cinnamon; set aside.
Mix all other ingredients; beat until smooth.
Alternate 1/3 batter and 1/3 apple mix until complete.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: angel sweets
directions: In saucepan, melt chocolate and butter over low heat.
Remove from heat and blend in egg.
Stir in sugar, nuts and marshmallows, blending well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in coconut.
Chill. Yield: 48.

title: paprika chicken
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; add oil.
Dip chicken in mixture and place in shallow pan.
Bake 1 hour at 400°, turning once.

title: mexican hot chocolate
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly. Stir until mix is blended and all chocolate is melted.
Beat to froth.

title: honey-apple pork chops
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pork chops; mix well.
Place pork chops in shallow dish; pour marinade over chops.
Cover and refrigerate overnight, turning occasionally.
Remove pork chops from marinade.
Place on grill approximately 6 inches above medium-hot coals.
Grill for 10 to 15 minutes, turning once and basting with marinade.

title: fudge
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients in heavy large saucepan.

Bring to a full boil, stirring, and cook for 10 minutes at medium-high heat, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat and add marshmallows and chocolate chips immediately. Do not stir. After 20 minutes, add vanilla and beat with electric mixer until thoroughly mixed. Add nuts and pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate. Makes 5 pounds.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Same recipe as Cinnamon Rolls except only roll dough to 1/2-inch thick and add raisins along with cinnamon.
Roll dough and place seam side down into loaf pan; be sure to tuck the ends down under and bake at 350° until loaf sounds hollow.

title: yummy fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve warm.
I have only tried sliced apples.
It's always a hit wherever I take it.

title: mock stroganoff
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain off grease.
Add soup and milk; heat well.
Remove from heat; stir in sour cream (be careful not to let cream curdle).
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix broccoli, mayonnaise, soup and cheese together.
Put into baking dish.
Put crackers on top of casserole.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until top is browned.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Beat 2 eggs and 1 cup sugar.
Add 2 more eggs and 1 cup sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add to this mixture 2 cups flour and 2 teaspoons baking powder.
Put on stove 1 stick margarine and 1 cup milk; let come to a boil.
Pour milk into flour mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 375° for layers for about 30 minutes or at 350° for a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Make day before or up to 3 days before serving.
Cook carrots until crisp-tender; drain and cool.
Place in a 3-quart bowl.
Add green pepper and onion; set aside.

title: chicken casserole or hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and chips.
Place in ungreased 1-quart baking dish.
Cover with cheese and crushed chips.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix sugar and flour in large mixing bowl.
Heat margarine, cocoa, water and oil in saucepan until it reaches boiling point.
Pour hot mixture over flour and sugar mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 11 x 15 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 20 minutes.
Frost as follows.

title: scrambled eggs with cheese
directions: Cook and scramble eggs until thick, but not solid.
Add cheese and cook 1 to 2 more minutes or until mixture holds together.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Stir flour and sugar together; add eggs, evaporated milk, juice from cherries and water.
Melt butter and add; stir in food coloring and vanilla.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Remove from stove and fold in cherries.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Refrigerate overnight and top with whipped cream to serve.

title: fudge cake
directions: Blend sugar and oil.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk.
Sift flour, cream of tartar, cocoa and salt.
Add to first mixture.
Mix well. Last, add boiling water containing soda.
Mix well.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into tin foil-lined cake pan and bake 30 to 35 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Melt
butter, water and milk together on stove at 110°. Then add to other ingredients.
Knead dough well.
Let sit for 1 hour. Knead again, let set for thirty minutes; knead dough; roll and bake until golden brown.

title: aunt mary's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and flour alternately (1 egg and 1/2 cup flour), mixing after each.
Add flavoring.
Beat well (2 to 3 minutes) on medium/high speed.
Pour batter into Bundt cake pan that has been sprayed with Baker's Joy, Pam or greased and floured.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes in 350° preheated oven.

title: catfish stew
directions: Mix bacon fat, potatoes and onions together in large pot and cook until potatoes are done.
Add tomato soup, catsup, salt, pepper and hot sauce.
Cook to a hard boil.
Add fish and cook for 20 minutes on medium heat, stirring often to prevent sticking. Serves 10 to 15.

title: grandma glazier's bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, peppers, onion and salt; let stand overnight.
Cover with weighted lid to keep vegetables under brine. Next morning drain well.
Make syrup of sugar, vinegar, mustard, turmeric and mustard seed.
Bring to boil, add vegetables, bring to a boil again, simmer a few minutes.
Pack into hot jars (sterile) and process 15 minutes in hot water bath.
Make about 7 pints.

title: pork chops or cube steaks
directions: Wash chops or steaks; drain, then batter in dry flour real good.
Put in pan with hot Crisco oil.
Brown quickly.
Put into baking dish with rack in bottom (where it won't stick, lay each one into baking dish or pan that you can cover for steaming).
Put in 300° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until very tender.

title: potato stuffed franks!(colorful and tasty)
directions: Fix hot dogs like this once, and we wager you'll do it often!! Cut frankfurters almost through lengthwise and lay open.
Place on a pan and heat in oven about 10 minutes.
Use leftover mashed potatoes (about 1 1/2 cups of them) in a bowl.
Add egg.
Then add chopped green onions (or regular onion), prepared mustard and celery salt (optional).
Spoon the potato mixture over the frankfurters.
Put the baking pan into the oven again and cook 10 to 15 minutes in a 425° oven.
An attractive and tasty dish.

title: margie's peanut brittle
directions: Cook raw peanuts, sugar and Karo to 300°.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Pour it on greased cookie sheet.
Let cool, then break into pieces.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, parmesan cheese together.
Fold in chilies and artichoke hearts.
Place in baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: In large saucepan, or Dutch oven, combine all ingredients over medium-high heat.
Stirring frequently, cook until jelly melts and ingredients are well-blended.
Remove from heat.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: fruit lizzies
directions: Mix as regular cookies.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: aunt marie's apple cake
directions: Combine apples, oil, sugar and beaten eggs.
Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to batter.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45
minutes.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Prepare Kool-Aid as directed on package.
Add all other ingredients and stir gently.

title: old settlers beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
In skillet, brown hamburger and cook onion until tender.
Drain fat.
In a large bowl, mix the barbecue sauce, catsup, sugars, chili powder, salt, pepper, mustard and molasses.
Mix well and add the bacon and cooked hamburger-onion mix.
Mix together the pinto beans, pork and beans, butter beans and the kidney beans.
Mix beans and meat sauce together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Add and mix all of the ingredients in a bowl. Refrigerate. Serve as needed.

title: crabmeat treats
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Pile high on toasted rounds of white bread.
Bake in 450° oven until heated through.

title: milky way cake
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients together.
Add eggs to mixture.
Add buttermilk to mixture and mix well.
Sift next 3 dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Add boiling water to mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Drop batter onto hot griddle.

title: tres leche cake
directions: In a medium sized bowl, mix together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add sugar and continue to beat until stiff.
Add yolks, one at a time and incorporate well.
Slowly add flour mixture, alternately, with milk; beat until mixed well.
Add vanilla.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 8-inch round layer pans.
Bake at 375° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool cake; remove from pans and set aside.
Do not wash pans; you will need them in a minute.
Then combine Carnation milk, Eagle Brand milk and whipping cream.
Place cooled cake rounds back in pans and pour 1/3 of the milk mixture onto each layer.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours, making sure all milk is absorbed.

title: red, white and blueberry shortcake
directions: Split cake into 3 layers.
Place bottom layer on serving plate; spread with 1 cup blueberry filling.
Add second layer of cake; spread with 1 cup strawberry or cherry filling.
Top with third layer of cake.
Frost top and sides of cake with whipped topping. Chill.
Slice and serve with remaining pie filling. Serves 6 to 8.

title: skillet corn bread
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, sugar and salt.
Add corn meal and mix.
Melt shortening in skillet.
Combine beaten egg, milk and melted shortening.
Add flour mixture and blend.
Pour into hot greased iron skillet.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Place 1/2 cup pecans and 1/2 cup fudge topping into bottom of pie crust. Spoon ice cream that has been blended with the coffee flavored liqueur and 1/2 cup whipped cream into pie crust. Freeze for 4 hours.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.
Top each piece with remaining whipped cream, pecans and fudge topping.

title: chocolate frosty
directions: Pour into ice cream freezer and make according to manufacturer's directions.

title: bitz' o' brickle
directions: Cook cake by box directions.
When done, poke holes in cake. The end of a wooden spoon works good.
Pour milk and fudge over cake.
Put in refrigerator to cool.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with candy.

title: braised veal
directions: Heat oil until nearly smoking.
Add meat (don't crowd) and brown quickly.
Remove and drain on paper towel.
Reduce heat.
Add onion, garlic and bell pepper.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes, stock and vermouth.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer.
Add herbs and mushrooms.
Cover and cook for 1 hour.
Serve plain or with rice/pasta.
Serves 4 people.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite-size pieces.
(This takes approximately 4 months.)
Cook over kerosene fire at 525° until tender (about 5 months).
Add salt and pepper and cover with brown gravy.
This will serve 3,800 people.
If more are expected, add 2 rabbits.
Do this only if absolutely necessary, as most people do not like to find hare in their stew.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Line casserole dish with chipped beef.
Top with chicken.
Mix sour cream and soup; spread over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 2 hours at 250°.

title: sunflower no knead bread
directions: Scald milk and add 1 cup warm water and 2 tablespoons of yeast. Mix in 4 1/2 cups flour, enough to make a gooey dough.
Add sunflower seeds.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Cook sausage and cut into bite-size pieces.
Mix together the eggs, mustard and 1-3/4 c. milk; set aside.
Layer bread cubes, sausage, grated cheese and chilies in pan.
Pour egg mixture over the top.
Mix soup with 1/2 c. milk and spread over the top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until set.
tags: cream of chicken and mushroom soup

title: taco bake casserole
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with broken taco shells or chips.
Cover with meat, browned with the taco seasoning mix added.
Next, layer the kidney beans or refried beans.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix ahead and let stand 1 hour.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: crab casserole
directions: Pick over crab meat, removing any shell.
Mix melted butter with dill, Tabasco, Worcestershire and lemon juice.
Place crab meat in a 2-quart casserole dish; pour seasoned butter mixture over all.
Top with stuffing and dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: maxine's french apple pie
directions: Roll apples in sugar and cinnamon.
Dot apples with a tablespoon and a half of butter.
Place apple mixture into deep-dish pie crust.

title: quick cherry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt butter or margarine in 9 x 9-inch cake pan.
In mixing bowl, combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk; pour over melted shortening but do not stir.
Add almond extract to cherries and pour cherries and juice over flour mixture.
Do not stir.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar over cherries.
Bake until done, about 45 minutes.

title: angel salad(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Drain pears and save 1 cup of the juice; put juice in a small saucepan and heat until boiling.
Dissolve Jell-O in it.
In blender, put water and cubed cream cheese; blend on high until creamy.
Add pears and Jell-O and blend.
Pour into serving bowl and add Cool Whip.
Blend in.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, butter, salt and milk for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and add oatmeal, peanut butter, vanilla and marshmallow cream.
Drop by spoonful on waxed paper.
Cool.

title: old-fashioned chicken and dressing
directions: Crumble all of these ingredients together and pour in the chicken broth.
The secret of good dressing is plenty of broth. Cook in 450° oven for about 35 minutes.
Debone chicken and set to the side.
Best to not place chicken on top during baking.
It will stay good for several days just plain.

title: italian fried chicken breast
directions: Heat skillet to between low and medium with olive oil 1/4-inch deep.
Pound chicken breasts until very thin. Dip in egg, then dip into the bread crumbs. Fry in the olive oil for 1 to 2 minutes. Season with Old Bay seasoning.
Cooking time will depend on how thin the breasts are pounded.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with pastry blender.
Combine next 3 ingredients and add to flour mixture.
Chill dough for at least 15 minutes.
Makes two 9-inch pies and 1 single crust.

title: never-fail pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add others and beat all together well. Cook on hot griddle until golden brown.

title: jack daniels b b q sauce
directions: Combine onion, garlic, and Whiskey in a 3 qt. pot.
Saute several minutes.
Remove from heat and light mixture, flame for 20 seconds.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer 20-25 minutes, stirring constantly.
Run sauce throughy a medium strainer to remove onion and garlic bits if you prefer a smoother sauce.
Cool and enjoy on any kind of meat.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli for 5 minutes, then drain.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Put in casserole dish and bake for 1 hour.
Top with Ritz crackers before baking.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Use a 2-quart casserole.
Put drained pineapple in bottom of dish.
Mix flour, sugar and cheese and put on top of pineapple. Then put on Ritz crackers and pour melted butter over crackers. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken, then pick chicken off bones.
Prepare cornbread stuffing as directed on package using chicken broth.
Spread stuffing in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix the two soups, adding just enough water or broth to make mixture spreadable.
Stir in chicken.
Alternate layers of stuffing and chicken mixture. Sprinkle stuffing over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: You will need 2 greased loaf pans.

title: pork roast(veseevio)
directions: Saute salt pork; add olive oil, minced garlic, rosemary leaves, salt and pepper.
Cook until well blended.
Put on roast. Bake at 350° until done according to size of roast.
Remove and add potatoes, which have been cut lengthwise (1 medium potato about 5 cuts).
Put back into oven and cook about 20 minutes.
Add some water if necessary.
Potatoes will turn brown.
Bon appetit!

title: nancy's sourdough bread
directions: You
should
mix
this
in
and let it stand out of the refrigerator
for
8 to 12 hours, uncovered.
The mixture will be very
bubbly
and if you listen carefully, you can hear it sizzling.
Take out one cup to make bread and return remaining starter
to
refrigerator.
Keep
in refrigerator 3 to 5 days, then
resume
feeding again.
If you do not plan to make bread after
feeding
the
starter,
just share a cup with a friend. They can
put
it in the refrigerator for a few hours, feed it and then make their own bread.

title: broccoli casserole with rice
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Cook broccoli by package directions.
Mix all ingredients and bake for 30 minutes at 325°. Serves about 8 people.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken

title: vienna chocolate frosting and filling
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Remove from boiling water; add sugar and water.
Beat well after each addition.
Add butter, 1/3 at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time. Combine flour and baking powder; add to butter mixture alternately with milk.
Add flavoring.
Pour into greased and floured pan. Set in cold oven.
Set temperature at 325° and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: creamy peas and carrots
directions: Drain peas and carrots.
Heat peas, carrots and margarine. Add just enough milk to cover peas and carrots; season with a dash of salt and pepper.
Let mixture simmer (don't boil); add a pinch of granulated sugar.
Remove from heat; add cornstarch and thicken to desired consistency.
Enjoy.

title: country ham and red eye gravy
directions: Place ham in a little oil and cook over low heat. Remove ham and add boiling water and coffee to drippings. Cook 10 minutes. Eat with hot biscuits and you will think you are back on the farm.

title: cheddary pasta and vegetables
directions: Cook macaroni.
In same pan, add at the last 5 minutes of cooking the carrots and broccoli.
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients; stir into pasta mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until cheese melts.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix all ingredients and let chill 3 hours or more.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth. On top of casserole, put the following mixture:

title: spinach dip
directions: Let spinach thaw in carton and squeeze water out.
Mix well with all ingredients.
Serve as a dip or stuff tomatoes.
(Take a round loaf of bread. Cut the center out and place dip in middle, using the cut up bread with the dip.)

title: parker house rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add sugar, salt and shortening to hot milk.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and flour. Beat well.
Cover.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness, cut with a biscuit cutter.
Cruse through the middle with the dull edge of knife.
Brush with melted butter and fold.
Press tightly.
Place on greased biscuit pans.
Cover to rise until light.
Bake.
Just before removing rolls from the oven brush tops with melted butter.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all together in bowl and form into patties, then fry in vegetable oil until lightly brown.
Turn once.
Can be formed into salmon loaf as well.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Cook beef and onion in butter until meat is lightly browned. Add mushrooms, including liquid, water, gravy mix and paprika. Simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sour cream. Heat, but do not boil.
Garnish with parsley flakes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: english martrimonials(for tea)
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and oats.
Work in softened butter until mixture is crumbly.
Press 1/2 evenly into bottom of an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Spread evenly with jam.
Press remaining mixture over jam, covering completely.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes. Cool and slice into squares.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Mix in blender chicken soup, mushroom soup, chicken broth, Ro-Tel tomatoes, chili powder and salt and pepper.
Butter a casserole.
Put in a layer of chicken, tortillas, bell pepper, onion and cheese.
Pour half the sauce on top.
Repeat another layer of each, saving some cheese for on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, milk, salt and pepper in bowl. Make into patties and brown lightly.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour mixture over browned patties.
Bake at 300° for one hour.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Mix separately the remaining ingredients. Combine and add beans.
Chill before serving.

title: tin roof pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and mix well.
Press firmly on bottom and sides of a buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Spread ice cream over crust.
Cover and freeze overnight.
To serve, drizzle with chocolate and sprinkle with peanuts.

title: liz's chill-out salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in salad bowl and toss. Add dressing and toss.

title: buttermilk mexican corn bread
directions: Combine flour, cornmeal, baking powder, baking soda and salt in large bowl.
Add buttermilk, eggs, picante sauce and butter. Stir just until ingredients are blended.
Pour into well-greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and set aside.
Sift together the flour, soda, salt and spices.
Use 1/4 cup flour mixture to dredge raisins and nuts.
Add flour mixture to sweet potato mixture and mix well.
Grease and flour four 1-pound coffee cans.
Divide mixture evenly in cans.
Bake at 290° to 300° for 2 hours or until done.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve with chips or veggie sticks.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Using a cookie sheet or similar sheet pan, unroll crescent rolls and lay dough side by side, overlapping dough and covering bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: alta's lemon icing
directions: Poke holes in warm cake with toothpicks or fork.
Mix juice of 2 lemons with powdered sugar.
Pour over warm cake.

title: orange blossoms
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Mix in sour cream and eggs. In a separate bowl, mix dry ingredients together.
Add flour mixture to batter and mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven to wire racks to cool slightly.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large punch bowl.
Let chill for at least 2 hours before serving.
Makes about 50 servings.

title: john's favorite penuche icing
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar.
Boil over low heat 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in milk; bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Cool to lukewarm.
Gradually add powdered sugar and beat on high until thick enough to spread.
If too thick, add a few drops of water.
Wonderful on spice or butter pecan cake.

title: chicken bites
directions: Cover 2 cookie sheets with foil.
Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Mix crumbs, cheese and seasonings.
Dip chicken pieces into melted butter, then into crumb mixture.
Place chicken pieces about 1/2-inch apart on cookie sheets.
Bake uncovered until golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes about 72 appetizers.

title: butterscotch patties
directions: Put syrup and sugar into saucepan; heat until sugar dissolves, then add vinegar.
Continue boiling, without stirring, until it reaches 260° (hard ball stage).
Add butter and continue cooking to 270° (soft crack stage).
Remove from heat.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Place eggs in buttered casserole and season to taste.
Cook sausage; drain and sprinkle over eggs.
Pour sour cream over sausage.
Combine crumbs and cheese.
Sprinkle over casserole. Place in oven to heat thoroughly and brown top under broiler. Serves 6.

title: fig bars
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until done. When cool, cut into squares.

title: confetti scalloped potatoes
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix shortening, hot water, lemon juice and egg yolk well and stir into flour mixture.
Chill.

title: "in and out" skillet beef
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, warm the roast beef. Separate the slices and "drape" them around the pan.
When warm, add the gravy, Worcestershire and salt.
Cook and stir, blending well and coating the meat as much as possible.
Add the sherry and cook for 1 to 2 minutes.
Then add the tomatoes, onion, mushrooms, peas and carrots.
Cover and simmer for about 5 minutes.
Serve hot with garlic bread.

title: penne with golden garlic
directions: Place oil and garlic in a medium saute pan.
Cook over medium-low heat until garlic is soft and light golden brown.
Stir frequently to prevent sticking.
Add tomatoes and their juice, salt and pepper and bouillon cube.
Cook until a sauce forms.

title: mama's homemade custard ice cream
directions: Heat
milk.
Beat eggs until light colored.
Sift sugar with flour.
Gradually
add eggs.
Add egg mixture to hot milk while stirring
constantly.
When spoon is coated and mixture slightly thickened,
remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
To make larger and richer, add 1 large can Pet milk with a little more sugar.
This mixture
will burn or boil over easily if vessel is not
large enough.
Use
medium heat.
Pour custard in ice cream freezer and let the men turn the freezer handle.

title: artichoke and crab meat salad
directions: Mix artichoke, crab meat, chopped olives and seasonings. Use enough oil to coat ingredients and 1/4 as much lemon juice. Chill and serve.

title: orange sweet potato casserole(especially for greg)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove skin from baked sweet potatoes and place in large bowl.
Add orange juice concentrate, orange zest, brown sugar, lemon juice and Molly McButter and mix.
Fold in marshmallows.
Bake in casserole sprayed with nonstick cooking spray at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Recipe makes 6 servings. Fat-free.

title: pecan pie
directions: Blend ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: layer lime salad
directions: Layer all ingredients in order given.
Chill overnight or at least 2 hours.
Toss before serving.

title: brother's chocolate cake
directions: Mix together in large bowl with electric beater. Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: irish potatoes(5 dozen)
directions: Cream together first 2 ingredients.
Add confectioners sugar and salt.
Combine vanilla and coconut.
Let sit to slightly harden.
Roll in cinnamon.
Refrigerate after rolled into balls.

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cheese. Press half of mixture into a casserole dish.
Put cheese on top and press the other half of meat on top of cheese. Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until done.
Mix mayonnaise, cheese and butter; pour over vegetables.
Crumble Ritz crackers on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: onion casserole
directions: Peel onions and slice into thin rings.
Saute in margarine until limp (opaque).
Put half of sauteed onions in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with Parmesan cheese and then with crushed crackers.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes (golden brown).

title: frozen crunch pops
directions: Pour yogurt into small mixing bowl.
Add the applesauce and granola or nuts.
Shake in the cinnamon.
Mix well.
Spoon half the mixture into each cup.
Put popsicle stick in the middle of each cup, standing up.
Place cups in freezer for at least 2 hours.
Peel off paper cups and share with a friend.

title: cabbage spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburg, not fried, and 1 onion, chopped.
Cook spaghetti.
Cut cabbage longways as thin as possible to resemble spaghetti.
Put chopped second onion in pan; don't fry.
Lay sliced cabbage on top.
Lower heat; add parsley.
Stir to coat with oil. When cabbage is tender, add cooked drained spaghetti.
Stir to coat.
Let cook for 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir often over low heat. Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together; add oil and vanilla.
Stir well. Add flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Blend and add zucchini and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (325° if glass pans) in greased and floured pans.
Makes 2 loaves or 1 Bundt pan.

title: peanut butter play dough
directions: Mix until it becomes like dough.
Eat while you play!

title: italian sauce la roma
directions: Heat oil in a large heavy saucepan over moderately high heat (275°).
Add sausage and cook until lightly browned, stirring occasionally.
Add onion and garlic; cook until tender.
Reduce heat to moderately low (225°).
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, water, bay leaf, beef bouillon cube, oregano, basil, salt and pepper. Cover and cook for two hours, stirring occasionally.
Add additional water if sauce becomes too thick.
Discard bay leaf. Viola! Italian Sauce La Roma.

title: pumpkin, raisin and nut bread
directions: Preheat oven
to
Grease
and flour 3 loaf pans. Combine oil,
eggs,
water	and
pumpkin.
Sift
together into mixing bowl,
flour, salt, nutmeg, baking powder, cinnamon and sugar.
Make a
well in the center and add the pumpkin mixture and blend in the dry ingredients until mixture is moist.
Stir in raisins and
nuts.	Turn in baking pans and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Beat eggs with fork in large bowl.
Stir in cake mix, extract, oil and cherries (get all juice from can with 2 Tbsp. water). Bake in greased, floured 9x13 pan for 25-30 minutes at 350°.

title: carrots
directions: Cover carrots with water (salted, if desired).
Boil 10 minutes; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients well and pour over carrots.
Toss, cover and let stand overnight.

title: lenas bread pudding
directions: In a mixing bowl beat eggs; add sugar then butter.
Stir. Add evaporated milk, water and vanilla, stir.
Pour mixture into a buttered 1 1/2 - 2 quart casserole dish.
Place broken pieces of bread over mixture; sprinkle top with cinnamon and sugar.
Place casserole dish into another pan with 1 1/2 inches of hot water. Bake for one hour at 350°.	Delicious!

title: play group muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line muffin tins with paper baking cups. Mix flour, oats, baking powder, cinnamon and salt in a large bowl. Whisk eggs and oil in another bowl until creamy.
Whisk in sugar and vanilla.
Stir in apple, cranberries and raisins.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Fold in just until dry ingredients are moistened (mixture wil be very thick).
Spoon batter into muffin cups.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until golden.

title: snicker bar cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to box instructions.
Pour half of this mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. (Don't flour pan.) This is the crust.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Meanwhile, melt caramels with margarine and milk.
Pour over baked crust. Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over caramel mixture.
Spread remaining batter over top.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°, then bake for 5 minutes at 325°.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Immediately press a chocolate kiss in the center of each cookie. Remove to wire racks to cool.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: buffet bean bake
directions: Drain all beans.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Fry bacon until crisp. Remove from skillet, crumble and set aside.
Drain all but about 2 tablespoons drippings from skillet.
Add sugar, vinegar, salt and mustard; simmer uncovered 10 minutes.

title: one bowl jelly roll
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla until lemon color with mixer, then add flour mixture. Blend only until mixed.
Spread evenly in a greased wax paper covered 9 x 13-inch cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Loosen cake carefully from paper and put on a powdered sugar towel and roll up.
Add jelly after cooled and slice.

title: bob hope's lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine first three ingredients in boiler; add water.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook 2 minutes or until mixture is clear and thickens.
Stir small amount of mixture into beaten egg yolks.
Stir egg yolks into hot mixture.
Cook on low heat for 3 minutes.
Stir in 1/3 cup fresh lemon juice, oleo and grated lemon.
Pour into pie shell.

title: turkey with wild rice and mushrooms
directions: Lightly brown the mushroom and onion in 2 tablespoons butter. Place in an oiled casserole dish.
Add the turkey, rice, almonds, salt and pepper.
Stir in the cream and chicken broth.
Cover and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.
Remove cover, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and dot with the remaining butter. Increase the oven temperature to 450° and bake for an additional 5 to 10 minutes.

title: red rice
directions: Fry strips of bacon and remove from pan.
Brown onion in fat and add tomatoes and salt.
When thoroughly hot, add rice and cook slowly until rice is done. Extra good if you break up bacon strips and add just before serving.

title: cheese cake
directions: Freeze carnation milk to mesh state.
Pour boiling water over jello an lemon juice.
Stir good, let cool.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and vanilla.
Mix cinnamon crisp with melted butter and line pan with crisp mixture.
Whip carnation milk.
Blend together milk, jello and cream cheese mixtures.
When mixed together good pour over crisp and chill in refrigerator over night.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Combine cooked carrots and margarine in blender.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Mix together all ingredients, adding the vanilla extract, in blender or food processor.
Pour into lightly greased 1-quart baking dish.
Place baking dish in another pan with water to help steam carrots as they bake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pickle-in-the-middle
directions: In medium bowl, stir together cream cheese and American cheese.
Spread about 1 tablespoon cheese mixture on each piece of bologna.
Place 2 pickles on bologna slices.
Roll.
Refrigerate for at least an hour to chill.
Cut each bologna slice into 3/4 slices.
Yield: 40.

title: impossible lasagne pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.

title: sissie's buttermilk biscuits
directions: If you choose not to sift flour, use 4 tablespoons shortening instead of 3.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place potatoes into baking dish.
In a small bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over potatoes and stir until potatoes are coated with mixture.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 30 minutes or until potatoes are soft.

title: potato soup
directions: Cover potatoes with water 2-inches over them. Add onion, crumbled bacon, salt, oleo and pepper. Cook until potatoes are done.
Mix meal and flour in 2/3 cup cold water. Stir in potatoes and let simmer while stirring for 5 minutes.

title: mexican bean soup
directions: Rinse beans and bring to a boil in enough water to cover by 1 inch.
Let stand 1 hour; drain.
Cook in the 3 cups water until tender, about 2 hours.
Puree 1/2 cup of the beans in a blender; reserve.
Saute garlic, onion, parsley, celery and cabbage until wilted in a medium size saucepan.
Add beans and all ingredients. Heat and serve hot.
Makes 8 servings.

title: apricot pecan bars
directions: Unroll crescent dough into a rectangle; press into a greased 13x9x2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with 1 cup pecans, confectioners sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Drop preserves over the top.

title: cheese dish
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, brown meat with 1 teaspoon garlic powder and 2 teaspoons salt until it loses its red color.
Drain off fat and put into a 2-quart casserole dish (oval heats more evenly than round).
Cook potatoes in boiling water with 2 teaspoons salt until barely fork-tender, 5 to 9 minutes depending on stove. Drain and put on top of meat in casserole.
Saute onion and green pepper in 1 tablespoon fat from heat, about 5 minutes or until tender.
Add thawed green beans.
Add tomato soup, water, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, 1 teaspoon garlic powder and black pepper to taste.

title: surfer squares
directions: Melt butterscotch pieces, sugar and butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat, add egg and beat well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in remaining ingredients after letting first mixture cool.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars or squares.

title: dump it cake
directions: First, dump pineapple and juice in a 12 x 9-inch cake pan, then dump the cherry pie filling on top.
Spread the cake mix over mixture.
Sprinkle coconut over cake mix.
Melt your butter and pour over coconut.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix fruit in dry jello and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: red beans 'n rice
directions: Fry bacon; remove from pan to paper towel.
In bacon grease, fry onions, green pepper and celery.
Sprinkle in cayenne pepper and cumin.
In a separate pan, fry sausage.
Drain and discard grease.
Stir in tomatoes and browned veggie mixture, including bacon grease.
Heat to simmer.
Stir in bacon and beans.
Heat to simmer again.
Add salt, pepper and picante sauce.
Serve over rice.

title: velveeta chillie roll
directions: On a board, place Velveeta between two pieces of waxed paper (cheese needs to be room temperature).
Using rolling pin, roll cheese into a thin rectangular shape.
Spread with sour cream; top with green chillies.
Starting with the wide end, shape and roll, jelly roll fashion.
Place rolled cheese in foil and chill.
To serve, place on platter; sprinkle with paprika and garnish with parsley if desired.
Serve with crackers.
Serves 30 to 40 people.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind the cranberries, apples and oranges (leaving some of the orange peel on).
Mix sugar in the ground ingredients.
Let stand overnight before using.
Keep in refrigerator.
Especially good with roast turkey.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix beans, corn, onion and cheese.
Drain corn and beans.
Add sour cream and soup. Top with Ritz crackers. Pour butter over crackers.
Top with almonds. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Do not cover.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix brown sugar and pecans together. Sprinkle over bottom of pie crust.
Bake for 5 minutes.
Combine pumpkin, sugar, spice, eggs and milk together.
Pour over pecan mixture.
Combine oatmeal, margarine and sugar together.
Pour over pie filling.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: easy cream cheese fruit squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a medium saucepan, place 1/4 cup sugar and butter.
Heat until butter is melted, stirring occasionally.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs; press evenly in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In a large bowl with electric mixer, beat the cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in remaining sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla until well blended. Spoon pie filling evenly over crust.
Carefully pour cream cheese mixture over pie filling.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool. Chill until cold.
Cut into 24 squares.

title: jimmy's harborside famous fish balls
directions: Bring potatoes to a boil in water to cover them and cook until soft.
Rice or mash them and put aside.

title: meat dip
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger together in a skillet.
Add garlic powder, salt and 2 pounds of Velveeta.
Then add cream of mushroom soup and Ro-Tel.
Yum yum good!
Keep warm in crock-pot.

title: mom julie's applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mix soda with applesauce and add to sugar.
Mix spices with flour.
Use 1/2 cup flour to dust raisins and nuts.
Add flour to mixture and then add raisins and nuts. This will be very thick.
Grease tube pan.
Then line with wax paper.
Grease and flour wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: broccoli waldorf salad
directions: Mix together the orange juice concentrate, oil, sugar, vinegar, mustard and hot sauce.
Combine broccoli, apples, raisins and pecans in a small bowl.
Add dressing and toss.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: teriyaki meat sticks
directions: Slice steak diagonally into 2 x 1 x 1/4-inch strips.
Combine all the remaining ingredients; marinate meat slices for 30 minutes.
Thread slices on skewers.
Barbecue or broil until done. Makes 48.
(Also great with chicken strips!)

title: texas pasta salad
directions: Mix together 24 hours prior to serving.
Serves 8 or more.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients.

title: chicken 'n' rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter in a small pan.
When tender, stir in soup, milk, Tabasco sauce, chicken and rice.
Pour into a buttered 2-quart casserole and top with onion rings.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: rice krispies jumbles cookies
directions: Blend butter and sugar thoroughly. Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour and Rice Krispies. Drop by tablespoon onto greased baking sheets. Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes.
Yields about 6 dozen.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook first three ingredients until tender; do not drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat until ready to boil; serve.

title: rum ball
directions: Combine butter,
sugar	and
rum in double boiler; cook until well
blended,
stirring
constantly.
Dip cake cubes in mixture; roll in
mixture
of
crumbs
and
pecans.	Place in paper bonbon cups.
Store in airtight container in cool place; let ripen before serving.
Yield: 8 dozen.

title: welsh rarebit
directions: Heat all ingredients, except toast.
Pour about 1/3 cup sauce over each slice of toast.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let come to a boil. Turn heat down low and let cook about 5 minutes.

title: christmas eve mushroom soup
directions: Soak mushrooms overnight in medium size bowl filled with water. Next day, strain mushrooms from liquid and rinse them thoroughly to remove sand, etc.
Cut in small pieces.
Strain the remaining liquid through coffee filters several times to remove sand and mushroom remnants.
Fill 8-quart pan 3/4 full of water and add mushroom liquid.
Bring to a boil and turn down to simmer.
Add beef bouillon cubes (about 4 to 5).
Add onion, celery sticks, mushrooms and carrots.
In a metal tea strainer, add parsley flakes, caraway seed and peppercorns; close top and let steep in soup mixture while cooking.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
When done, remove celery sticks, carrots, onion and tea strainer.
Put in cooked Kluski noodles and serve.

title: pinto beans
directions: Sort and wash pinto beans.
Soak overnight in cold water.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Mix ham and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle ham, 4 ounces cheese and onion into pie shell.
Beat eggs and beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shell. Cook, uncovered, in a 425° oven for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Reduce oven to 300°. Cook, uncovered, about 30 minutes longer.
Insert knife in center of quiche.
If knife comes out clean, quiche is ready.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: orange scampi
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter and saute the garlic until brown.
Add the pepper and shrimp.
Toss gently and saute for 5 minutes over medium heat.
Remove the shrimp and set aside.
Pour off the butter.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first six ingredients and mold into ball.
Chill.
Roll in crushed walnuts and/or parsley flakes.
Makes 1 large ball or 2 small balls.

title: coconut tarts
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into shells and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Grease large skillet and sprinkle with meal.
Put on medium heat to heat skillet.
Mix the ingredients and bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown.

title: shrimp flambe
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Wrap each shrimp in bacon and fasten with toothpick.
Spread on a cookie sheet and bake, turning frequently, until bacon is crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Place in a chafing dish and pour warmed rum over shrimp; ignite.
Serve immediately.
Yields 12 servings.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine cheese, pepper, celery, pineapple, onion, 1/2 cup pecans, and salt.
Mix together and chill in bowl in refrigerator. Remove from fridge and form into ball and roll in remaining nuts. Can be used now or freeze.

title: striped fruit pops
directions: You will need 12 plastic cups or popsicle molds (3 ounces each) and 12 popsicle sticks.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Mix the cake mix using the lite recipe.
Put the nuts and coconut in a 9 x 12-inch pan; sprinkle coconut on top of the nuts. Pour the cake mix over the nuts and coconut mixture.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and melted butter together.
(Mixture will be thick.)
Drop the mixture into the cake mix; do not stir. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: dump cake
directions: Put all ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix by directions on box.
Mix other ingredients with cake mix.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes to 1 hour.

title: 25 pound lasagna
directions: Boil water in large pan for noodles.
Fry hamburger; drain grease.
Fry sausages.
Fry pepperoni in olive oil.
Slice sausages.
Mix meats together in a big bowl.
Add sauces, paste, spices and sugar.
Mix well.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Boil everything, except popped corn, for 5 minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon of soda.
Cook until it foams, then pour over popcorn. Mix well.
Bake well in 200° oven for 1 hour.

title: pasta salad
directions: Prepare "Pasta Accents" as directed on package.
Cool in fridge.
Add ingredients of your choosing, sliced, diced or chopped and serve with your favorite salad dressing (Ranch, Honey Dijon and Italian dressings are all excellent).

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, butter and milk in a large, heavy pan over medium heat.
Stir the mixture constantly until all ingredients melt. Continue cooking to soft ball stage, 235° on a candy thermometer.

title: jimmy cricket shake
directions: Put all ingredients into blender and blend well.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: This
is so easy the kids can even do it.
Just combine all the
ingredients
to the right consistency to form little balls and refrigerate.
I use about 3 cups of oats, about half a	jar of honey, half jar of peanut butter, and just a little powdered milk.
Try them, you'll like them.

title: venison or beef stew
directions: Cook meat with bay leaves until tender.
Add onion, potatoes, vegetables, tomato soup, tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Simmer on low heat for approximately 45 minutes.
Makes 8 or 10 servings.

title: ida belew's chocolate drop candy
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in a sauce pan.
Add milk gradually, then add melted butter.	Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.	Remove from heat.	Add peanut butter, oats, vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: raspberry-cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Combine flour and 3/4 cup sugar.
Cut in butter with pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup crumb mixture. Add baking powder and next 4 ingredients to remaining crumb mixture, blending well.
Spread mixture on bottom and 2 inches up sides of a greased and floured 10-inch spring-form pan.

title: surprise pie
directions: Layer fruit and bread.
Mix sugar, flour, butter and egg.
Pour over layers; sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix brown sugar, white Karo syrup and butter over medium heat together.
Heat only until it is mixed well.
Beat eggs and vanilla, then combine the sugar mixture.
Mix well; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 275° for 45 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: In a big bowl, mix flour and sugar together.
In a saucepan, mix next 4 ingredients; bring to a boil and pour over first mixture.
Mix well and add remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture into greased cookie sheet pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes (11 x 17-inch pan with sides).

title: brownie pound cake
directions: Soften margarine.
Add cake mix, flour, sugar, pudding mix and water.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 325° or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool 25 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Lay slices of bread in greased pan (large).
Sprinkle cooked, crumbled sausage over bread, then sprinkle cheese over sausage. Pour milk evenly over the cheese, then add beaten eggs.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 325° or until firm.
Uncover the last 5 minutes to brown.

title: century griddle cakes
directions: Measure and sift dry ingredients; beat eggs until light, then add milk.
Add dry ingredients to milk and eggs.
Beat thoroughly. Add melted butter.
Makes about 16 medium cakes.

title: banana pie supreme
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients to make cream filling.
In a prepared pie shell, add a layer of bananas, alternating with cream filling above.
Top with 1/2 cup whipped cream.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Cream butter; gradually beat in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in sweet potatoes and milk. Combine flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg; add to combined mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Stir in raisins and pecans.
Spoon in greased muffin pans filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: beef jerky
directions: Freeze brisket overnight.
Let it thaw a bit, then slice thinly against the grain. Mix the liquids and seasonings in a container and then add the strips of meat.
Shake or turn the container to coat all the strips thoroughly.
Marinate overnight. Put meat strips on a rack in the oven, set at its lowest temperature (warm for a gas oven, or lowest electric setting).
Be sure to use a drip pan or foil.
Check after about 5 hours of baking, but figure that it will take 6 or 7 hours to be completely done.
Take out before becoming too tough.

title: blueberry-cornmeal loaf cake
directions: Toss blueberries with 1 tablespoon flour and set aside.
Stir together remaining flour, cornmeal, baking powder and salt in mixing bowl.
Combine yogurt and lemon juice in another small bowl. Whisk together 2/3 cup sugar, oil and lemon zest in medium mixing bowl. Beat in eggs, beating well.
Alternately add dry ingredients and yogurt mixture, beginning and ending with dry ingredients. Mix until just combined.
Gently fold in blueberries. Spoon batter into lightly oiled 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Combine remaining 2 teaspoons sugar and cinnamon in small bowl and sprinkle over batter.

Bake at 350° until cake is golden and wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 50 to 60 minutes. After 20 minutes of baking, loosely cover pan with aluminum foil. Cool cake in pan on wire rack 10 minutes, then turn out onto rack and cool completely.

title: apple crisp
directions: Pare apples and slice thin.
Arrange slices in greased 8-inch round pan.
Combine oatmeal, sugar, flour and spices; cut in butter.
Sprinkle this mixture over apples.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with cheese wedges or whipped cream.

title: practically foolproof meringue
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites and salt until soft peaks form.
Gradually add Marshmallow Creme and beat until stiff peaks form.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: low-fat bran muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, baking powder, soda and cinnamon in large bowl.
Mix cereal, milk and brown sugar in another bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in egg and applesauce.
Add to flour mixture; stir just until moistened.
(Batter will be lumpy.)
Spoon batter into muffin pan sprayed with Pam, filling each cup 2/3 full. Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until golden.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 medium muffins.

title: no crust spinach sausage quiche
directions: About 1 hour before serving, preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Into 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, crumble turkey sausage.
Add oregano and onion.
Cook, stirring frequently, breaking up sausage with spoon until sausage is well browned and onion tender.
If sausage is dry during cooking, add 1 to 2 teaspoons salad oil.
Remove skillet from heat, stir in spinach and shredded cheese.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: About 1 hour before starting, spread 1 cup of the sour cream in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate together.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pie shell and bake in a 300° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate.
Top with chocolate flavored frozen whipped topping, thawed.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough 1/8-inch thick.
Arrange on pizza pan, overlapping slightly.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until golden.
Cool.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Drain and spread the pineapple chunks in the bottom of a 9-inch baking dish.
Save some juice for later.

title: cream of carrot soup
directions: *Can use bouillon cubes dissolved in the water used for boiling carrots.

title: belizean rice and beans
directions: Cook beans in water until tender.
Remove coconut from shell; rinse and grate.
Pour 1 1/2 cups warm water over grated coconut; mix and squeeze juice through sieve.
Repeat with 1 1/2 cups warm water.
Add milk and rice into 2 to 3-quart-sized pot.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring to boil and let simmer for about 1/2 hour.
Stir.
Cover and leave on turned-off stove for about 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in saucepan.
Add everything else. Pour into greased and floured pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: garden vegetable party pitas
directions: Split each pita bread round in half; cut each piece into 4 triangles.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes or until edges are lightly toasted.
Combine cheese, salad dressing, radishes and onions; mix lightly.
Spread onto bread; continue baking until cheese is melted.
Makes 16 appetizers.

title: braised green beans
directions: Place bacon, bacon drippings, butter, water and green beans in skillet.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover with lettuce leaf.
Put lid on skillet and cook on high heat for 1 minute.
Lower heat.
Cook until tender, 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove lettuce leaf and serve.

title: chocolate lovers delight truffle
directions: Make devil's food cake according to mix.
Then cool completely. Cut into cubes and set aside.
Make pudding with milk, set aside. Cut up all candy bars into tiny cubes and set aside.

title: grandma's tea cakes
directions: Soften	yeast in warm water.
Combine milk, shortening, sugar and
salt.	Sift
together	1 cup of flour and currants. Stir in milk
mixture.
Add
well beaten eggs.
Add yeast and remaining flour.
Mix
well.	Knead.	Put
into large greased bowl.
Brush top of dough with melted butter.
Cover; let rise until doubled in bulk.
Shape into small, round buns.
Put on greased pan.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Beat together 1 egg and
1/2 cup milk.
Brush on buns and sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake 40 minutes at 300°. Use Bundt pan.

title: ham glaze
directions: Heat slowly until smooth.
Spoon over ham the last 1/2 of baking.
May serve the remaining in a dish.

title: jello mold
directions: Stir Jell-O and hot water until dissolved.
Add mayonnaise and beat or whip well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold and chill until set.

title: colorful fruit bowl
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; chill.
Peel and section oranges and grapefruit, placing sections and juice that accumulate in a bowl.
Add remaining fruit, tossing gently.

title: rolled-up chicken breasts
directions: Flatten chicken breasts somewhat (do not pound).
Salt and pepper and place a pat of butter in them, with 1/2 teaspoon tarragon.
Roll up the breasts and freeze.
Dip frozen rolls in flour, then egg with 1 tablespoon water mixed, and again in flour and crumbs mixed together.
Brown in oil or Crisco.
Put breasts in baking dish.
Add to pan mushroom soup and sherry.
Stir and cook to boil.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: rolls
directions: Put
first 3 ingredients
in saucepan and let come to a rolling boil.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup of water.
Add to cooled milk mixture.
Add enough flour to make soft batter.
Set in warm, draft-free place to rise until double, approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: sunshine fizz
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in container of electric blender; process until smooth.
Stir in club soda and pour into soda glasses.
Add a scoop of orange sherbet to each glass and garnish, if desired.
Serve immediately.
Yields 3 servings.

title: baked chicken
directions: Soak chicken breasts in milk and egg mixture.
Mix all ingredients together.
Coat chicken in mixture; place in baking dish.
Pour 1/2 stick oleo over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Real good.

title: italian pork chops in crock-pot
directions: Brown pork chops in 1 tablespoon oil.
In bottom of crock-pot cut up onion, green pepper, garlic and mushrooms.
Place pork chops on top of mixture.
In small bowl mix tomato sauce, lemon juice and remaining ingredients; pour over pork chops.
Put on low setting for 7 to 9 hours.
Serve hot with side dish of pasta and salad.

title: easy peanut butter cookie
directions: Beat the egg, add the sugar then peanut butter.
Beat together thoroughly.
Cool batter in the refrigerator, then make into balls and place on a cookie sheet.
Press down with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: peas 'n rice
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Add green pepper and onion to the pan and cook until onion is clear.
Add water, peas, tomato paste, salt, black pepper, paprika, thyme and rice.
Cover the pot with a tight fitting lid and simmer until all of the water has been absorbed.

title: old-fashioned chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugars.
Add beaten egg, water and vanilla; mix well.
Pour in flour and stir.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Grease 2 cookie sheets.
Place dough about 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes or until desired brownness.
Dough will be soft.
Let set in pan until firm, then remove.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: poppy seed filling(for nut roll or cookies)
directions: Boil milk; add poppy seed, honey and sweet cream.
Cook until thick, about 5 to 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add beaten egg.

title: aunt mee mee's sherry cake
directions: Mix together and pour into a Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes
or until done with toothpick test.
If toothpick comes out clean, it's done.
Remove from pan and sift powdered sugar on top.
Serves 8.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: In skillet saute onions and celery in the margarine until tender (about 5 minutes). In large bowl combine bread cubes, corn bread, sage, poultry seasoning, salt, pepper, and sauteed vegetables.
Mix well.
Add eggs, broth and milk.
Toss to mix. Spoon into 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30-40 minutes.

title: chocolate caramel brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, melted margarine and 1/3 cup evaporated milk, beat with mixer for 2 minutes.
Spread 1/2 cake batter in 13x9 pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Then melt caramels and other 1/3 cup milk over low heat.
I use double boiler.
Mix until caramels are completely melted and smooth.
Pour over baked cake. Spread chocolate chips and 1/2 of nuts over baked batter.
Then mix other half of nuts in remaining batter and drop by spoonfuls over chocolate chips.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 350°

title: apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil and sugar.
Blend well.
Sift in flour and mix well.
Add vanilla, chopped apples and nuts.
Blend and pour into a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix sugar, salt and flour.
Add melted margarine; then eggs and milk.
Then add corn; stir well.
Pour into a glass (Wesson oiled) baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven (preheated) for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, lemon juice and salt.
Grease casserole dish.
Layer the casserole in this manner: 1/2 sliced artichokes, spinach, cheese mixture.
Repeat.
Top with cracker crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Use 1/3 cup mix to 1 cup of water.
Makes 50 servings.

title: snowballs
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and milk in large bowl.
Gently stir in Cool Whip.
Hold cupcakes, top side down, in palm of hand. Spread Cool Whip on bottom and sides.
Press coconut onto frosting.

title: chinese rice
directions: Simmer soup in 1 quart boiling water for 10 minutes.
Pour over first ingredients and mix.
Put in casserole.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes at 350°.

title: queen elizabeth's chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Season chicken with salt and pepper. Top each with 1 teaspoon parsley, 1 slice cheese, 1 slice ham. Roll tightly and brush with butter and roll in crumbs.
Arrange compactly seam side down in square baking dish.
Pour remaining butter on top and sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Cover and bake 45 minutes.
Remove cover and bake until golden, about 30 minutes.

title: great peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar and milk to a boil on medium-high heat.
Turn down to low and simmer for about 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and beat in peanut butter until thick.
Pour into a buttered 8 x 8-inch pan and put in freezer for about 20 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix well.
Put in refrigerator to firm for handling.
Form ball and roll in 1 cup finely chopped pecans.

title: swiss spinach
directions: Saute onion in margarine until golden.
Add flour and garlic powder; cook at low heat for 1 minute.
Add milk, salt and pepper; cook at low heat until thickened.
Add cheese and cook until smooth.
Add spinach.
Put in greased casserole.
Cook at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: glorified brownies
directions: Melt margarine with cocoa.
Mix sugar and flour.
Add flour and sugar to margarine and cocoa mixture.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: baked salmon croquettes
directions: Drain liquid from salmon into measuring cup and add milk to make the one cup liquid.
Melt butter.
Add onions to butter and tenderize (not brown).
Blend into this flour, salt and Tabasco. Add milk liquid and cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Flake salmon and add to sauce along with lemon juice.
Stir in 1/2 cup crushed corn flakes.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Divide into 8 or 10 portions and shape into cones.
Roll in the remaining corn flakes to coat.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Also you can make these into flat patties and fry in a skillet.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Cook for 35 minutes at 325°.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Blend all together.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
