Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
If double the recipe, add 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: bran muffins
directions: In a medium bowl, soak the cereal in boiling water.
Set aside to cool, then stir in the buttermilk.
In a large mixing bowl, beat the oil, sugar and eggs until well blended.
Mix in the bran-buttermilk mixture.
Sift or stir together the dry ingredients.
Add dry mixture to the bran mixture, stirring just enough to combine.
Add raisins or other fruit, if desired. Either refrigerate the batter in tightly closed container for later use (up to 3 weeks) or divide among 24 muffin cups, filling each cup about 2/3 full.
Bake the muffins in a preheated 400° oven for 15 to 18 minutes.
Remove muffins to a rack.
Cool to warm (they are best when eaten warm).

title: flank steak
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over steak.
Marinate overnight.
When ready to use, broil until tender.

title: bart and cherry's zippy beef "wiches"(tailgate party treat)
directions: Combine sauce mix, milk, horseradish and mustard, beating briskly until smooth.
Stir in beef and mushrooms; chill at least 10 minutes to blend flavors.
Serve on rolls with lettuce and onion.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Crust:
Mix together graham cracker crumbs and margarine. Line pan (9 x 13-inch) with crumb mix; press down.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: coffee breeze
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring, until sugar is dissolved. Remove from heat.
Let stand until cool. Combine milk mixture, coffee, vanilla and 1 cup whipping cream. Pour mixture into loaf pan. Freeze until slush, about 1 to 2 hours.
Beat cream until stiff. Stir slush mixture. Spoon into dessert dishes. Top with whipped cream.
Makes 12 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: no fail dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll thin and cut into small squares. Let dry 1 or 2 hours.
Drop in boiling broth.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Do not remove lid during cooking.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In an iron skillet, cook sugar, water and Karo syrup until it strings from spoon.
Add margarine, vanilla and peanuts.
Cook until the peanuts are done.
Add soda; mix and pour into a buttered cookie sheet.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Drain all fruits and put in salad dish.
Mix in marshmallows and coconut.
Save small amount of coconut to put on top.
Mix everything with sour cream.
Sprinkle with remaining coconut.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except 1/4 cup cracker crumbs. Put in greased casserole (I use Pam to grease).
Cover with 1/4 cup cracker crumbs.
Dot with oleo and cook at 350° until brown, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: ham and macaroni casserole
directions: Prepare boxed macaroni according to package directions, including adding the cheese. Combine chopped ham. Add 1/2 cup water. Let simmer for 10 minutes. Add sweet peas; simmer 10 more minutes. Serves 4.

title: easy dirty rice
directions: Brown ground meat.
Remove from pan and use small amount of fat to brown onions and bell pepper.
Add mushroom gravy, 1 can water and ground meat.
Let cook for about 20 minutes.
Add to cooked rice; serve warm.

title: italian tomato sauce
directions: Brown garlic in oil; add rest of ingredients except pasta and Italian cheese.
Simmer after it comes to a boil for 1 hour.
Cook ziti or spaghetti and put sauce on top with Italian cheese.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon together. Mix oatmeal, buttermilk and brown sugar together.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add eggs and oil.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients to oatmeal mixture just to moisten.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Makes 10 muffins.

title: country chicken 'n' biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a greased 8 x 16-inch baking dish, combine bacon, chicken, vegetables, tomatoes and 1 cup cheese. Blend soup and milk.
Pour over casserole and bake, covered, at 400° for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine biscuit mix, 2/3 cup milk and 1/2 can of French fried onions.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls to form 6 biscuits around edge of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.
Top with remaining cheese and onions and bake about 2 to 3 minutes or until onions are toasted.

title: potato deluxe
directions: Thaw the potatoes for 30 minutes.
Mix with remaining ingredients except corn flakes.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole. Top with corn flakes and bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: potato chip chicken
directions: Melt butter in pan and add garlic salt. While hot, put into a deep bowl. In another bowl, mash the potato chips until very small pieces. Dip chicken in butter first and then roll in potato chips. Place in a shallow baking dish. Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until done.

title: plantation pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: barbecue ham
directions: Mix chili sauce, brown sugar, vinegar and mustard together. Cut up ham into small pieces and add to sauce.
Heat and serve hot on buns.

title: angel food surprise
directions: Tear up angel food cake into bite-size pieces.
Mix with Cool Whip until cake is well coated.
Put Thank You pie filling into jello mold or Bundt pan.
Then put cake mixture on top of filling. Pack down lightly.
Then freeze.
About 1 hour before serving, take out of mold and put on plate with cherries on top.
Serve slightly frozen.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, creaming until light and fluffy.
Beat for 10 minutes on electric mixer or longer by hand. Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time to creamed mixture, beating well after each addition.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk and flavorings, beating after each addition until smooth.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured pans.
Use 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add remaining ingredients as listed.
Grease muffin tins.
Fill about half full with batter. Bake in a 425° oven for about 20 minutes.
(Can be put in refrigerator and used as needed.
Dough keeps well.)

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together. Put in buttered casserole dish. Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes.

title: meal in one baked potatoes
directions: Rinse and dry potatoes. Prick once with fork. Arrange in a circle on paper towels in microwave. Cook on High 12 to 14 minutes, rearranging once. Let potatoes cool to touch. Slice away top of each potato and carefully scoop out pulp, leaving shells whole. Mash pulp. Place margarine in bowl and cook on High 30 to 45 seconds until melted. Combine margarine, mashed potato, ham, cheese, sour cream, salt and pepper. Mix well and stuff into potato shells. Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes until heated through, giving dish one-half turn during cooking time.

title: enchilada sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender.
Fill rest of blender with water and blend.

title: soft ginger cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together well.
Set aside.
Sift together spices, salt and 7 cups of the flour.
Dissolve baking soda in boiling water.
Add water mixture alternately with flour mixture to the sugar and molasses and combine well.
Dough will be thick.
Turn onto a floured board and knead in more flour if dough is sticky.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness and cut into rounds or desired shapes.
Bake in a 375° oven on greased cookie sheets for 9 to 10 minutes.
Makes 6 or 7 dozen cookies, depending on size of cookie cutter.

title: tuna broccoli cups
directions: Grease 12 muffin pan cups.
Cook broccoli as directed on package and drain.
Pat dry with paper towels.
Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Drop dough by spoonful into muffin cups.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Spread in baking pan (13 x 9-inch) the washed rice.
On this, lay the chicken pieces.
Over this, pour the cream of celery and mushroom soups.
Spread over this the dry onion soup mix.
Pour over the top of this the white wine.
Seal pan tightly with double thickness of aluminum foil.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: molasses  crispy cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix all ingredients together. Roll into small balls.
Place cookies on a cookie sheet and bake nine minutes.

title: microwave vegetable-cheese soup
directions: In 2-quart casserole, combine vegetables with water.
Cook according to package microwave directions.
Stir in the milk, bouillon granules, dry mustard, oregano and Worcestershire sauce. Cook, uncovered, for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: raisin rice pudding
directions: Mix rice with 2 cups of the milk in top of double boiler; cook over hot water until tender.
Add raisins and butter.
Combine eggs, sugar, vanilla, salt and remaining milk.
Stir into rice mixture.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: palmer's special fruit salad
directions: Combine apples and grapes in bowl.
Top with lemon juice.
In microwavable bowl, heat honey and jam 1 minute on High.
Pour over fruit; add cinnamon and toss.
Refrigerate.
Serve plain or top with whipped cream or yogurt.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 1 tablespoon syrup.
Drain oranges. Combine all ingredients except pecans with the 1 tablespoon reserved syrup.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Sprinkle with pecans and serve.

title: cheddar cheese meatballs
directions: Mix onion with hamburger meat.
Shape into balls.
Fry them in frypan.
Drain off excess grease.
Mix cheese soup with water. Pour into baking dish and place the meatballs in mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: champagne fruit salad
directions: Whip cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Add strawberries, pineapple, bananas and pecans.
Pour into bowl or rectangular dish.
Top with whipped topping.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: joel's mother's great date nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add beaten egg yolks, then sifted flour with dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and lemon juice.
Dredge chopped pineapple (not in small pieces) and cherries (cut up in large pieces, if cut at all).
Add with nuts.
Lastly, add beaten egg whites.
Put in normally large tube pan (greased, waxed paper in bottom).
Bake 3 hours at 250°.
Freezes well.

title: saucy-cheesy meatloaf
directions: Prepare your favorite meatloaf.
Instead of making into a loaf, spread out meatloaf mixture onto a piece of wax paper so that it will form into a flat 1 inch high rectangle.
Spread tomato sauce on the surface of rectangle as if you were frosting it.
Next sprinkle cheese on top of sauce, then chopped green peppers.
Roll meatloaf into a roll (like a jelly roll), seal the edges and place in a regular loaf pan.
Bake at 350° until done. This recipe (sauce & cheese) will make enough for a standard loaf pan.
If your recipe is larger, than double the sauce & cheese. When baking, you may have to drain more liquid.

title: deep south pie
directions: Cook rice until very soft (at least twice as long as customary).
Drain and mash with a fork.
Melt butter in a large saucepan.
Stir in molasses, sugar, eggs, salt, vanilla and rice; pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle pecans evenly over the top.
Bake in a moderate oven (375°) for 50 minutes.
Cool before serving. Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: crystal pickles
directions: Wash
cucumbers and put in stone jar.
Make brine of coarse salt and 1 gallon water.
Heat until salt has dissolved; do not boil.
Weight down with plate.
Leave 2 weeks.
Skim if needed. Drain and wash.
Slice or chunk as desired and cover with cold water to which powdered alum has been added.
Let stand 24 hours. Drain and wash.
Make syrup of vinegar, sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Put in bag.
Bring syrup to boil.
Pour over cucumbers. Heat syrup for 4 days.
On the 4th day, put pickles in cans and seal.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Take jello and mix with boiling water; add frozen strawberries. Stir until berries and jello are thick. Add pineapple, then bananas. Put half of mixture in pan and spread sour cream over after jelled. Then add other half.

title: old german sauerbraten
directions: Combine vinegar, water, onion and seasonings; bring to boil. Place meat in large bowl; pour hot mixture over meat.
Cover bowl and marinate for 2 to 4 days (depending on the sourness desired). Put in refrigerator, turning several times.
Remove meat; strain and save sauce.
Rub well with seasoned flour; brown on all sides in shortening.
Add marinade liquid to depth of 1/2-inch.
Bring to boiling point; reduce heat and simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Take all leftover liquid, restrain and take 1 cup or more crushed ginger snaps and add to liquid.
Stir until thickened.
You may need to add more water.
Should make about 2 cups of gravy.
Serve with mashed potatoes, red cabbage and biscuits.
You can add biscuit mix into gravy to make dumplings.

title: frosted pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco; add pumpkin and 1 egg.
Combine flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix into creamed mixture.
Stir in butterscotch bits, nuts and raisins.
Spoon onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: more-more
directions: Cook noodles; brown hamburg.
Combine all ingredients together, except cheese, and pour into casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs.
Add flour and cream of tartar.
Chill for 1 hour. Roll into balls.
Dip the balls into a mixture of cinnamon and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Place on cookie sheet and bake for 8 to 10 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: real maryland crab cakes
directions: Pick shells out of crab meat.
Toss bread crumbs gently into crab meat.
Mix rest of ingredients and gently mix into crab meat mixture.
Form into 6 cakes. Roll each cake into cracker crumbs. Refrigerate for 1 hour (if there is time).
Deep fry at 350° until golden brown (2 to 3 minutes).

title: pink jello salad
directions: Mix jello (dry) and pineapple with juice in a pot and bring to a boil.
Set this pot in cool water until mixture is cool.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place in a jello mold and chill until set.
Can be frozen ahead of time, then thawed.

title: st. louis fanatical barbecue
directions: Smoke pork steaks with indirect heat hickory smoke for 6 to 8 hours.
Put 1/2-inch barbecue sauce on the bottom of a roasting pan.
Put a couple of steaks on the sauce in the pan.
Pour a little sauce on top, then add more steaks.
Add more sauce and more steaks on top of that.
When all of your pork is in the roaster, pour the rest of the sauce over the meat until the pan is about 2/3 full.
Cover the pan, then bake at 300° for 3 hours. Sear steak on barbecue for just a minute or two on each side.
Be careful!
The meat is so tender it can fall through the grill.
If the meat is too tender, just skip the searing.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cornmeal and salt; mix well.
Add butter and milk, mixing well.
Add lemon juice, lemon rind and eggs; beat well.
Broil unbaked pie shell 1 minute.
Remove from oven and pour in filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until slightly firm in the center.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and take off bone; put chicken in baking dish and cover with chips.

Put chicken soup, mushroom soup, cheese and milk in pot and heat on low fire until all is melted, then pour over chicken and chips and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until well heated and brown on top.
(You can also layer in deep pan if you make for a large crowd; just double recipe.)

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place rice in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Arrange pork chops on top of rice and sprinkle dry Lipton onion soup on top of chops.
Add 3 cups water on top of this.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Boil noodles in salted water.
While noodles are boiling, melt margarine in small pan over low to medium heat.
When margarine is completely melted, add whipping cream, nutmeg and black pepper. Bring mixture to low boil.
Drain noodles and add sauce mixture. Add Parmesan cheese.
Mix thoroughly and serve.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Cut chicken wings in half (at joint) and discard wing tips. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Fry wings (6 to 8 at a time) in hot peanut oil (375°) for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain well on paper towels.

title: patricia's coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour and add 1/2 cup of milk.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks and rest of milk.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Stir and cook slowly and mix well so it will not be lumpy. Remove from heat and add butter, coconut and vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: twisted cheese loaf
directions: You will need two medium 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 loaf baking pans, greased or Teflon.
Reduce heat 25° if glass pans are used.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In a sauce pan put margarine, sugar, milk and cocoa.
Bring to boil and boil for 1 minutes.
Take off stove.
Add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until well blended.
Drop on cookie sheet or wax paper.

title: s'more puddin' dessert
directions: Line bottom of an 8 x 6 x 2-inch glass or metal baking dish with 3 honey graham crackers.
In medium saucepan, combine milk and pudding mix.
Cook over low heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Cool 5 minutes.
Spread half of the pudding over crackers; top with second layer of crackers.
Place candy bars on crackers. Spread remaining pudding over candy bars; top with third layer of crackers.
Sprinkle with marshmallows; broil until golden brown, about 2 to 4 minutes.
Serve warm or chill in refrigerator.

title: irish cream liqueur
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender until smooth.
Store in refrigerator.
Keeps 1 month if it lasts that long.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, salt and add melted butter along with tap water.
In separate bowl, mix 1 package yeast with 2 cups flour. Add to liquid and beat with mixer until stiff.
Add remaining 2 1/2 cups flour.
Place in greased bowl and cover top with oil or thin film of butter.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight. When ready for use, divide into 3 parts; cut into circle.
Brush with melted butter and cut into 12 wedges.
Roll each wedge, starting with wide side.
Let rise on greased cookie sheet for 4 hours.
Bake at 375° until brown.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: california chicken
directions: Sprinkle soup mix over bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle rice evenly over dry soup mix.
Place chicken on top.
Dilute mushroom soup with water or chicken broth and pour over chicken.
Dot with butter and bake, uncovered, in preheated oven for 1 hour at 325°.

title: white cake
directions: Cream
shortening
and sugar.
Measure and sift all dry ingredients; mix alternately with shortening and sugar and the first 3/4
cup of milk.
When this is blended, add vanilla and remaining 1/4 cup milk.
Beat egg whites until very stiff; add remaining 1/2
cup	of
sugar and fold into batter.
Bake as a layer cake	or
a
sheet cake.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes. Cool and frost with your favorite frosting.

title: hickory nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
This should be very fluffy for fine texture.
Add the dry ingredients alternating with milk all but about 1/2 cup.
Mix nuts in remaining dry ingredients and fold into batter.
Add flavoring and fold in beaten egg whites. Generously grease and flour 2 (8 1/2-inch) cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool layers for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Saute green pepper, mushrooms, celery and onion.
Add mushroom soup.
Add Velveeta cheese and Colby cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until it bubbles.

title: spicy pot roast
directions: Heat olive oil in a large Dutch oven; add pot roast and brown on all sides.
Add tomato sauce, 1/2 cup wine, orange peel, cloves, cinnamon sticks and garlic.
Cover and bake at 300° for 2 to 3 hours.
Add remaining ingredients; cover and cook 1 hour longer or until meat is tender.
Remove meat to a warm platter and let stand for 15 minutes before slicing.
Skim grease from pan juices and serve as a sauce over meat slices.

title: old fashion egg custard
directions: Bake pie shells. Set aside. Separate eggs. Set whites aside. Put egg yolks, 1 cup milk, butter, sugar and vanilla in a saucepan and mix well. Cook on medium heat on top of stove. Bring to a boil. Mix flour and 1 cup milk and pour into mixture on stove. Cook until thick. Pour into pie shells.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix margarine, sugar and vanilla together.
Add potato chips and stir in flour.
Form balls with mixture and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press balls flat with the bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 16 to 18 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash for 10 minutes, then drain water.
Mix other ingredients together.
Add squash to mixture and bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Sprinkle dressing on top.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruit with can of peach pie filling.
Coat well with filling.
Yummy; keeps well for several days.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until just tender.
(I use microwave.) Arrange stalks in greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Place chopped cooked chicken on top of broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour this over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese. Combine dressing with butter and sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender; drain and mash.
Mix with 1 1/2 cups of crumbs, onion, sugar, eggs, cheese, seasoning and 1/2 of melted oleo.

title: squash
directions: Fry some bacon in a skillet until brown, then add cut up squash.
Add some water until skillet is half full.
Then add minced onions and cover.
Turn heat down low and simmer until squash is tender.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish and bake at 375°
for 60 minutes.
Stir 3 times during baking.
Add about 1 tablespoon vanilla when cool.

title: milk chocolate torte
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In small mixer bowl, chill frosting mix (dry) and whipping cream 1 hour.
Grease and flour jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely.

title: wet bottom shoo-fly
directions: Mix well the flour, brown sugar and Crisco.
Save half cup crumb mixture for top.

title: lafayette's onion pie
directions: Cook bacon until crisp and drain.
Saute onions in butter over medium heat until soft and translucent, stirring constantly.
Beat eggs and combine with onions, sour cream, sweet cream, chives, salt and pepper.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour filling mixture into pie crust in pan. Crumble bacon on top.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until crust is golden brown and custard sets so that the tip of a knife inserted into it comes out clean.
Serve hot or cold.

title: corn casserole
directions: Stir ingredients together well and bake in 2-quart dish at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cajun spiced chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl except chicken and olive oil.
Dredge the chicken into the seasoning until well coated.
Heat oil over medium heat.
Cook chicken about 4 minutes per side or until lightly browned.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream butter in a large mixing bowl.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add honey; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: chili baked corn
directions: Saute onion in 1 tablespoon of butter.
Mix together 1/2 cup of the cheese, 4 tablespoons of the cracker crumbs, half and half cream, chilies, seasoning salt and corn.
Turn into greased 1-quart baking dish.
Melt remaining butter and mix together remaining cheese and cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle on top of the corn mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375°
for approximately 30 minutes.

title: rice pilaf(serves 6)
directions: Melt butter; saute onion.
Add everything else.
Put in casserole dish and cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet-n-sour chicken
directions: Drain pineapple; set aside juice.
Cut chicken breasts into chunks.
Cook in butter.
Add bouillon and carrots.
Cover and cook until tender.
Combine pineapple juice, brown sugar, cornstarch, vinegar and soy sauce.
Add to chicken.
Add vegetables; cook until tender.
Serve over rice.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and mix all ingredients well.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and pour into 2 graham cracker pie shells.

title: frozen salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Put in Pyrex dish and freeze.

title: amaretto cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese, butter, cream cheese, raisins and amaretto. Shape into ball and roll in nuts.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together the Crisco, white sugar and brown sugar.
Add peanut butter, salt, flour, egg, milk and vanilla.
Mix well. Roll into size of walnuts and flatten with fork dipped in flour. Bake at 425° for 7 or 8 minutes or until brown.

title: baked chicken parmesan
directions: Combine crumbs and cheese.
Brush chicken with salad dressing and coat with crumb mixture.
Place in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken wings with honey orange sauce
directions: Cut tips off wings.
Cut wings in half at joint.
In a 13 x 9-inch microwave baking dish, blend remaining ingredients. Add wings and turn to coat.
Microwave, uncovered, on High 20 minutes, turning and basting during cooking time.
Microwaves vary so make certain chicken is cooked through. Sauce should be thick.

title: snow ghost chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients
in
a
medium saucepan.
Add milk. Cook over medium heat stirring constantly until mixture boils. Boil one minute.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla. Pour into pie
shell.
Place	plastic
wrap
directly
on top. Chill. Remove plastic wrap and decorate with whipped cream.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Peel the lemon of the white pulp; cut up lemon minus the seeds and put all in blender container.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar, cocoa, and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Add flour, coconut, and nuts.
Bake in a greased 9 X 13 pan for 40 minutes.
Spread marshmallow creme on top.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar and Eagle Brand milk together. Add to the other ingredients and refrigerate.
Will keep several days.

title: noodle surprise
directions: Brown and cook the meat; add salt and pepper.
Add the onions, celery and green pepper; cook all well into meat.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Combine all ingredients and place in casserole.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Heat for 1 hour in slow oven.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cheesy apple pie
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together flour and salt.
Cut in the shortening to the size of small peas.
Stir in the cheese. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of the water over the mixture; toss with a fork.
Repeat until all is moistened. Form into a ball.

title: chicken nachos
directions: In saucepan, mix soup, salsa and chicken.
Over low heat, heat through, stirring occasionally.
Serve over chips.
Top with onions and olives.
Serves 6.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Blend Cool Whip and cream cheese in a deep bowl until smooth. Add juice of lemon and mix just until mixture starts to thicken. Spoon into pie crust and cover with topping.
Chill approximately 1/2 hour.

title: sour cream spice cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, brown sugar, white sugar, egg and sour cream. Sift together flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves. Combine with dates, raisins, nuts or citron. Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; cool.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: angolan chicken(galirhamuamba)
directions: Combine chilies, ginger, oil, garlic, onions, salt, pepper, lemon juice, 1 cup water and oil; mix well.
Place chicken pieces in mix and marinate at room temperature for 3 hours.
Remove chicken and pat dry.
Strain and reserve liquid and any solids. Brown chicken in remaining oil; add more oil if needed.
Add solids from marinade and cook until onions are soft but not brown. Return chicken to pan and add 1/2 cup of the marinade and 1 cup water.
Simmer 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.
Serve with saffron rice.

title: curried honey chicken
directions: Blend well salt, curry powder, mustard, honey and margarine. Use mixture to coat chicken.
Chicken can be skinned if you wish. Place chicken in roasting pan and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Baste with pan drippings.

title: *quick fruit squares
directions: Mix margarine with beaten egg; add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, using fork.
Mix well, but leave crumbly.
Divide batter into 2 portions.
Using a 9 x 12-inch pan, place half of the batter on the bottom; spread evenly.
Pour fruit filling over batter.
Spread remaining batter on top.
Sprinkle top of batter with a mixture of the brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed.
Prepare soup with 1/2 can of water and 1/2 can of milk.
Mix first 5 ingredients.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top of mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown ground beef; add onion and green pepper.
Saute until vegetables are tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for one hour.
Add 1/4 cup meat sauce to one half of an English muffin. Serving size 1/2 English muffin.
Carbohydrate 19 g, protein 9 g, fat 5 g, calories 157.
One serving = 1 meat medium fat exchange, 1 bread starch exchange, 1/2 fruit exchange.

title: pasta-e-tasule
directions: In saucepan, put olive oil and saute chopped onion, but do not brown.
Add parsley, tomato sauce, water, salt and pepper. Let simmer for 1 hour.
Then add beans and let simmer 10 minutes longer.
Cook macaroni in 1-inch lengths or elbow macaroni in boiling, salted water.
Drain and add to first mixture
Serves 6.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and pour into pie shell. Refrigerate.
Mix together pudding mix, Jell-O and water.
Put in microwave and heat.
Stir 2 times; bring to a boil.
Remove and cool well.
Add the strawberries.
Pour over cream cheese in pie shell and cool.
Spread Cool Whip on top.

title: vegetarian vegetable soup
directions: Saute the onion, celery and bell pepper in the olive oil in a large Dutch oven.
Add the other ingredients and simmer until softened.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: In oblong pan, pour and spread the pie filling.
Drain pineapple and spread over pie filling.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over mixture.
Slice margarine in thin slices and drop over the top of the cake mix.
Sprinkle pecans over top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until mixture starts to bubble and turns brown on top.
Serve warm.

title: hash and eggs for brunch
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in melted butter until tender. Stir in hash, bread crumbs, pimiento and salt.
Heat until mixture leaves side of pan. Spread evenly in bottom of buttered 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: pumpkin pie dessert
directions: Mix together eggs, pumpkin, sugar, pumpkin pie spice, salt and evaporated milk.
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix over filling;
pour melted butter over top. Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, or until knife comes out clean.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: In a large pan, melt margarine with hot water.
Add brown sugar and beat well with spoon.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add sugar mixture.
Stir in zucchini and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased and floured.
Sprinkle with butterscotch bits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: texas cobbler
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer rest of ingredients in order given.
Top with other stick of margarine which has been melted.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour, until golden brown on top.

title: spanish beans
directions: Brown hamburger with onion. Mix with other ingredients. Bake in a slow oven.
Add a little salt and pepper.

title: barley and green pea salad
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, bring water and bouillon to boil over high heat.
Stir in barley.
Cover; reduce heat to low.
Simmer 40 to 45 minutes until water is absorbed and barley is tender but firm.

title: granny's pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening, and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine dry ingredients; add dry ingredients and milk alternately to creamed mixture beating after each addition.
Add flavoring and mace.
Spoon batter into a greased and waxed paper-lined 10 inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat, and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool.
Remove from pan.

title: shrimp or crawfish jambalaya
directions: Cook rice separately.
Melt butter and add onions, celery, bell pepper and garlic in heavy pot.
Cook uncovered over medium heat until onions wilt.
Add tomato paste and cook stirring constantly for about 15 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 cups water.
Season to taste.
Add sugar and cook uncovered over medium heat for 40 minutes, stirring constantly until oil floats to top.
Add shrimp and continue cooking for 20 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1/2 cup water and add.
Cook another 5 minutes.
Mix ingredients with cooked rice. Add green onion tops and parsley.
Mix again.
Serves 8 generously.

title: hellfire and damnation chicken wings(not for the faint of heart!)
directions: Peel garlic and bruise severely.
Chop garlic finely.
Blend with remaining ingredients except chicken and rice, to an odd reddish color.
Add water to taste.
Spread chicken wings in a baking dish and cover with sauce.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve with prepared white rice.
The vinegar, sugar and rice will help cut the "heat" of the wings.
Serves 12.

title: manicotti
directions: Mix with spoon.
Fill uncooked manicotti shells.
Then put sauce in bottom of pan.
Put in dish.
Then add rest of sauce.
Put cheese over top.
Cover dish with Reynolds Wrap.
Use an 8 1/2 x 13 1/2-inch dish.
I use a long dish.
You will have two rows of manicotti.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: 10x sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients; chill for 1/2 hour.
Mixture will be stiff. Roll out and bake (thin).
Used for holidays in cutout designs.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Spread bananas over crust.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over bananas.
Add crushed pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple, then 1/2 cup coconut and then 1/2 cup chopped nuts and cherries.

title: ham steak oven dish
directions: Trim ends and fat from ham steak; cut into serving size pieces.
Place ham steak in 9 x 13 x 2 inch baking dish or sheet pan.
For easier clean-up, line with aluminum foil.
Core apples and cut into halves.
Mix brown sugar and butter for apples; fill openings and place at ends of the pan.
In a small saucepan mix cranberry sauce, brown sugar for sauce, and juice together.
Heat until boiling; reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour hot sauce over ham and apples.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes, turning apples and ham once and spooning sauce over them. Transfer to platter or serve from pan.
The sauce can be served as a side dish, if desired.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Combine cream cheese and soup mix; mix well.
Spread mixture on a slice of ham, then roll up lengthwise.
Refrigerate until firm.
Slice into 4 pieces and put a toothpick in each piece.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugars, oleo and vanilla.
Add eggs and dry ingredients. Stir until moistened.
Form into patties the size of silver dollars and 1/2-inch thick.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and press with a fork.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen large cookies (3-inch diameter).

title: green onion cheese ball
directions: Chop up green onion and dried beef.
Mix well with other ingredients.
Shape into ball.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown meat.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, seasoning mix, water and pepper; simmer 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in onion.
Place rounded tablespoon of meat filling and cheese on each tortilla.
(If using corn tortillas, fry in oil a few seconds so they are easier to work with.)
Roll up tightly.
Place seam down in 12 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lima bean delight
directions: Combine lima beans, croutons and soup.
Mix together.
Place in greased casserole with the 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: mexican chef salad
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Drain and rinse red beans.
Add beans to meat; set aside.
Break up lettuce, cut up tomatoes, grate cheese and crunch up Doritos.
Just before serving, heat meat and beans.
Add to salad mix; toss with Thousand Island dressing.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, cinnamon, allspice and cloves.
Bring to a boil. Add peaches, a few at a time, until transparent.
Have jars ready.
Pack peaches in jars. Cover with syrup.

title: charlie bread(mouth-watering southern corn bread)
directions: Blend and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: potato puffs
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Form into balls. Roll in fine bread crumbs.
Fry at 375°.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Serve piping hot.
Serves 4.

title: almond butter toffee
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet over medium heat.
Add sugar and stir until smooth.
Continue stirring until butter separates (about 5 minutes).
Add almonds and continue stirring until butter blends back into mixture (about 8 minutes).
Pour in ungreased cookie sheet 1/4-inch thick.
When still warm, place chocolate bars on top to melt.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: corned beef pasties
directions: In a bowl, combine corned beef, pineapple, cheese and horseradish. On a lightly floured surface, roll each biscuit into a 5-inch circle. Place about 1/4 cup corned beef mixture on half a biscuit, leaving an edge of pastry for sealing; fold in half. Seal edges with tines of fork. Prick tops. Place on baking sheet; let stand 15 minutes. Bake in preheated 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Yield: 10 pasties.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Mix chicken with soups, sour cream, almonds and poppy seed.
Melt oleo and crumble crackers, then mix together until all oleo is gone.
Put chicken mixture in a casserole dish, then sprinkle the crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° until set.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Bake empty pie shell according to directions.
Combine milk, cornstarch, sugar, well beaten egg yolks, butter and cocoa.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick. Pour into pastry shell.

title: fried pies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pie filling. Roll out and cut into circles. Fill with pie filling, then seal dough and deep-fry in Creamtex.

title: chocolate chip sour cream cake
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon together.
Cream butter and 1 cup sugar together.
Beat in eggs until fluffy.
Sift together flour and baking soda.
Mix together sour cream and milk.
Into butter, sugar and egg mixture add flour mixture alternately with sour cream mixture.
Add the vanilla and chocolate chips.
Pour half the batter into greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle half the cinnamon sugar mixture over batter.
Add remaining batter and sprinkle with rest of cinnamon sugar.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: honey chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Melt butter and add remaining ingredients.
Roll chicken in mixture to coat both sides.
Arrange meaty side up in single layer with sauce over it.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serve with rice, peas and salad.

title: beefaroni skillet dinner
directions: Brown ground beef, drain.
Add chopped onion. Stir well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until macaroni is tender. Add more water if needed.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease and flour a 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, then add chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoons on slightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: ham quiche
directions: Mix eggs, milk, pepper, salt, seasoning, onion, onion tops and green pepper well.
Add shredded cheese, ham and mushrooms.
Pour into a 9-inch prepared pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Crumble 4 slices cooked bacon on top.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: hot cider punch
directions: Combine spices and tie in cheesecloth bag.
In a 2-quart saucepan, combine brown sugar, cider, orange juice, lemon juice and ginger ale.
Add spice bag; bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: strudel
directions: Mix
first
7 ingredients well and divide into 3 parts. Roll out
dough	in pie shape.
Spread with apricot preserves and orange mixture.
Sprinkle on coconut, pecans, raisins and sugar/cinnamon
mixture.
Roll
up jelly roll fashion, tucking ends
under
securely.
Place
the 3 rolls on a greased cookie sheet.
Drizzle
top
with	a
little oil and sprinkle on sugar/cinnamon.
Score the rolls
with sharp knife.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut up while still hot.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix all of the ingredients well except tortillas and salsa. Divide the filling into 5 parts.
Spread one part on each tortilla and roll up tightly.
Cover well with plastic wrap and twist ends. Refrigerate for several hours.
When ready to serve, cut in slices 1/2 to 3/4-inch wide.
Serve with salsa as the dip.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Layer coconut, pecans and cake mix in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend the cream cheese and powdered sugar and place spoonfuls (blots) on top of cake mix.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: peppered pita pizzas
directions: Heat 4 teaspoons of oil in small skillet.
Chop the peppers; saute in the skillet until just soft, about 5 minutes.
Spread 1 teaspoon of olive oil on each pita, then spread 1 tablespoon of sauce on each pita.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Decorate with peppers and spices.
Heat in oven on 400° for approximately 5 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.

title: string bean and mushroom salad
directions: In a large saucepan bring water to a boil. Add beans and salt to taste.
Cook about 5 minutes or until tender.
Drain and cool. Wash and dry mushrooms; slice thinly.
Prepare sauce by whisking together the mustard, vinegar, cumin, Tabasco, salt and pepper. Slowly add oil while whisking vigorously.
In a salad bowl; place beans, mushrooms, onions and chives.
Pour sauce over the vegetables and toss gently.

title: potato filling
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Drain and mash.
In skillet, saute onion and celery in butter until tender.
Add mashed potatoes with bread cubes, 1/2 cup milk, salt, pepper, poultry seasoning and parsley.
Mix well.
Beat in egg and remaining 1 cup milk until mixture is smooth.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Serves 6.

title: easy meat and rice
directions: Combine both cans of soup (concentrated) with meat in a crock-pot.
Cook on low for about 6 hours.
Serve over cooked rice.
Serves 4.

title: greek cornbread
directions: Cook broccoli until tender, but crisp; drain well.
Mix all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Split and butter.
Cut into squares.
Quick bread.

title: debbie's party dip
directions: Stir together the night before serving and use a dip with Doritos or corn chips.

title: dilly beans
directions: Pack raw green beans in hot pints. To each pint add 1/2 tsp. red cayenne pepper, 1 clove garlic and 1 head dill.
Put 2 c. water, 2 c. cider vinegar (not white) and 1/4 c. canning salt in saucepan and boil a minute or two. Pour this into jars and seal. No need to process, just let set a week or so and enjoy.

title: cheese soup
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients.
Blend in flour, mustard and chicken stock.
Cook 5 minutes.
Blend in Cheddar and Parmesan cheeses and seasonings.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Be sure to stir before dishing each bowl.
Can sprinkle more Parmesan/Romano cheese on top when serving.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream the rest and add to dry. Add bananas and nuts last and stir.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: chicken-amaretto curry
directions: Heat butter in a large skillet. Brown chicken on all sides. Add mushrooms, lemon and Amaretto. Simmer 5 minutes. Add remaining ingredients. Cook, stirring over low heat until thickened. Serve over rice with pea pods and tomatoes. Serves 6.

title: strawberry jello pie
directions: Pour can milk into bowl and chill in refrigerator real good, or 2 hours in freezer.
Beat milk until like Cool Whip.
Pour in sugar; beat again.
Put jello and water in bowl and mix real good. Add jello to milk mixture and beat again until fluffy.
Pour mixture into crust made from vanilla wafers (crumble cookies into bottom of pie plate and stand around edges).
Freeze pie for about 4 hours and keep in freezer when not eating.

title: pork chop and potato bake
directions: Brown pork chops in a lightly greased skillet.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Meanwhile, in a bowl, combine soup, milk and sour cream.
Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and half the French-fried onions.
Spoon int a 9 x 13-inch pan and arrange pork chops on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and onions on top; return to oven for 5 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Prepare tortellini as per instructions.
Drain and cool.
Cut pepperoni into 1/4-inch slices, then quarter each slice.
Prepare dressing as per instructions.
Cook broccoli.
Cool and chop into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients and chill before serving.

title: special lemony chicken
directions: In plastic bag, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Add chicken, a few pieces at a time; shake to coat.
In large skillet, brown chicken in margarine until golden brown.
Add lemon juice and mushrooms.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes or until tender.
Serve with rice; garnish as desired.

title: barbecue sauce for meats
directions: Brown onions and celery in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 15 to 30 minutes.
This sauce can be stored, frozen or canned for future use.
Yields 4 quarts.
Makes delicious barbecue spareribs.

title: beer batter for fish
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine batter ingredients and beat well. Fill deep electric fry pan with oil 1/2-inch deep.
Heat oil to 375°.
Pat fillets dry and coat with batter.
Drop fish in oil and brown 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cantonese chicken dinner
directions: Pat chicken pieces dry with paper towel.
Heat oil in a large flameproof casserole.
Working in batches, brown chicken until golden brown on all sides. Drain on paper towel.
Pour all but 2 tablespoons fat from casserole.
Saute onion until tender, about 5 minutes.
Return chicken to casserole. Add chicken broth, soy sauce and ginger root.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add cabbage and cook 5 minutes longer. Add mushrooms, bean sprouts and bamboo shoots.
Cook 5 minutes longer. Mix cornstarch and water in a small bowl until smooth. Stir in casserole.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens. Sprinkle with toasted almonds.
Serve over Chinese noodles, if you wish.

title: fruit cocktail-nuts cake
directions: Mix and cream first 5 ingredients.
Pour into lightly greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch deep cake pan.
Mix the brown sugar and nuts together and sprinkle onto the batter.
Place in oven and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Spread icing on cake while hot.
